can lead to creating competitive advantage and IP. You will conceptualise and implement algorithmic solutions to challenging problems. This can include machine learning techniques, but also defining and analysing product use cases. Your profile includes... An advanced quantitative degree - e.g Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or related fields. Several years of professional experience with a track record of bringing Data Science use cases into production. Demonstrable ability to develop data science products and work with large structured and unstructured data sets. Strong programming skills in Python and R. Experience in using a wide range of ML frameworks such as SciKit, Tensorflow, Pymc in production. Strong inner drive to get things done: you''re not waiting for others to manage or tell you what to do, you are self-driven and an internal change-maker. Quality ambassador: you combine an obsession with research quality with a highly pragmatic prioritisation of tasks to maximize your efficiency. Organisational mastermind: you are able to manage simultaneous external stakeholders and projects with overlapping deadlines and requests. What else makes Dalia awesome? No "ninja" culture - teamwork here is paramount, and that means others will help you when you need it. Mentorship is always available. Occasional remote work is possible. A well-stocked kitchen, where you can request grocery items. A team boat ( https://daliaresearch.com/blog-how-we-built-a-boat/ ) that we built ourselves!', 'Senior Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'Dalia Research', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4707, 'Project A ist der Operational VC, der neben Kapital ein großes Netzwerk und exklusiven Zugang zu einem breiten Spektrum an Services bietet. Der Berliner Investor verwaltet 260 Millionen Euro, mit denen er Technologie-Startups finan- ziert. Kern von Project A ist das Team aus 100 erfahrenen Experten, die die Port- foliounternehmen operativ unterstützen in Bereichen wie Software Engineering, Digitales Marketing, Design, Kommunikation, Business Intelligence, Sales und Recruiting. Zum Portfolio gehören Unternehmen wie Artisense, Catawiki, Horizn Studios, KRY, LIQID, Spryker, uberall und WorldRemit. Mehr Informationen auf www.project-a.com und auf dem Blog insights.project-a.com. Wir suchen: Ein neues Teammitglied für unser A-Team. Was wird dich herausfordern? Entwicklung datengetriebener Anwendungen für unsere Ventures: Data Warehouses, Marketing-Automatisierungen, Recommendation Engines, etc. Integration verschiedenster Datenquellen in flexible und konsistente Repräsentationen. Bereitstellung der Daten für alle Mitarbeiter und IT-Systeme in der Organisation durch verschiedene Front-ends und Schnittstellen Anpassung unserer Tools an sich stets verändernde Herausforderungen Eigenverantwortliche Mitarbeit in einem agilen Softwareentwicklungsprozess und in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem BI Team Welche Eigenschaften tragen zu deinem Erfolg bei? Einen Masterabschluss in Informatik oder einen vergleichbaren Abschluss Großes Interesse an Daten und Algorithmen sowie daran komplexe Problemstellungen effizient zu lösen Beherrschung der Grundwerkzeuge der Softwareentwicklung: Programmierung in mehreren Sprachen, HTTP und aktuelle Webtechnologien, sicherer Umgang mit der Unix-Kommandozeile und einfache Systemadministration, Versionsverwaltung, Grundverständnis des Zusammenspiels von Software mit Hauptspeicher, Festplatte und CPU Tiefgreifendes Wissen zur Funktionsweise von Datenbanken Bereitschaft dich in neue Programmiersprachen und Technologien einzuarbeiten Grundverständnis von Mathematik und von Verfahren des maschinellen Lernens Die Fähigkeit, mit Data Science- Projekten ein Business voranzubringen (näheres dazu findest du hier) Unser aktueller Stack: Mac oder Linux, Python, Bash-Skripte, Makefiles Unser eigenes open-source Datenintegrationsframework Mara (näheres dazu findest du hier), aber auch Airflow, Luigi PostgreSQL für ETL (näheres dazu findest du hier), Kinesis & BigQuery für Event Collection und -Abfrage AWS, GCP, Azure, Saltstack, Ansible Was du von uns erwarten kannst: Werde Teil eines hochprofessionellen und motivierten Teams Erhalte die Chance, den Aufbau neu gegründeter Unternehmen mitzuerleben und durch eigene Ideen voranzubringen Entwickle dich optimal weiter durch ein Höchstmaß an Gestaltungsspielräumen Arbeite an einem hochmodernen, top ausgestatteten Arbeitsplatz mitten in Berlin Profitiere von einem kommunikativen, anregenden und inspirierenden Umfeld Lust bekommen, an unserer Erfolgsstory mitzuwirken? Wir freuen uns auf deine Onlinebewerbung. Empfehlen und 1000€ verdienen', 'Data Engineer/Data Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Project A Services GmbH & Co. KG', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4708, 'DATA SCIENTIST (M/W) Was Sie bei ixto erwartet: Ein junges, vielseitiges Team Abwechslungsreiche Herausforderungen bei unseren Kunden vom Mittelstand bis zum Großkonzern Erschließung neuer Technologien für die Anwendung in DWH- und BI-Lösungen Entwicklung innovativer Projektideen in verschiedenen Schwerpunktthemen wie Internet of Things (IoT) und Machine Learning Fachliche und technische Kommunikation mit unseren Kunden Erfassung von funktionalen und technischen Anforderungen Beratung der Kunden für optimale Lösungsarchitekturen Realisierung von DWH- und BI-Lösungen Durchführung von PoCs und Workshops Das sollten Sie mitbringen: Abgeschlossenes Studium mit dem Schwerpunkt Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, BWL, Physik, Mathematik, Naturwissenschaften oder eine vergleichbare Berufsausbildung Kenntnisse im Bereich relationaler und multidimensionaler Datenbanken Hohes Maß an Begeisterung für Datenanalysen und Business Intelligence Erfahrungen in Sensordaten-Analyse, Machine Learning und Programmierkenntnisse in Python, Java, C/C++ und R sind von Vorteil Analytisches und vernetztes Denken Kunden- und Serviceorientierung Kommunikationsstärke und Teamfähigkeit Reisebereitschaft Was wir Ihnen bieten: Wir legen größten Wert auf ein gutes Betriebsklima. Mitarbeiter Meetings, interner Wissensaustausch und viele gemeinsame Aktivitäten fördern die teamübergreifende Zusammenarbeit und das Gemeinschaftsgefühl. Wir entwerfen persönliche Entwicklungsmodelle und vereinbaren individuelle Ziele. Jeder unserer Mitarbeiter ist beteiligt am Unternehmenserfolg; wir bieten einen Beitrag zur Altersvorsorge und Zuschläge für besondere Flexibilität und Reisebereitschaft. Für die Vereinbarkeit von Beruf und Familie bieten wir Teilzeitmodelle, Sabbaticals und Elternzeit auch für Väter.', 'DATA SCIENTIST (M/W)', '2019-06-03', 'ixto', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4709, 'bonify – a Berlin based FinTech Startup enables customers to benefit from their credit scoring and financial data. We give customers free & easy access to their credit score and let them upload additional relevant data. Then we offer tools and personalized recommendations to help optimize our customer’s financial situation. Founded in 2015 by key executives of McKinsey and Zalando, bonify has received significant funding from international leading VCs, e.g., Mosaic Ventures and Ribbit Capital, and successful entrepreneurs, e.g., Zalando founders and Raisin founders. These will be your tasks You will lead and supervise all partner communication with Risk- Managers in banks Manage the development and deployment of the Data Science solutions end-to-end Oversee the process of developing models for estimating credit-risk Working with our data, this include Data-cleaning, Data-Modelling and Data-processing Manage a cross functional team (Data-Science and Business Intelligence) High competence in formulating business goals into analytics tasks You''re offering these qualifications You have a Masters Degree or above preferably in either Computer Sciences or related You have already acquired experience in project management with high focus on Research You have a good understanding of Data Privacy laws & Data Security or are keen to learn very fast about it Good understanding of Micro-services and creating architectures based on this principle Good understanding of REST-Api’s and other forms (like queueing systems esp. RabbitMQ) of inter process communication Knowledge of Relational and Non-Relational databases Very high Python proficiency Following tools have no secret for you: Graphana, ELK-Stack, Pandas, Scitkit-learn, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, RabbitMQ, Docker, Jenkins Ability to perform even with short deadline Exceptional conversational skills Exceptional planning skills for research and development projects Highly creative in finding solutions for difficult tasks in a short time frame Proficiency in German Language (At least C1) We''re offering these benefits Shape the future of the analytics department Have an enormous chance to professional and personal growth Take responsibility from day one. Take ownership of projects. See your innovation in the product. Use our budget for education and growth (language Courses free Books) . Enjoy the usual Start-up stuff: Dart, Table Football, Fresh Fruits Enjoy free coffee and free beer! Enjoy a workplace in the heart of Kreuzberg.', 'Lead Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'bonify', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4710, 'Deine Aufgaben: Analyse und Aufbereitung von Daten für die IT und die Fachabteilungen Prüfung der Daten auf Konsistenz und Qualität Automatisierte Bereinigung der Daten Beratung der Fachabteilungen bei Anforderungen zu Datenanalysen Konzeption und Dokumentation Matching von Daten der Schwestergesellschaften Dein Profil: Abgeschlossenes Studium der Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Mathematik oder eine vergleichbare Ausbildung Mehrjährige Berufserfahrung als Data Analyst von komplexen Datenstrukturen Sehr gute Kenntnisse im Umgang mit relationalen Datenbanken (PostgreSQL) Datenmanagement-Knowhow mit Talend, Microsoft SQL Server und Python-Kenntnisse von Vorteil Sowie eine exzellente methodisch-analytische Denk- und Arbeitsweise Fähigkeit, komplexe Zusammenhänge strukturiert darzustellen Teamplayer, hohe Verantwortungsbewusstsein und Zuverlässigkeit Selbständiges Arbeiten und hohes Eigenengagement Gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift Dein Mehrwert: Ideen entwickeln: Erfahre eine hohe Kollegialität, ein Prinzip der offenen Tür und viel Gestaltungsspielraum. Vorankommen: Bei der GVL entwickelst Du Deine Kenntnisse durch interne oder externe Fort- und Weiterbildungen und durch regelmäßige Mitarbeitergespräche. Außerdem profitierst Du von flexiblen Arbeitszeiten. Gesund bleiben: Ob Vitamine, Bewegung oder Entspannung: Wasser und Obst erhältst Du gratis. Zudem fördern wir Deinen Besuch im Fitness-Studio und zahlen einen Zuschuss für eine mobile Massage am Arbeitsplatz. Informieren: Mitarbeiterversammlungen, Intranet und Online-Mitarbeitermagazin versorgen Dich regelmäßig mit Informationen zur GVL und zur Branche. Vorsorgen fürs Alter: Die GVL bietet dir als Mitarbeiter die Möglichkeit der betrieblichen Altersvorsorge in Form einer Gehaltsumwandlung. Genießen: Lass uns nicht nur zusammen arbeiten, sondern auch gemeinsam abschalten: Ob bei Sportveranstaltungen, während des Betriebsausflugs, auf Firmenfeiern oder beim regelmäßigen Feierabendbier im Garten. Haben wir Dein Interesse geweckt? Dann sende uns Deine vollständigen Bewerbungsunterlagen mit Angabe Deines frühestmöglichen Einstiegstermins sowie Deiner Gehaltsvorstellungen zu.', 'Data-Analyst / Data Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Gesellschaft zur Verwertung von Leistungsschutzrechten mbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4711, 'Für einen Kunden im Bereich Big Data suche ich zum nächstmöglichen Zeitpunkt einen Data Scientist (m/w/x). Ihre Aufgaben: Beratung der Kunden in allen Belangen Aufnahme und Analyse der Kundenanforderung rund um die Themen Big Data und Advanced Analytics Anwendung und Entwicklung von analytischer Technologien und Applikationen Schulungen und Workshops für Kunden und Mitarbeitern Ihr Profil: Abgeschlossenes Studium der (Wirtschafts-) Informatik oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation Umfangreiches Wissen in R und Python Zusätzlich Kenntnisse in relationalen und NoSQL Datenbanksystemen Uneingeschränkte Reisebereitschaft Ihre Vorteile: 50% Homeoffice / 50% Reisebereitschaft Aktuelle Zertifizierungen sowie Trainings und Workshops Unbefristete Anstellung bei einem Microsoft zertifiziertem Unternehmen Attraktives Gehaltspaket Die Beschreibung trifft auf Sie zu und Ihr Interesse wurde geweckt? Dann senden Sie noch heute Ihre vollständigen Bewerbungsunterlagen an meine E-Mail Adresse: j.beardmore@nigelfrank.com oder kontaktieren Sie mich, Frau Joanna Beardmore, direkt unter der Nummer +49 (0)303 080 8807 damit wir weitere Details besprechen können. Ihre Vorteile mit Nigel Frank zu arbeiten: Nigel Frank International ist die weltweit führende Personalberatung, welche sich auf die Vermittlung von Fach- und Führungskräften in den Bereichen Microsoft Dynamics (AX, NAV & CRM), SharePoint, MS Business Intelligence, MS Infrastruktur und weitere MS-Technologien, wie u.a. im .NET-Bereich spezialisiert hat. Wir verfügen über das größte Stellenangebot in unserem Spezialgebiet und haben uns schnell zum Marktführer der Microsoft Dynamics Personalrekrutierung entwickelt. Täglich bieten wir weit über 1000 offene Jobs. Wir sichern Ihnen Diskretion, Integrität und persönliche Betreuung, Fachwissen, Kundenbeziehungen und Professionalität! www.nigelfrank.com', 'Microsoft BI Consultant', '2019-06-03', 'Nigel Frank International Limited', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4712, 'DATANOMIQ ist der herstellerunabhängige Beratungs- und Service-Partner für Business Intelligence, Business Analytics und Data Science. Wie kein zweites Unternehmen erschließen wir die vielfältigen Möglichkeiten durch Big Data und künstliche Intelligenz in allen Bereichen der Wertschöpfungskette, um einen signifikanten Wertbeitrag zu verwirklichen. Dabei setzen wir auf die besten Köpfe und das umfassendste Methoden- und Technologieportfolio aus der Digitalisierung. Unsere Praxiserfahrungen aus einer Vielzahl von Big Data-Projekten, der Zugang zur Spitze der deutschen Datenwirtschaft und Domänenwissen in ergänzenden Themen wie Datensicherheit und Datenschutz verschaffen uns eine einzigartige Marktposition. Auf das Lösungsportfolio von DATANOMIQ setzen Unternehmen aus den unterschiedlichsten Branchen – von der Industrie, Handel und Energieversorgern über Banken und Versicherungen bis hin zu E-Commerce-Anbietern. Data Scientist in Berlin Deine Aufgaben Algorithmenentwicklung für unterschiedlichste Analyseprojekte Explorative Datenanalyse, Data Mining, Predictive Analytics, Process Mining, Machine Learning Mitarbeit in Kundenprojekten an der Erstellung innovativer (Software-)Lösungen für unterschiedliche Branchen Projektbezogene analytische und kommunikative Aufgaben Dein Profil Erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium in den Fächern Physik, Ingenieurwesen, (Wirtschafts-)Informatik, (Wirtschafts-)Mathematik oder Wirtschaftswissenschaften mit starkem quantitativen Fokus bzw. Statistik Mehrere Jahre Berufserfahrung im Bereich im Data Science mit Schwerpunkt auf Business Analytics Fortgeschrittene Statistikkenntnisse und mindestens Grundkenntnisse in gängigen Machine Learning Methoden „Fließend“ in mindestens zwei der folgenden Programmiersprachen: Java, R, Python, Scala, Octave, SPSS, JavaScript, SQL Sicherer Umgang sowohl auf Windows- als auch auf Linux-Umgebungen Erste Erfahrung im Umgang mit BI-Tools wie IBM Cognos, Power BI, MicroStrategy oder Qlik wünschenswert Optional: Erfahrung im Umgang mit NoSQL-Datenbanken, Apache Hadoop, Apache Spark Optional: Erfahrung mit Neuronalen Netzen / Deep Learning Network Verhandlungssichere Englisch- und Deutschkenntnisse Hohes Maß an Eigeninitiative und Zielorientierung Wenn Du gerne in einem dynamischen Umfeld mit flachen Hierarchien und kurzen Entscheidungswegen arbeiten möchtest, sende uns bitte Deine aussagekräftige Bewerbung mit dem Stichwort „Data Scientist“ unter Angabe Deiner Gehaltsvorstellung sowie möglichen Eintrittstermins an jobs@datanomiq.de. Wir freuen uns darauf, Dich kennenzulernen!', 'Data Scientist (m/f)', '2019-06-03', 'DATANOMIQ GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4713, 'Your tasks and responsibilities Active member of a highly interdisciplinary and cross-organizational and cross-corporate team, including scientists from multiple European Pharma companies Contribute to the implementation and evaluation of a deep learning platform to leverage data in computational chemistry, pharmacokinetics, and toxicology Extensively validate and further improve the deep learning platform for various property predictions of drug development compounds Research, design, and implement deep learning algorithms for analysis problems related to prediction of properties of small molecules and proteomic data Generate direct impact on our discovery projects to help patients The position is within the Machine Learning Research department, located in Berlin The applicants are expected to start July 2019 Please note: the position is limited for 36 months Who you are PhD degree in bioinformatics, computational biology or chemistry, computer science or related fields and a solid background in chemistry, biology and machine learning Profound experience with state-of-the-art machine learning methods (e.g. graph convolution, representation learning, multitask learning) and model selection concepts is an imperative prerequisite Excellent programming skills in Python (PyTorch or TensorFlow, RDKit) are essential, additional skills in R, or C++ would be of advantage. Proficiency in writing clean, fast, idiomatic Python code. Expertise in handling, processing, integrating and analyzing data sets related to research in the pharmaceutical industry You are a highly creative person with outstanding problem-solving ability and the willingness to undertake challenging analysis tasks Strong interpersonal skills, excellent written and verbal communication, and the ability to work effectively both independently and in cross-functional teams Willingness to travel between research sites Oral and written proficiency in English is mandatory Your application Are you looking for a new challenge where you can show your passion for innovation? Are you interested in working as part of a global team to improve people’s lives? Then send us your online application including cover letter, CV and references. Bayer welcomes applications from all individuals, regardless of race, national origin, gender, age, physical characteristics, social origin, disability, union membership, religion, family status, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression or any unlawful criterion under applicable law. We are committed to treating all applicants fairly and avoiding discrimination. Country: Germany Location: Berlin Reference Code: 40077 Functional Area: Entry Level:', 'Research Scientist - Machine learning/Deep learning (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Bayer', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4714, 'Werde Wegbegleiter der digitalen Transformation. Unterstütze uns als Data Scientist (w/m/x) in Berlin, Hamburg oder Stuttgart. WHO WE ARE WE CREATE DIGITAL CHAMPIONS! Seit 1995 unterstützen wir Branchenführer wie Mercedes-Benz, Bosch, Kodak Alaris oder Sick dabei, das Potenzial der digitalen Transformation zu nutzen und Millionen von Kunden außergewöhnliche Erfahrungen zu bieten. Als starker Partner begleiten wir Unternehmen durch den gesamten Prozess der Digitalisierung: Von Innovation & Strategy, UX, Marketing & KI, Commerce und Technology bis hin zum Aufbau digitaler Einheiten. Einer für alle, alle für einen! Über 600 Kolleginnen und Kollegen betreuen unsere Kunden von weltweit elf Standorten aus: Stuttgart, Berlin, Hamburg und Karlsruhe sowie Bangalore, Detroit, Peking, Lissabon, London, San José und VaE. Was uns vereint? Der Mut, neue Wege zu gehen, gegenseitige Achtsamkeit, Teamwork und der Wille, nachhaltig etwas zu verändern. Wir sind diconium. Deutschlands größtes unabhängiges Digital Business- und Technologieunternehmen. WHAT WE OFFER Raum für persönliche und fachliche Entwicklung in einem integrativen Umfeld interessante Projekte in unterschiedlichen Wirtschaftsfeldern eine Chance für dich, mit state-of-the-art Architekturen und Algorithmen zu arbeiten individuelle Balance zwischen Programmierung und Beratung ein interdisziplinäres Team, welches sich durch Ehrlichkeit und offene Kommunikation auszeichnet bei uns hast du immer die Chance, deine Meinung zu äußern und stößt damit immer auf offene Ohren du kannst dein Kernfeld mitbestimmen (z.B. Modelling, Consulting, Produktentwicklung) und deine eigenen Ideen beisteuern, um damit das Team zu verstärken WHO YOU ARE du hast Erfahrung mit Data, Analytics oder Modelling in einer Programmiersprache deiner Wahl (wir nutzen derzeit Python, Java und R) du arbeitest analytisch und strukturiert du bist offen, dich in neue Technologien und Strategien einzuarbeiten für dich ist Kommunikation kein Buzzword sondern sowohl innerhalb des Teams als auch zwischen einzelnen Units eine Voraussetzung für tägliches Arbeiten dein Englisch ist verhandlungssicher WHY DICONIUM Verschiedene Möglichkeiten für deine persönliche Entwicklung (z.B. Zertifizierungen, Konferenzen, Open-Source Fridays uvm.) interdisziplinäre Teams, "You-first-culture", internationales Umfeld kollaborative Problemlösungen und reger Austausch zwischen den Standorten flexible Arbeitszeiten und die Möglichkeit zu Home Office Corporate Benefits wie Jobticket, frisches Obst, Getränke und Firmenevents sowie eine unterstützende Firmenkultur INSPIRED? Stell dich uns vor, wenn du willst, ganz unkompliziert nur mit deinem CV - idealerweise über unser Onlineportal oder per Mail an jobs@diconium.com. diconium group Rommelstraße 11 | 70376 Stuttgart Miriam Ott | people & organisation 0711 29 92 0 | jobs@diconium.com www.diconium.com/career Wir freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung!', 'Data Scientist (w/m/x)', '2019-06-03', 'diconium group', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4715, 'Wir helfen unseren Kunden dabei, die richtigen Lösungen für Ihr Geschäft zu finden, indem wir sie in den Bereichen Data Analytics und Artificial Intelligence beraten und begleiten. Sie bringen sich folgendermaßen in unser Team ein: Analyse, Extraktion und Dokumentation von geschäftsentscheidendem Wissen und Kundenanforderungen Konzeption von Data Processing sowie Data Analytics Lösungen mit Hilfe von neuesten analytischen Tools und Algorithmen, Modellierung von Datenschemata Technische Umsetzung und Implementierung von Lösungen bei Kunden Kundenkommunikation, Visualisierung von Daten und Aufbereitung von analytischen Erkenntnissen Ihr Hintergrund Ihre bisherigen Erfahrungen haben Sie zu der Person gemacht, die Sie heute sind: ein lern- und leistungsbereiter Teamplayer, der andere begeistern kann, Spaß am Organisieren und kundenorientierten Arbeiten hat, sehr gut Englisch spricht und bereit ist, regelmäßig zu reisen. Ihre Basics: Abgeschlossene Qualifikation in Mathematik, Physik, Astrophysik, Chemie, Informatik oder vergleichbar mit Schwerpunkt in Text-Analyse, Computer Vision, AI oder Predictive Analytics Know-How in den Bereichen Datenanalyse, Data Mining und Statistik Sicheres Beherrschen des Tools R Sehr gute Kenntnisse im Bereich der Datenbereinigung, Modellierung und Vorverarbeitung Erfahrung mit der Visualisierung von Daten, analytischen Ergebnissen und im Bereich Machine Learning Ein Plus, kein muss Bereitschaft zur Einarbeitung in Java Fortgeschrittene Erfahrungen mit Reporting Tools Unser Hier und Jetzt Warum Sie zu T-Systems Multimedia Solutions GmbH kommen sollten? Weil Sie bei uns unter besten Bedingungen die digitale Revolution mitgestalten können: Flexibles Arbeitszeitmodell Mobiles Arbeiten und Home Office Betriebliche Altersvorsorge Individuelle Weiterbildungsangebote Reisezeit ist Arbeitszeit Fach-Communities Bereit für die digitale Revolution? Dann bewerben Sie sich! Zeigen Sie uns, wer Sie heute sind, wo Sie hinwollen oder wo Sie bereits angekommen sind. Ihre Ansprechpartnerin Sie haben noch Fragen oder suchen nach fachspezifischen Informationen? Zögern Sie nicht und kontaktieren Sie mich jederzeit. Carolina matthies +49 351 - 2820 - 7555 | T-Systems Multimedia Solutions.com/karriere', 'Data Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'T-Systems Multimedia Solutions', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4716, '- Hi, - We are the moovel / reach now technology teams! We are about 90 happy people in technology roles working on our fascinating mobility products. One part of our services are the different apps we build. For these we need data to enable smart decisions and constantly improve the product. Together with a data scientist you are going to establish and enhance solid data pipelines and connect relevant data bases for traffic & demand prediction and related use cases. First a quick look at us: - Daimler AG and BMW Group are bundling their mobility services in the areas of Carsharing, Ride-Hailing, Parking, Charging and Multimodal Platforms, and create a new global player comprising of five joint ventures. moovel Group is joining forces with ReachNow - and becomes REACH NOW Our vision is a planet without traffic jams. Our mission is to transform cities by providing the most convenient and sustainable mobility solutions. We create outstanding products with technical excellence, an agile mindset, an open feedback and failure culture and fun at work. moovel (REACH NOW) is part of two global corporations, but at the heart of it we are still a start-up. We act as a partner for cities, transport networks and mobility service providers with the goal of making cities smarter and creating an operating system for urban mobility that provides access to appropriate mobility options in urban areas and paves the way for the future with autonomous vehicles. Currently, 300 employees work in small creative teams in Germany and the US at four locations - Hamburg, Berlin, Stuttgart and Portland. Some of the things you will do: - You are part of an interdisciplinary agile working team, responsible to empower smart mobility solutions Architect and create data processing pipelines on our AWS cloud infrastructure Scouting of external data sources that are useful for our business Ingest data from internal and external sources (databases, APIs, web scraping etc.) Preprocess data in a scalable way Work together with a data scientist to implement Feature Engineering Save data in different and appropriate data stores Deploy and maintain machine learning models as a service on our AWS cloud infrastructure Collaborate with other teams, contribute and give feedback to pull requests Work with source code in GitHub Enterprise Cloud About you: - You have 3 or more years of industry experience in Data Engineering You have at least a basic knowledge of the basic machine learning algorithms to support the data scientist in Feature Engineering tasks and deployment of machine learning models You are an expert in working with various data stores and can make informed decisions when to use which database You are a very good Software Engineer and are experienced with AWS, Linux & Bash, Container technologies, Continuous Integration and Testing You have a strong demand for delivering quality products You know how to create and implement machine learning algorithms and advanced statistics in Python and Scala You are familiar with and use engineering best practices with a focus on high-quality production code combining the art of Software Engineering and Data Science You own a Bachelor or Master in Informatics or another quantitative field You are on top of the full pipeline of data, analytics, machine learning algorithms and production ready product You are able to work in a fast changing and challenging environment with a focus on collaboration Benefits: - Choose your own hardware Working with newest technologies + microservices Working on products with a high impact on society International teams Flexible working hours Free breakfast, good coffee & fresh fruits Monthly mobility budget If you have any questions or are in need for further information feel free to contact Mr. Janosch Fingerhut +49 30 549073811', 'Data Engineer (f/m/d) Traffic &amp; Demand Prediction', '2019-06-03', 'Moovel Group GmbH ( becomes REACH NOW )', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4717, 'At the heart of our success is our team. We are searching for a talented Data Scientist to join our adventure and play a key role in our growth. About Omio Driven by our team of over 300 people from more than 40 different countries, Omio is changing the way we travel across Europe. With Omio you can compare and book trains, buses and flights to anywhere in Europe with one simple search, on mobile, app or desktop. By offering transparent pricing and easy booking, Omio makes travel planning simple, flexible and personal. With over 800 European transportation partners across 15 countries, Omio is one of Europe''s fastest growing travel companies backed by 20 million monthly users and the world''s leading tech investors. Data Scientist - Product Intelligence f/m/d ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- You are a creative thinker and data guru who can drive great customer experience through data-driven insights and personalisation. Your tasks Collaborate closely with the Product team to develop a customer-driven and data-driven strategy to drive product evolution Perform statistical analyses - including A/B tests and pre/post analyses - on feature usage to advise on feature adoption and evolution Develop customer segmentations and path analyses to drive feature evolution and web/app personalisation Develop insights and predictive models on key KPIs such as Retention and CLV Prototype data-driven features based on insights and/or machine learning models Generate tactical insights from analytics and visualisation to drive product strategy Act as an advocate of our company''s data-driven culture: produce reports that are actionable, dashboards that are diagnostic, and recommendations that drive growth Your Profile You proactively take action, drive toward clarity, and think holistically You thrive in a diverse, interdisciplinary environment You possess exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, enabling effective collaboration with business and technical stakeholders You have a scientific mindset; backed by solid analytical problem solving skills, strong attention to detail, and a mild obsession with data accuracy You enjoy informing, influencing, and shaping product decisions with data You are proficient in SQL with an understanding of database management You have development experience in either Python or R You have experience with reporting tools such as Tableau or Excel You are grounded in Statistics You have strong experience with econometrics, data mining, and/or machine learning You have experience in one of - product analytics, customer analytics, marketing analytics, recommendation systems - in an e-commerce environment 3+ years non-academic experience in data science What''s in it for you? #LifeAtOmio Annual travel allowance to fund your trips and adventures Catered weekly lunches and monthly company events German classes and yoga sessions An educational budget for courses or workshops to help you gain even more skills A diverse team of more than 45 nationalities Why you should apply We encourage you to apply even if you''re still developing some of these skills! We value diversity and welcome all applicants regardless of ethnicity, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, age or disability. Ready, Set, GoForIt Apply here in English.', 'Data Scientist - Product Intelligence', '2019-06-03', 'Omio', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4718, 'We’re DCMN – the growth marketing partner for digital businesses and startups. Our holistic, data-driven approach combines technology with expert knowledge to grow the market leaders of tomorrow. Our vision is bold: we want everyone in the world to use one of our client’s services. If you have the drive to get us there, let’s talk. We are looking for a full-stack Machine Learning Expert (m/f/d) to join our Data Science team! Responsibilities: As a Machine Learning Expert, you will build tools and frameworks to support all areas of the marketing value creation chain. This spans from using Bayesian Inference to predict future website traffic to using LSTM-Neural-Networks to understand the language of our client’s customers. You should have experience with advanced methods in statistical analysis and machine learning, including Deep Neural Networks, MCMC Sampling, Time-Series-Analyses, Linear Programming, and an advanced understanding of developing statistical models. You can expect to be part of a team of enthusiastic Data Scientists who are constantly developing new products. We support every branch of DCMN’s growth strategy for the market leaders of tomorrow with a huge variety of tools, reports, and insights. Minimum Qualifications: Besides having excellent theoretical knowledge, you define yourself as a full-stack machine learning expert: You know how to evaluate your models, have a lot of programming experience in Python within a team, and love clean code. You also feel comfortable setting up the occasional database, managing our cloud-based job system, and are not afraid of building a frontend to showcase your newest data product. You should know where and how to use the toolbox of data science to build all kinds of data products from start to finish You collect needs and use-cases to build and implement machine learning models and products. You understand that evaluation not only concerns your models but also the final product. You also realize that explaining and presenting the results of your work is absolutely essential for a successful product. Benefits: Awesome office space in the heart of Berlin full of radically supportive colleagues Support for your personal and professional growth, whether this means regular massage sessions and pilates classes or an overseas conference trip Flexibility to manage your own hours and work from home whenever you need A multicultural work environment, plus the chance to visit our international offices and apply for our exchange program within our international locations No hierarchies, freedom and full responsibility from day one. We believe top-down hierarchies just limit our progress – so we’ve created a whole new way of working Can’t wait to get started? Then we’d love to hear from you. Please send us your CV along with any relevant documents and your earliest possible starting date. And don’t hesitate to reach out if you have any questions! Please note: We prefer applications via our application form (click the ‚Apply‚ button on this website). It really makes life easier for us and means your application can be processed quicker. For further questions please do not hesitate to contact: Silke Hofman s.hofman@dcmn.com 0176-40456113 or Mertcan Uzun m.uzun@dcmn.com 0162 1322936', 'DCMN: Lead Data Scientist (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'media.net berlinbrandenburg', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4719, 'YOUR ROLE We are looking for an ambitious and talented Data Scientist who wants to leave its mark in the mobile gaming industry. The right candidate has a pragmatic approach to games and is eager to design and develop business metrics, create insightful automated reports, dashboards and data visualization formats to track and convert the results into actionable recommendations. In order to set you up for success, we provide everything you need within our dynamic and employee-centric company structure. You will work closely with the Data Engineer, whilst showing full responsibility and ownership of your project – you are the game! YOUR CONTRIBUTION Strong understanding of machine learning and data modelling Excellent analytical skills and tech-savinness Develop an analytics tool with the Data Engineer to provide actionable insights into our audience behaviour, gaming efficiencies and performance metrics Design, build, and launch metric reports and dashboards Determine predictive models and methods for data analysis and model analysis Iterate the data processing and modelling process rapidly and creatively to derive non-linear solutions that are easily scalable Strong ability to formulate business goals into analytics tasks YOUR PROFILE Comfortable working with unstructured data Excellent communication skills with both technical and non-technical peers Experience with Big Data Technologies (MapReduce, Hive, etc.) Knowledge of machine learning algorithms (forecasting, clustering algorithms, probabilistic dels) and data modelling Entrepreneurial mindset and high level of self-motivation YOUR FUTURE TEAM Provides a driven, agile and ambitious environment that meanwhile encourages you to be your authentic self Emphasizes the need for commercial thinking and pragmatic, data-driven decision making Believes in accountability, direct feedback and self-reliance as the foundation of our work', 'Data Scientist (M/F/X) // Popcore', '2019-06-03', 'Popcore', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4720, 'Consultant (m/w) Data Scientist Daten sind Ihre DNA? Dann haben wir eine Gemeinsamkeit! Aachen, Berlin, Dortmund, Frankfurt/Main, Hamburg, Köln, München, Nürnberg, Stuttgart IHRE ROLLE - DAS WARTET AUF SIE Gestalten Sie gemeinsam mit uns die Line of Business Data & Analytics. Wir fokussieren uns auf die Daten unserer Kunden und konzipieren Lösungen durch technologieunabhängige Beratung. Sie haben bereits erste Erfahrungen im Machine-Learning Umfeld gesammelt und möchten sich mit unserer Unterstützung tiefer in dieses Feld einarbeiten? Dann sind Sie bei uns genau richtig! In interdisziplinären Projektteams sind Sie für die fachliche Entwicklung und Umsetzung von Data Science Use Cases zuständig. In diesem Kontext übernehmen Sie mit Ihren Kollegen die folgenden Aufgaben: Sie analysieren die Daten unserer Kunden nach Trends und Mustern und helfen damit bei der Optimierung der Geschäftsprozesse unserer Kunden Zusammen mit Senior Data Scientists konzipieren und implementieren Sie neue Data Science Use Cases Unter Verwendung moderner Machine Learning und Deep Learning Verfahren beantworten Sie verschiedenste Fragestellungen aus den Fachbereichen unserer Kunden und leiten daraus Handlungsempfehlungen ab Wir verstehen Daten als unsere DNA und transportieren dieses Selbstverständnis an unsere Kunden. Seien Sie Teil dieser DNA und gemeinsam machen wir die Welt binärer.“ Wir wissen – diese Aufgaben lassen sich nur mit offenem Erfahrungsaustausch, gegenseitiger Unterstützung, kontinuierlicher Weiterbildung und gut ausgestattet erfüllen. Mehr als 500 Consultants – davon über 70 Big Data-Spezialisten -bei adesso und über 100 Schulungen sowie Laptop und Smartphone ab Tag 1 warten auf Sie! IHRE SKILLS – DAS BRINGEN SIE MIT Abgeschlossenes Studium der Informatik, Statistik, Mathematik oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation Überzeugende Programmierkenntnisse in Python, R, SAS, Scala oder Java Erfahrung mit großen Datenmengen, z.B. Soziale-Netzwerk-Daten, wissenschaftliche Daten, Weblogs, Sensordaten, etc. Sie haben sich im Studium oder in der Praxis schon intensiv mit maschinellen Lernverfahren wie Clusteranalyse, Entscheidungsbäume, Neuronale Netze, Random Forest oder Support Vector Machine beschäftigt Kenntnisse im Umgang mit SQL Erste Erfahrungen mit dem Hadoop Ecosystem sind ein Plus Analytische und ergebnisorientierte Arbeitsweise Ausgezeichnete kommunikative Fähigkeiten und Überzeugungskraft Sehr gute Deutschkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift Dauerhaft 4 bis 5 Tage die Woche projektbezogene Reisebereitschaft innerhalb von Deutschland CHANCENGEBER – WAS ADESSO AUSMACHT Wir gehören für Einsteiger und Professionals zu den Top-Adressen in der IT-Welt. In unseren interdisziplinären Teams bringen wir unsere Technologie und Beratungskompetenz mit der Branchenexpertise der Menschen zusammen. Kontinuierlicher Austausch, Teamgeist und ein respektvoller sowie anerkennender Umgang sorgen für ein Arbeitsklima, das verbindet. So belegen wir nach 2016 auch dieses Jahr erneut den 1. Platz beim Wettbewerb „Deutschlands Beste Arbeitgeber in der ITK“! Wir eröffnen Entwicklungs- und Führungsmöglichkeiten – unser Versprechen, ein Chancengeber zu sein, nehmen wir ernst. Egal ob Sie eher die Fach- oder Führungslaufbahn anstreben – unsere transparenten Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten bspw. zum Managing- oder Principal Consultant sorgen dafür, dass Ihre Entwicklung bei uns nicht still steht. Sie sind offen für neue und anspruchsvolle Aufgaben? Dann senden Sie uns Ihre aussagekräftigen Bewerbungsunterlagen inklusive der Angabe Ihrer Gehaltsvorstellung sowie des frühestmöglichen Eintrittstermins vorzugsweise über unser Webformular. Kontakt: adesso AG Olivia Slotta Adessoplatz 1 44269 Dortmund T +49 231 7000-7100', 'Consultant (w/m/d) Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'adesso AG', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4721, 'Basic qualifications 5+ years professional experience MS degree or PhD in quantitative field Experience with math/stats software (R, Matlab, SAS, Stata) or other domain specific software Some experience with developing production code Practical understanding and hands-on experience with the following: * Supervised learning methods (linear and logistic regression, generalized linear models, decision trees, random forests, support vector machines, graphical models, neural networks / deep learning, etc.). * Unsupervised learning methods (K-means, hierarchical clustering, association rules, principal components, etc.). * Mathematical optimization (mixed integer programming, linear programming, stochastic programming/optimization discrete optimization convex optimization, reinforcement learning, etc.). At Amazon, we get our energy from inventing on behalf of customers. Success is measured against the possible, not the probable. We are inventors that are working to build the best solutions to unique problems through breakthrough technology – for example, Kindle has revolutionized the way customers consume digital content. Working on the EU Amazon Content team will be unlike any job you have had. The Kindle EU Content team is looking for an experienced Research Scientist based in the Berlin Office. This role requires an individual with excellent analytical abilities, deep knowledge of predictive analytics (supervised, unsupervised learning) and Optimization techniques. The successful candidate should be able to learn by doing and apply methods quickly, iterating as necessary to drive business value. We are looking for someone with big love for big data. You will help us solve complex business problems and challenges we are facing by using top-of-the-line machine learning techniques and practices. This is a hands-on, high-impact technical position. You will spend most of your time writing code and wrangling data. The successful candidate will also be a self-starter, be comfortable with ambiguity, have strong attention to detail, and will be comfortable accessing and working with data from multiple sources. Amazon is an equal opportunities employer. We believe passionately that employing a diverse workforce is central to our success. We make recruiting decisions based on your experience and skills. We value your passion to discover, invent, simplify and build. We offer a competitive salary and stock units, we offer a whole host of other benefits, including an employee discount and pension scheme. We are committed to keeping compensation fair and equitable. Preferred qualifications PhD in a quantitative field such as Economics, Mathematics, Information Systems, Statistics, Operations Research or Computer Science Experience in NLP/Deep Learning/Reinforcement Learning Verbal/written communication & data presentation skills, including an ability to effectively communicate with both business and technical teams. Understanding of our technology environment, and the performance and scalability issue associated with certain applications. Superb attention to details and organizational skills', 'Research Scientist - Kindle Content', '2019-06-03', 'Amazon Development Center DEU', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4722, 'At Wooga, our Data Scientists play an instrumental role in driving the successful development of our games. The Data Science team explores new methodologies and delves deep into every aspect of our data to identify opportunities and make a real impact on our business. We are looking for a data enthusiast, who is passionate about games and is excited to think analytically about what makes a game great! These will be your tasks: You will work on analytics projects involving multiple team members to understand, segment, predict and influence the behavior of our players across our games portfolio You will use experiments, advanced analytics and machine learning to find levers for product optimization You will contribute to building data products for our game teams, empowering them to deliver actionable insights and recommendations You will proactively drive improvements of and provide education on our data analytics tools You will get involved with our products across different teams to ensure our games are loved by more and more people, every day About you: You have a degree in a highly quantitative field (e.g.statistics, economics, research, computer science) You have an affinity for the Engineering side of Data Science You have professional experience in data science and business analytics You are proficient in using Python for data analysis, and you can use SQL effectively to query large volumes of data You have a solid understanding of how data science can impact the core business and of economics in a freemium business model You have an understanding of commonly applied advanced statistical and machine learning techniques, and can generate ideas on how you could apply these to improve our games Our promise: Shape the future! Challenge the status quo and team up with a diverse group of experts working on crafting the world’s best games! Excite millions of players around the world every day through our games! Work just minutes from the center of Europe’s most vibrant city, Socialize in our hang-out spaces, and enjoy many fun events and parties! Enjoy our unique office space! A relocation support which matches your needs to make your and your loved ones’ move to Berlin smooth! Did we mention that we also cooperate with Kindergartens? Make use of an education budget and extra days off for self-development. Join our meetups, talks, brown bag lunches, world cafe’s, internal trainings, workshops and many others! We offer German language classes for you and your significant other! Choose your own equipment and be set up for success! We got your back! At Wooga we are committed to providing a friendly, safe and welcoming environment for everyone who works here or with us, regardless to gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, age, religion (or lack thereof) and game preferences.', 'Senior Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'Wooga GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4723, 'Über uns StackFuel ist Deutschlands erster Anbieter für praxisnahe Online-Trainings im Bereich Data Ana-lytics und Data Science. Im Zuge der digitalen Transformation bereiten wir Konzerne, mittelstän-dische Unternehmen und Start-ups auf ein effektives, datengetriebenes Arbeiten vor. Dabei setzt das Team von StackFuel auf die eigens entwickelte und mehrfach ausgezeichnete cloud-basierte Trainingsumgebung Data Lab. Teilnehmende können in einem praxisorientierten Trainingsansatz interaktive Programmier-Übungen durchführen, Algorithmen für Machine Learning oder künstli-che Intelligenz entwickeln und mit echten Daten aus verschiedenen Industrien lernen und arbei-ten. Damit nimmt StackFuel im Bereich der digitalisierten und datenorientierten Weiterbildung eine innovative Vorreiterrolle ein. Jobbeschreibung In dieser Position arbeitest du in einem Team aus Educational Data Scientists an der Erstellung von Lerninhalten auf Basis von echten Industrieszenarien. Du entwickelst Inhalte für unsere in-teraktiven Programmieraufgaben im Data Lab sowie auch Text- und Videoeinheiten für unsere Online-Trainings Data Analytics, Data Science und Data Engineering. Durch deinen Einsatz ge-staltest du das Unternehmen aktiv mit und legst damit den Grundstein für deine Karriere in einem aufstrebenden Startup. Deine Aufgaben Entwicklung und Umsetzung von interaktiven Lerneinheiten in Python (Jupyter) und R. Erstellung von Data Science Inhalten für Videoskripte, Lehrtexte und Projektaufgaben basierend auf realen Datensets und echten Business-Szenarien. Konzeption und Auswahl von fachlichen Curricula und Data Science Inhalten. Formulieren von Texten für Video-, Übungs- und Projekteinheiten. Logische Strukturierung und Modularisierung der Inhalte zur Erreichung der Lernziele. Entwicklung von Storyboards für Projekteinheiten. Qualitätssicherung und kontinuierliche Weiterentwicklung bestehender Trainings. Datengetriebene Evaluation von Lerneinheiten. Entwicklung von Dashboards zur Unterstützung der Betreuung von Teilnehmenden. Hilfestellung und Tutorium zu trainingsbezogenen Data Science Problemstellungen. Präsentation von Inhalten in Videolektionen und Webinaren (optional). Dein Profil Du hast ein abgeschlossenes Studium (Bachelor, Master oder PhD) im Fachbereich Data Science, Ökonometrie, Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Statistik oder ähnliches. Du verfügst über 1 – 2 Jahre Berufserfahrung im Bereich Data Science, Data Analytics, Business Intelligence oder angrenzenden Fachbereichen. Idealerweise hast du Erfahrungen als Tutor oder wissenschaftlicher Mitarbeiter. Du beschäftigst dich mit Python, R und statistischen Verfahren. Erfahrungen mit Algorithmen der künstlichen Intelligenz, Natural Language Processing und Zeitreihenanalysen sind wünschenswert. Du bist in der Lage, die Perspektive unserer Kursteilnehmenden einzunehmen. Dich zeichnet eine selbstständige und strukturierte Arbeitsweise aus. Du hast gute Kommunikationsfähigkeiten, Spaß an projektbezogener Arbeit im Team und eine Hands-on-Mentalität. Du sprichst Deutsch auf hohem Niveau (C2, C1+). Unser Angebot Erlebe ein von Leidenschaft angetriebenes Startup im EdTech-Bereich. Arbeite in einem jungen, dynamischen und motivierten Team. Übernehme vom ersten Tag an Verantwortung und bringe eigene Ideen ein. Gut ausgestattetes Startup-Büro mit Kicker und Tischtennisplatte. Absolviere unsere Online Trainings und bilde dich selbst zum Datenexperten weiter. Zentrales Büro zwischen Alexanderplatz und Hackescher Markt. Wir sorgen uns mit kleinen Aufmerksamkeiten wie frischem Obst, vielfältigen Teamevents und gemeinsame Aktivitäten um jeden einzelnen unserer Kollegen. Arbeitszeit: 40 Std./Woche. Hört sich das nach dir an? Dann sende uns deine aussagekräftige Bewerbung per E-Mail an jobs@stackfuel.com und lass uns wissen, ab wann du frühestmöglich anfangen kannst! Wir freuen uns darauf, dich kennenzulernen. Ansprechpartner: Dr. Richard Kunert', 'StackFuel: Data Scientist (m/w/d) zur Erstellung von Lerninhalten', '2019-06-03', 'media.net berlinbrandenburg', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4724, 'Seit Gründung unseres Unternehmens im Jahr 1951 haben wir uns ein großes Netz von Kunden und Transportdienstleistern in Europa aufgebaut. Als europaweit operierendes Unternehmen suchen wir Mitarbeiter, die weltoffene Teamplayer sind und ihr Ziel nicht aus den Augen verlieren. Fixemer Logistics wurde im Jahr 1951 gegründet und hat sich seither ein internationales Netzwerk von Kunden und Transportdienstleistern aufgebaut. Als europaweit operierendes Unternehmen suchen wir Mitarbeiter, die weltoffene Teamplayer sind und ihr Ziel nicht aus den Augen verlieren. Weitere Informationen über Fixemer Logistics erhalten Sie unter: www.fixemer.com Wir suchen für unseren Standort in D- 12055 Berlin (Neukölln) und unsere Zentrale in D- 66706 Perl Borg einen: Data Analysis - und Machine Learning Solutions Engineer/Scientist (m/w/d) Ihre Herausforderung: Planung und Aufbau von innovativen AI- und Machine-Learning-Systemen End-to End-Design und Implementierung von Datenanalysesystemen; dazu gehören Datenerfassung, Anforderungsengineering und Spezifikation sowie die Konzeption von technischen Lösungen auf der Grundlage von Geschäftsanforderungen Ihr Profil: Sie verfügen über einen Abschluß in Informatik oder in ähnlichen quantitativen Studiengängen wie Statistik, Operations Research, Mathematik oder Physik 1 Jahr Arbeits- oder akademische Erfahrung im Machine Learning und künstliche Intelligenz 1 Jahr relevante Erfahrung im Bereich der Datenanalyse (Statistik/Datenwissenschaft) Erfahrung in der Entwicklung von IT- Softwarearchitekturen im Microsoft-Umfeld Programmiererfahrung in mindestens einer Programmiersprache wie Python, Java, Scala, C# oder einer ähnlichen objektorientierten Sprache Wir bieten: Herausfordernde Aufgaben in einem international agierenden Unternehmen Eine gute Einarbeitung und Betreuung im Team Eine leistungsgerechte Vergütung Vereinbarkeit von Beruf- und Privatleben Sie möchten Teil eines wachstumsstarken Unternehmens sein und bringen Engagement und Erfolgswillen mit? Dann freuen wir uns auf Ihre Bewerbung!', 'Data Analysis - und Machine Learning Solutions Engineer/Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'FIXEMER Logistics GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4725, 'Your Role Analyze vast data-sets of banking transaction data & explore and enrich with relevant external data Develop user segmentation models and propensity scores based on a range of data sources Partner with data engineering in developing solutions to scale approaches to gathering, enriching and modelling said user & transaction data Collaborate across functions (sales, product, management) in researching and answering critical questions for our business Design, instrument, and analyze experiments that produce reliable insights that drive business efficiency Develop reports & visualizations that support data-driven business decision making Your Profile Bachelor or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Analytics, Statistics, Economics, or other quantitative fields 3+ years of full-time work experience as a Data Analyst / Data Scientist at a technology company Advanced proficiency in SQL and a data manipulation language, such as R or Python Hands-on experience with data pipelines, ETLs, and data visualization tools Solid knowledge of statistical analysis techniques & machine learning techniques Familiarity with web analytics (Mixpanel) & A/B Testing Tools (VWO / Optimizely) Strong communication skills with a consistent record of collaborating across a wide variety of teams and disciplines in a dynamic environment Team player, with a strong capacity to work independently on mission critical tasks Our Offer The opportunity to play a pivotal role in shaping a data-driven organisation Join as the first member of our newly formed insights team Work with very exclusive large sets of product, user behaviour and banking transaction data Exposure to all levels (engineering, sales, product, C-Level) of an exciting, rapidly growing B2B2C Fintech A tightly knit team of experienced engineers with lots of interesting challenges to dive into Extensive individual responsibility and personal support to grow professionally Become part of a talented multinational team of 50 working in Berlin Semi-monthly OptioAcademy - our internal knowledge sharing project Prime office location - top floor of the city’s tallest building, the best view in Berlin! Various fun events (weekly team lunch, Friday after work drinks and BBQ, OptioAcademy, Meetups) EUR 2,000 annual training budget for conferences, books, trainings, etc. Free educational library, breakfast, drinks and fruit to keep energy levels high Your choice of hardware and software', 'Data Analyst (m/f/x)', '2019-06-03', 'OptioPay', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4726, 'Für unser wachsendes & ambitioniertes Team suchen wir ab sofort eine/n Praktikanten/in mit hoher Einsatzbereitschaft, die/der datengetriebene Er- kenntnisse mit Business Impact als Data Scientist liefert! Das sind Deine Aufgaben • Deine Aufgabe ist es, top-aktuelle Themenstellungen für IoT und Big Data Analytics vor dem Hintergrund praxisnaher und disruptiver Anwendungen zu bearbeiten • Du analysierst Daten und Zusammenhänge für verschiedene Use Cases • Dazu implementierst Du Software im Backend und Frontend unserer Cloud-Plattform • Die Umsetzung von Mockups und Minimum Viable Products (MVP) steht dabei im Vordergrund • Rapid-Prototyping und die Lean-Start-Up-Methode sind für Dich Deine täglichen Begleiter • Demos der ShowCases und Mockups vor dem Team und vor Kunden runden Deine Aufgaben ab Das sind Deine Qualifikationen • Kenntnisse in Einrichtung & Anwendung von Cloud-Plattformen für Big Data + Analytics • Erfahrungen im Umgang mit R, Python, TensorFlow, SQL, NoSQL o. Ä. • Erfahrung in der Verarbeitung großer Datenbestände für Data Mining • hohes Maß an unternehmerischem Denken sowie Eigeninitiative • Programmierkenntnisse in Java; sowie JavaScript, HTML5, CSS (optional) • Sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse • Fortgeschrittenes oder abgeschlossenes Studium der Mathematik, der (Wirtschafts-) Informatik, oder einer Ingenieurswissenschaft • Berufserfahrung im Bereich Data Science, Advanced Data Analytics oder Machine Learning Das ist unser Angebot • Wir bieten Dir die Chance, sehr schnell Verantwortung in einem aufstrebenden Start-Up zu übernehmen und Deine Arbeiten direkt in unsere Cloud-Produkte zu integrieren • Du startest sofort mit abwechslungsreichen Aufgaben und profitierst von unserer flachen Hierarchie • Dabei kannst Du Deine eigenen Ideen einbringen und schnell Erfolge erreichen • Zudem lernst Du unsere unkomplizierte Unternehmenskultur kennen, die geprägt von Spaß und Leistungsorientierung ist. • Wir bieten Dir regelmäßige Teamevents, ein Teamfrühstück, einen Obstkorb sowie kalte und warme Getränke • Dein Arbeitsplatz liegt in attraktiver und dynamischer Lage in Berlin-Charlottenburg', 'Data Scientist Praktikant/in', '2019-06-03', 'Virtenio GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4727, 'About the job: At HeroKey we develop software for events since 2015. Among our clients are Melt Festival, splash! Festival and Lollapalooza Berlin. Our software provides B2B partners with a toolset to engage with customers, manage tickets, accreditation and payments. We’re pioneering with our products in the event and festival industry towards a seamless, secure and stress-free experience for both promoter and customer. HeroKey is expanding its team in all areas to handle an increasing demand from international festival promoters and distribution partners in South Africa. We’re building a data science team to provide our clients with the best possible tools to analyse their data and to identify opportunities to make our software even better. You will handle multiple stakeholders in projects, deliver structured requirements and drive the implementation of a company wide data strategy. During events of various sizes, you will observe the HeroKey toolset in the wild and generate learnings for further improvements. When you’re not out in the wild you’ll be working from our bay office in Rummelsburg and be part of an international dynamic team. Minimum qualifications: 4+ years of experience working in Big Data environments. Experience in visualising data and structuring reports for various audiences. High ability to solve problems and to structure and simplify complex scenarios. Excellent written and verbal English communication skills. Preferred qualifications: Experience with Postgres databases and cloud-based infrastructure e.g. Google Cloud. Good coding knowledge in a scripting language such as Python, R, Ruby etc.. Understanding of Machine Learning methods and techniques. Responsibilities: Conceptualise and lead implementation of architectures for real-time data processing. Lias with our development team to establish approaches for efficient data processing and mining. Deliver automated reports, dashboards and visualisations for various audiences. Manage Big Data and reporting backlogs, straighten priorities and develop roadmaps to align with the business strategy. Establish a toolset that provides a basic data analysis suite but also allows the usage of more advanced tools such as tableau, Metabase or Microsoft BI. Maintain awareness of “state of the art” technologies for data analytics, data warehousing, processing and machine learning. Provide analytical insights on how customers use our products to help our product management team to prioritise features and improvements. Benefits Work in a highly motivated, great team Daily communication with our international network Exciting and diversified projects in a start-up environment with individual development potentialities.', 'Product Owner Business Intelligence / Data Scientist (F/M/D)', '2019-06-03', 'Goodlive GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4728, 'As the digital innovation, consulting and transformation brand of the Capgemini Group, Capgemini Invent helps CxOs envision and build what’s next for their organizations. Located in more than 30 offices and 22 creative studios around the world, it´s 6,000+ strong team combines strategy, technology, data science and creative design with deep industry expertise and insights, to develop new digital solutions and business models of the future. We are a rapidly growing team of talented AI enthusiasts which have dedicated themselves to building innovative and data-driven products & services for customers across industries. Our aim is to rapidly develop cutting-edge solutions by applying the latest technologies and data science techniques. What we do Our main focus is currently five subject matters, which are closely related and mutual, so is our team: Analytics & Visualization we bring big data to live and gain insights from it. Utilized technologies are e.g.: Tableau, Power BI, Qlik, R Shiny, Bokeh, D3.js among others. AI Applications we build bots, automate back-office applications with cognitive solutions (like RPA, ICR, NLP etc), intelligent search appliances etc. Key technologies are Microsoft Bot Framework, Kore.ai, Dialogflow, UIpath, Neo4j, ElasticSearch and many others. Training & Enablement we offer different curricula & workshop formats for our colleagues but also for our clients, enabling them to understand what it takes to be data-driven and data-ready. Predictive Models state-of-the-art machine learning and data science techniques allow us to build powerful models to forecast & optimize sales, churn, fraud etc. We build predictive maintenance, image & object recognition and anomaly detection models. Data Engineering & Infrastructure for us technology is an enabler, thus we make sure we utilize what is most suitable for solving the given problem. Modern tech stack, cloud-driven services, powerful GPUs – these are some of the ingredients that make us successful. We are looking for you Is any of the subject matters above the area you’d like to focus on? Let us know. We are looking for you to join us. What we expect from you A strong academic background (MSc or Ph.D.), having studied a quantitative subject such as mathematics or statistics or equivalent experience in a related subject. can-do /can-solve attitude team-play and good communications skills (good English is a must, good German is a plus) willingness to travel passionate curiosity … and… …and at least 3 questions answered with a confident yes (the more the better) Do you have a strong knowledge of Python and/or R (or any other data-science related language? Are you a mathematical and statistical expert? Are you familiar with SQL and are you adept at Data Mining and Explorative Data Analysis? Do you have experience in dealing with large amounts of data and building scalable data pipelines? Are you as comfortable interfacing directly with the customer as you are developing hypotheses or exploring & wrangling datasets? Are you capable of explaining complex concepts in an easy to understand manner? Are you keeping up with state-of-the-art Data Science technologies, algorithms & techniques by attending relevant conferences and courses and you love sharing your knowledge with your peers? If your are an expert in one of the subject matters we offer – don´t hesitate to get in touch! Send us your complete application by our application tool, including your expected salary, starting date and your location preference. For questions Julia Loy will be at your disposal at: julia.loy@capgemini.com.', 'Capgemini Invent: Data Scientist (m/f/d) Insight Driven Enterprise – AI Garage', '2019-06-03', 'Capgemini', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4729, 'Caroobi is one of Europe’s fastest growing online car repair companies. Our primary mission is simple: to provide the best end-to-end repair experience with a 100% transparent and easy booking process. We seek to revolutionize the automotive aftersales industry – across Europe and throughout the world. As one of Europe''s fastest growing tech startups with services that experience increasing demand, we are also growing our team with the sharpest talent in the market. We offer exciting opportunities for motivated talents who would like to join the booming and yet not disrupted world of the aftersales market. Caroobi has both the product and the team to drastically change the market in Germany. Our investors include BMW iVentures, DN Capital, Cherry Ventures, as well as NGP and Target Global. Your Role translate abstract high-level ideas into well-defined logical problems and solve them using large amounts of data come up with actionable recommendations based on your results and discuss them with different stakeholders (management, product, marketing etc.) collaborate with management to define meaningful KPIs and track them against business goals build reports and dashboards for the operational teams to analyse performance help promote a data-driven mindset across the entire organisation Your Profile preferably an academic degree (BSc or MSc) in Business, Economics, Statistics, Data Science or a similarly quantitative field previous relevant work experience in a consulting firm, investment bank, start-up or vc fund (internships or full-time) good Excel skills and an interest in learning how to solve problems using SQL, previous knowledge with databases will be a plus - the same goes for working experience with R or Python hands-on mentality, solution-oriented and structured thinking, very analytical problem solver, high attention to detail feeling comfortable with working on big amounts of data, ability to work on abstract quantitative problems under pressure and time constraints fluency in English - German is a plus Our Offer Scale with us: Join Caroobi during its most exciting growth period. Teamwork: You work with an outstanding international team of developers, product managers, designers, performance marketing specialists, and BI experts every day. Love your Job: Varied and challenging projects in a rapidly developing business with responsibility from day 1. Get strong with us: We believe in a healthy lifestyle. That is why we sponsor gym memberships, so you can exercise with the whole team during lunch break. Never stop learning: Use your personal learning budget to broaden your knowledge and train your skills - no matter what it is. Other Benefits: Company Events, Company Pension, Relocation Support Sounds good? Send us your application online, and we’ll get back to you!', 'Business Intelligence Analyst / Data Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Caroobi', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4730, 'About Ree: We are committed to redefine how people move in big urban areas in a fast and sustainable way. We use the latest technologies from autonomous driving and video streaming to achieve this goal. You’d join an experienced but more importantly fun and open-minded team. We have worked for many years at Zoox (Silicon Valley), Google (Silicon Valley), Waymo (Silicon Valley), Amazon (Silicon Valley), P3 Engineering (Silicon Valley), Microsoft and Skype (Stockholm) as well as having founded various other companies before. Our current team size is 10+ and we’d like to grow to > 100 by next year. We are backed by top investors (from Europe and Silicon Valley) with many years of runway. And we’d love to add you to our team! The role: As Data Scientist (m/f/d) you will be involved in the analysis of all the data we collect and produce, from networking data, to mobility simulation and video codec data. Based on the output of your work we will be deriving essential operational decision that will shape our entire business. In addition, you will be essential in defining the foundations of our product and culture. The profile: You have relevant work experience in fast moving environments like a start-up, technology companies, or from technical university programs You are experienced in hypothesis testing and risk analysis You have a very solid statistic foundation and can teach us all about predictive models for machine learning based on time-series data You know the data science tools like relational databases, NoSQL and Python programming language Strong passion for autonomous mobility technology and you want to shape the industry with us Fluent verbal and written English language skills You think big and like to build something, you are solution oriented and like to get stuff done You enjoy working in a fast-moving environment and have a strong tech affinity At the same time you are a true team player and we will enjoy working with you Nice to have’s: Data engineering background and respective expertise Background in mobile networks (e.g. 4G / LTE, over the top services, real time services) General networking experience (e.g. VPNs, TCP/IP, packet routing, network performance tuning) Video and audio encoding (e.g. H.264/AVC, H.265/HEVC) and multimedia systems with deep understanding of codecs for optimisations Knowledge in C or C++ programming Knowledge in Robot Operating System (ROS) Knowledge in Embedded systems We obviously don''t expect anyone to check all of these nice to have''s! Our offering: Change how people move in big urban areas while making car ownership obsolete The opportunity to build up the data science function from scratch A competitive compensation package & unlimited vacation Involvement in one of the most exciting tech projects in Europe An open-minded and fun work environment Be surrounded by a highly committed and very experienced team Relocation services to Berlin - It doesn’t matter where you currently live! Note: Ree provides an equal opportunity to all candidates. All candidates will be considered for employment regardless of age, ancestry, color, gender identity or expression, marital status, medical condition, national origin, political affiliation, race, religion, sex, sexual orientation. Come join us! : )', '(Senior) Data Scientist (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Ree Technology', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4731, 'JUNIOR DATA SCIENTIST (m/f/d) BERLIN 50.000 - 65.000 + BENEFITS Are you passionate, driven and like to go the extra mile? One of the leading German industrial companies is looking for a tech/data science-enthusiast who loves to innovate and work with machine learning. If this applies to you and you are ready to utilise your skills in a fast paced, collaborative environment that will allow you to develop and advance your skills - this role is well suited for you. THE COMPANY As a Data Scientist you will be working with one of the leading industrial companies in Germany. The company is going through growth due to their continued success and are now expanding their Data Science team. They offer the fantastic opportunity to question the data science team of how they can improve the business value, yet still giving everyone the freedom to look for their own projects within the business. Supporting growth is key at this company hence, the candidate will benefit from individual mentoring and training. THE ROLE As a Data Scientist in this fast-paced team, you will be working on large data sets alongside your colleagues to create innovative and forward-thinking data driven solutions. You will combine your technical skills with the ability to translate insights to a non-technical audience. In specific you can expect to be involved in the following: Machine learning is one of the core tasks from developing, testing and implementing machine learning algorithms using Python Data Architectures and data lakes development and implementation To be able to have all data available for Machine learning, a close collaboration with Data Engineers and IT is required Provide support to other departments in terms of the digitalization YOUR SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE Master''s degree in information technology, computer science or mathematics (PhD is not required but an advantage) Profound knowledge in Python to be used for machine learning Big data technologies should be familiar as well as cloud solutions (like AWS and Azure) Knowledge in deep learning and time-series sensor data is advantageable Participation in Kaggle challenges or Hackathons in the past is a benefit High curiosity in working innovatively, independent but also loving to solve problems in a team Experience or strong interest in industry-related fields THE BENEFITS Salary ranging from 50.000 to 65.000 Strong support from experienced Data Scientists A challenging but fun position Working in an international team A salary package that is performance-oriented as well as supplying social benefits HOW TO APPLY Please register your interest by sending your CV to Sophia Fassbender at Harnham via the apply link on this page.', 'JUNIOR DATA SCIENTIST', '2019-06-03', 'Harnham', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4732, 'OptioPay is a payment processor with a difference. Our mission is to build best-in-class value-adding financial technology services for businesses and consumers powered by banking data. OptioPay was founded by Marcus Börner and Oliver Oster in 2014 and is located at the top floor of the Treptowers. At OptioPay we work cross-functionally, agile and test our limits to outgrow ourselves. Our goal is to change the way how people receive and spend money. To do this, we need your talent, creativity and drive. Join our diverse, multi-cultural and inspiring team, a fun and friendly group with a multitude of talents. At OptioPay you will find an ambitious and empowering environment with a shared vision and passion. We are looking forward to meeting you! These will be your tasks Analyze vast data-sets of banking transaction data & explore and enrich with relevant external data Develop user segmentation models and propensity scores based on a range of data sources Partner with data engineering in developing solutions to scale approaches to gathering, enriching and modelling said user & transaction data Collaborate across functions (sales, product, management) in researching and answering critical questions for our business Design, instrument, and analyze experiments that produce reliable insights that drive business efficiency Develop reports & visualizations that support data-driven business decision making You''re offering these qualifications Bachelor or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Analytics, Statistics, Economics, or other quantitative fields 3+ years of full-time work experience as a Data Analyst / Data Scientist at a technology company Advanced proficiency in SQL and a data manipulation language, such as R or Python Hands-on experience with data pipelines, ETLs, and data visualization tools Solid knowledge of statistical analysis techniques & machine learning techniques Familiarity with web analytics (Mixpanel) & A/B Testing Tools (VWO / Optimizely) Strong communication skills with a consistent record of collaborating across a wide variety of teams and disciplines in a dynamic environment Team player, with a strong capacity to work independently on mission critical tasks We''re offering these benefits The opportunity to play a pivotal role in shaping a data-driven organisation Join as the first member of our newly formed insights team Work with very exclusive large sets of product, user behaviour and banking transaction data Exposure to all levels (engineering, sales, product, C-Level) of an exciting, rapidly growing B2B2C Fintech A tightly knit team of experienced engineers with lots of interesting challenges to dive into Extensive individual responsibility and personal support to grow professionally Become part of a talented multinational team of 50 working in Berlin Semi-monthly OptioAcademy - our internal knowledge sharing project Prime office location - top floor of the city’s tallest building, the best view in Berlin! Various fun events (weekly team lunch, Friday after work drinks and BBQ, OptioAcademy, Meetups) EUR 2,000 annual training budget for conferences, books, trainings, etc. Free educational library, breakfast, drinks and fruit to keep energy levels high Your choice of hardware and software', 'Data Analyst (m/f/x)', '2019-06-03', 'OptioPay Group', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4733, 'Who we are This ad goes out to all those who want to find a purpose in what they’re doing and take accountability for their work. At Blinkist, we’ve created a meaningful product that is growing fast. Our blinks – key insights from the world’s best nonfiction – help more than 10 million people around the globe to keep learning new, exciting things each and every day. In 2017, we received the United Nations World Summit Award in the Learning & Education category, a Google Material Design Award for Brand Expressiveness, as well as an Android Excellence Award. Why we need you Our data stack has always been a core pillar of our business success. We’ve spent the past years developing solutions to gather key data points that can fuel complex algorithms and predictive models, and through them create value for our users. In order to continue delivering on this vision, we are looking for an experienced Data Scientist to join our small but well equipped team. The ideal candidate should have experience in setting up and managing recommender models, be enthusiastic about NLP and using the power of data to remove uncertainties innate to subscription models (i.e. churn predictions). You will not only take part in a wide spectrum of projects and work closely with business stakeholders but also improve the customer experience immensely through personalisation. Responsibilities – Design and implement an array of recommender systems to provide our users with the right content at the right time; – Perform analyses of structured and unstructured data; take part in data science projects ranging from data exploration to model building, performance evaluation, and testing; – Utilize advanced statistical techniques to predict churn likelihood, attribute signup/purchase to the right channels and reduce uncertainties that come with the subscription business; – Crunch vast amounts of data in order to understand user behavior, extract valuable insights, identify new product opportunities and model improvements; – Apply Natural Language Processing techniques to categorize our content better; – Develop high-performance algorithms in scalable and product-ready code, and collaborate with our Data Engineering team to develop new data structures and to put algorithms in production. Requirements – You have 4+ years experience in applied data science; – Your expertise lies in building end to end data science solutions; – You''ve worked with the Python ecosystem: Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, Jupyter – You are fluent in PostgreSQL – You have good knowledge of software architecture and design patterns – You are skilled data-visualiser and you can communicate data-analytic insights effectively – You have experience with the AWS landscape, ideally played around with SageMaker – [Bonus] Practical experience with prediction.io – [Bonus] Experience with RESTful APIs (implementation and consumption) – [Bonus] Previous work experience in a subscription business – [Bonus] Knowledge of information retrieval techniques – [Bonus] Contributions to open source What’s in it for you At Blinkist, we offer a fantastic workplace in the heart of Berlin-Neukölln including all the benefits you’d expect – from a personalized perk system to free language lessons. Use your development budget to attend Recsys, NIPS, other conferences or development opportunities of your choice. Add free lunch, a competitive salary, flexible working hours, and a meaningful product on the rise, and you’ll get a first impression of why Blinkist is a great place to work at. We got rid of classical management hierarchies and, instead, distributed authority among all colleagues. We foster a unique company culture championing self-empowerment, personal development, direct communication and mutual support. Not only do we want you to grow into this role, but we want this role to grow with you. If we’ve captured your interest and you want to take part in building the leading destination for the modern lifelong learner, apply now and let us know why you’re the perfect fit for the job! At Blinkist, we don’t just accept difference — we celebrate it and support it. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, or gender identity.', 'Senior Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'Blinkist', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4734, 'About the job: At HeroKey we develop software for events since 2015. Among our clients are Melt Festival, splash! Festival and Lollapalooza Berlin. Our software provides B2B partners with a toolset to engage with customers, manage tickets, accreditation and payments. We’re pioneering with our products in the event and festival industry towards a seamless, secure and stress-free experience for both promoter and customer. HeroKey is expanding its team in all areas to handle an increasing demand from international festival promoters and distribution partners in South Africa. We’re building a data science team to provide our clients with the best possible tools to analyse their data and to identify opportunities to make our software even better. You will handle multiple stakeholders in projects, deliver structured requirements and drive the implementation of a company wide data strategy. During events of various sizes, you will observe the HeroKey toolset in the wild and generate learnings for further improvements. When you''re not out in the wild you''ll be working from our bay office in Rummelsburg and be part of an international dynamic team. Minimum qualifications: 4+ years of experience working in Big Data environments. Experience in visualising data and structuring reports for various audiences. High ability to solve problems and to structure and simplify complex scenarios. Excellent written and verbal English communication skills. Preferred qualifications: Experience with Postgres databases and cloud-based infrastructure e.g. Google Cloud. Good coding knowledge in a scripting language such as Python, R, Ruby etc.. Understanding of Machine Learning methods and techniques. Responsibilities: Conceptualise and lead implementation of architectures for real-time data processing. Lias with our development team to establish approaches for efficient data processing and mining. Deliver automated reports, dashboards and visualisations for various audiences. Manage Big Data and reporting backlogs, straighten priorities and develop roadmaps to align with the business strategy. Establish a toolset that provides a basic data analysis suite but also allows the usage of more advanced tools such as tableau, Metabase or Microsoft BI. Maintain awareness of “state of the art” technologies for data analytics, data warehousing, processing and machine learning. Provide analytical insights on how customers use our products to help our product management team to prioritise features and improvements. Benefits Work in a highly motivated, great team Daily communication with our international network Exciting and diversified projects in a start-up environment with individual development potentialities If we have aroused your interest, we look forward to receiving your application. In addition to your CV, please send us a short cover letter stating the reasons for your application to: job(at)goodlive.ag Art der Stelle: Vollzeit', 'Product Owner Business Intelligence / Data Scientist (f/m/d)', '2019-06-03', 'HeroKey UG', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4735, 'Your tasks and responsibilities Participate in 3-year EU-funded IMI-project FAIRplus as a member (m/f/d) of a large multi-disciplinary team Drive "FAIRification" of public and proprietary data and develop guidelines and tools on how to do so properly to eventually generate new scientific insights and discoveries Contribute significantly to highly innovative research projects in oncology, gynecological therapies, cardiovascular or adjacent indications reaching or at least significantly contribute to gate stage decisions Make data FAIR to eventually identify novel targets or biomarkers in above indications using state-of-the-art bioinformatics methods to analyze large and complex data sets more efficiently Develope, evaluate, implement, and application of novel bioinformatics methods to scale up FAIRification of complex data sets Collaborate with academic or commercial partners as well as support occasionally scientific personnel (master or PhD students) Maintain interfaces between R&D and IT functions Who you are PhD degree in bioinformatics, biostatistics, informatics, biochemistry, biophysics, biology, medicine or equivalent areas, alternatively PhD-equivalent research activities Several years of working experience in the field of data and knowledge management incl. semantics and ontologies Profound capabilities in programming and scripting (R, Python) as well as experience with high-performance computing, cloud computing, would be an asset Hands-on experience of making data FAIR are requested Strong background in and passion to enable new discoveries by efficient data integration, data and knowledge management, data annotation and big data analytics Very good communications skills and capability to present complex issues clearly and convincingly to project teams Highly self-motivated and strive for scientific excellence Fluent in English, both written and spoken FURTHER INFORMATION This is a fixed-term contract for initially 2 years located in Berlin. Your application Are you looking for a new challenge where you can show your passion for innovation? Are you interested in working as part of a global team to improve people’s lives? Then send us your online application including cover letter, CV and references. Bayer welcomes applications from all individuals, regardless of race, national origin, gender, age, physical characteristics, social origin, disability, union membership, religion, family status, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression or any unlawful criterion under applicable law. We are committed to treating all applicants fairly and avoiding discrimination. Country: Germany Location: Berlin Reference Code: 31306 Functional Area: Entry Level:', 'Research Scientist Bioinformatics for Innovative Medicines Initiative project FAIRplus (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Bayer', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4736, 'Your tasks and responsibilities Participate in this EU-funded IMI project in the field molecular biology, high throughput omics and biomarker data analysis and work as a member (m/f/d) of a large multi-disciplinary team Share responsibility for collection, curation and advanced analysis of bulk tumor as well as single cell RNA-seq public and proprietary data Evaluate, implement and use state-of-the-art computational methods to generate new scientific insights and discoveries Contribute significantly to highly innovative research projects in oncology, gynecological therapies, cardiovascular or adjacent indications reaching or at least significantly contribute gate stage decisions Identify novel targets or biomarkers in above indications using state-of-the-art bioinformatics methods to analyze large and complex data sets Develope, evaluate, implement and application of novel bioinformatics methods on complex data sets Collaborate with academic or commercial partners as well as support occasionally scientific personnel (master or PhD students) Maintain interfaces between R&D and IT functions Who you are PhD degree in bioinformatics, biostatistics, informatics, biochemistry, biophysics, biology, medicine or equivalent research areas, alternatively PhD-equivalent research activities Several years of working experience in the field of RNA-sequencing data analysis is essential Experience in the analysis of data from cancer, immunology, and single cell RNA-seq would be an important asset Profound capabilities in programming and scripting (R, Python) as well as experience with high-performance computing, cloud computing, and workflow systems are beneficial Strong background in and passion to make new discoveries by data integration, data and knowledge management, data annotation and big data analytics Highly self-motivated and strive for scientific excellence Keen to work within and across interdisciplinary teams Fluent in English, both written and spoken FURTHER INFORMATION This is a fixed-term contract for 2 years. Your application Are you looking for a new challenge where you can show your passion for innovation? Are you interested in working as part of a global team to improve people’s lives? Then send us your online application including cover letter, CV and references. Bayer welcomes applications from all individuals, regardless of race, national origin, gender, age, physical characteristics, social origin, disability, union membership, religion, family status, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression or any unlawful criterion under applicable law. We are committed to treating all applicants fairly and avoiding discrimination. Country: Germany Location: Berlin Reference Code: 31307 Functional Area: Entry Level:', 'Research Scientist Bioinformatics for Innovative Medicines Initiative IMMUcan project (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Bayer', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4737, 'Ph.D. in NLP, ML, dialog systems, or another highly quantitative field Publications in top-tier NLP and ML conferences and journals 3+ years of recent development experience in Python, Java, or other high-level programming language Strong sense of ownership and drive Strong communication skills Do you want to join an innovative team of scientists and work on some of the most interesting problems in Machine Learning, Natural Language Processing and Conversational Agents to provide the best customer experience on the Earth? Do you want to change the way that people work with customer service? Our team wants to lead the technical innovations in these spaces and set the bar for every other company that exists. We love data, and we have lots of it. We''re looking for machine learning scientists to develop cutting edge machine learning and NLP solutions that help customer resolve their problems in the quickest and most convenient way. If you want to be part of a smart and passionate team of scientists and engineers, work on leveraging and advancing the state-of-the-art in ML, NLP and Conversational Agents, and own an end-to-end business problems to ensure that your solutions have a direct impact to business and effectively improve customer experience, if you love to innovate and to discover knowledge from big structured and unstructured (text and voice based) datasets, then we want you to be in our team. In this role you will: Work in a team with other scientists and developers to design and implement automated, scalable NLP/ML models to develop innovative conversational interfaces that make it easier for customers to resolve their problems; Drive scalable solutions from formalizing the business problem to algorithm design, prototyping, production testing all the way to delivering to production; Drive best practices on the team, deal with ambiguity and competing objectives, and mentor and guide interns and junior members to achieve their career growth potential. 2+ years post-doc or industry experience Deep knowledge of one or more major deep learning framework Experience in Reinforcement Learning and Dialog Systems', 'Machine Learning Scientist / NLP', '2019-06-03', 'Amazon Development Center DEU', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4738, '4flow – das sind über 600 Teammitglieder an 15 Standorten weltweit. Wir sind einer der Marktführer im Bereich Logistikoptimierung und vereinen Logistikberatung, Logistiksoftware, 4PL-Leistungen und Logistikforschung in einem innovativen Geschäftsmodell. Im Zuge der 4flow-Exzellenzstrategie führt unser Bereich 4flow research Forschungsvorhaben durch, entwickelt innovative Digitalisierungslösungen und erstellt marktrelevante Studien im Bereich Supply Chain Management. Wir setzen auch in diesem Jahr unsere erfolgreiche Unternehmensentwicklung fort. Wachse mit uns und werde Teil eines exzellenten Teams am Standort Berlin als: Supply Chain Scientist (m/w/d) Was erwartet dich bei uns? Als Supply Chain Scientist übernimmst du fachliche und organisatorische Aufgaben in Logistikforschungs-projekten – aktuell in den Themenfeldern Risikomanagement, Optimierung und Industrie 4.0 – sowie im Bereich Data Science. Wesentliche Aufgaben sind: Recherche, Aufbereitung und Analyse von Informationen und Daten zu innovativen Forschungsfragestellungen, beispielsweise durch Experteninterviews Erstellung von Konzepten sowie von prozessualen und quantitativen Modellen für logistische Entscheidungsprobleme Konzeption und Anwendung von Modellen für künstliche Intelligenz, z. B. für die Bedarfsprognose Erstellung von Markt-, Branchen- und Technologieübersichten für Kunden Darum passt du zu uns: Abgeschlossenes Masterstudium in Betriebswirtschaftslehre, Volkswirtschaftslehre, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Wirtschaftsingenieurwesen, Wirtschaftsmathematik oder einer vergleichbaren Studienrichtung mit Logistik/Operations Research als Studienbestandteil sowie erste relevante Praxiserfahrung Ausgeprägte analytische und konzeptionelle Kompetenz sowie Kreativität Kenntnisse in einem der folgenden Kompetenzbereiche: Prozessmodellierung und -management (z. B. BPMN 2.0), Datenanalyse mit Python oder R, Logistik und Supply Chain Management Was können wir dir bieten? Forschungsnahes Arbeiten in einem erfolgreichen Beratungs- und Dienstleistungsunternehmen mit vielfältigen Perspektiven Ein abwechslungsreiches Aufgabengebiet, das dir ermöglicht, eigene Ideen und Lösungsansätze in einem interdisziplinären Team zu entwickeln und umzusetzen sowie methodisches Wissen (beispielsweise im Bereich Simulation und Big Data) aufzubauen Zusammenarbeit mit Top-Universitäten und die Option zu wissenschaftlichem Veröffentlichen Darüber hinaus bieten wir dir ein gemeinsames Freitagsfrühstück, Mitarbeiterparkplätze, ein modernes Bürokonzept, Sport- und Mitarbeiterevents, Teamreisen u. v. m. Bereit für 4flow? Dann bewirb dich bitte online. Wir freuen uns auf dich.', 'Supply Chain Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', '4flow', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4739, 'Als (Senior) Data Scientist (m/w/d) haben Sie zwei zentrale Aufgaben. Erstens entwickeln Sie innovative datenbasierte Produkte und quantitativ-analytische Lösungen für unsere Kunden. Diese Lösungen implementieren Sie auch, gemeinsam mit unserem Engineering Team (Data Engineers, Data Architects, Software Architects). Zweitens unterstützen Sie die Businesswelt unserer Strategieberater und Data Analytics Consultants bei Projekten, die einen quantitativen, datenorientierten Fokus haben. Sie helfen ihnen, den Mehrwert von Daten und Datenanalysen zu erkennen und zu schaffen. Sie arbeiten dabei mit State-of-the-Art quantitativen Methoden und Modellierungstechniken. Ihr Vorgehen ist stets ziel- und kundenorientiert sowie objektiv und wissenschaftlich. Ihr Profil Master-Abschluss oder Promotion mit hervorragenden Leistungen mit quantitativem/empirischem Schwerpunkt in Wirtschaftswissenschaften, einem MINT- oder einem verwandten Fachgebiet Strategisches und unternehmerisches Denken, Teamorientierung Fortgeschrittenes praktisches und methodisches Wissen in Ökonometrie/Statistik (Machine Learning bzw. nichtparametrische Statistik). Kenntnisse über kausale Inferenz sind vorteilhaft. Versiert in mindestens zwei gängigen Programmiersprachen bzw. statistischen Softwarepaketen (mindestens R oder Python sowie C/C++, GAMS, Stata, MATLAB oder Vergleichbares) Haben wir Ihr Interesse geweckt? Wir freuen uns auf Ihre vollständigen Bewerbungsunterlagen (Anschreiben, Lebenslauf, Abiturzeugnis, Zeugnisse aller Studienabschlüsse, sämtliche Praxiszeugnisse inkl. Praktika) über unser Online-Bewerbungsformular. Für Rückfragen steht Ihnen Alina Zieboll unter Tel.: +49 89 9230-9655 gerne zur Verfügung', '(Senior) Data Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Roland Berger', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4740, 'PhD in Computer Sciences, Mathematics, or Statistics with specialization in machine learning. 2+ years of hands-on experience in predictive modeling and analysis, and in deploying machine learning models in production. 3+ years of hands-on experience in programming languages such as Java and Python As an Applied Scientist, you will transform the way people enjoy music through personalized recommendations, search results or songs sequencing. You will collaborate with scientists and engineers to design and evaluate new machine learning models using audio features, meta-data, search queries or customer''s listening behavior to create a personalized customer experience. Amazon Music is looking for an Applied Scientist in Berlin with strong software development skills as we build a team of talented and passionated applied scientists to personalized the customer experience of Amazon Music. Our mission is to push the envelope in music recommendation and personalization. As an Applied Scientist, you will participate in the design, development, evaluation, deployment and updating of data-driven models and analytical solutions for machine learning. You will work with software developers and other teams to design and implement statistical models for recommending the right music at the right time considering context and behavior of a customer. Imagine being a part of an agile team where your ideas have the potential to reach millions. Picture working on cutting-edge consumer-facing products, where every single team member is a critical voice in the decision-making process. Envision being able to leverage the resources of a Fortune-500 company within the atmosphere of a start-up. PhD with specialization in machine learning with at least 5 years of related work experience. Strong software development skills. Experience working effectively with science, data processing, and software engineering teams. Proven track record of innovation in creating novel algorithms and advancing the state of the art. Entrepreneurial spirit combined with strong problem solving skills. Previous experience with methods in the Reinforcement Learning space (for example, Multi-Armed Bandits). Strong publication record in top tier ML conferences (NIPS, ICML, AISTATS, etc.).', 'Applied Scientist - Amazon Music', '2019-06-03', 'Amazon Development Center DEU', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4741, 'WunderAgent ist ein sehr dynamisches Start-up im Herzen von Berlin. Unsere Mission ist es, Makler-Dienstleistungen jederzeit bequem online buchbar zu machen. Hierfür haben wir eine Plattform entwickelt, die die Buchung professioneller Immobilienexperten so einfach macht wie nie zuvor - mit einem Maximum an Transparenz und zu attraktiven Preisen. WunderAgent ist derzeit in über 20 Städten aktiv, in denen wir wöchentlich unsere Kunden begeistern. Mit einem Netzwerk von mehr als 500 hochmotivierten WunderAgenten deutschlandweit arbeiten wir jeden Tag daran, unsere führende Position auszubauen um noch mehr Verkäufer und Vermieter von WunderAgent zu überzeugen. Unterstützung bei der Analyse unserer Prozessdaten und Kundenverhaltensmodelle Kontinuierliche Optimierung und Weiterentwicklung der Reporting- und Performance-Tools Unterstützung bei der Analyse der KPIs und Ableitung der Handlungsmaßnahmen Konzeption, Planung, Durchführung und Controlling der Maßnahmen Lösen komplexer Geschäftsherausforderungen mit kreativen Wegen Praktikum Data Scientist - Business Intelligence (m/f) Wir suchen: Ein neues Teammitglied, das mit positiver Energie die Herausforderungen eines jungen Unternehmens angeht, sich einbringt und gemeinsam mit uns daran arbeiten möchte, a weiter voranzubringen und unsere Kunden noch zufriedener zu machen. Was wir gerne bei deinem Profil sehen würden: Multi-tasking ist kein Problem und in stressigen Situationen verlierst du nicht den Blick für Details Du verfügst über sehr gute Excel-Kenntnisse Du bist ein offener, kommunikativer Typ, der gerne mit Menschen in Kontakt steht Du möchtest in deinem Praktikum Vollgas geben & tief in die analytischen Prozesse eines jungen Unternehmens eintauchen Du bist proaktiv und zeigst bei Problemen Lösungsansätze auf Du hast bereits deinen Bachelor (oder bist kurz davor) in BWL/Wirtschaft oder Vergleichbarem Deine Aufgaben: Was wir bieten: WunderAgent ist eines der spannendsten Startups Berlins mit einem zukunftsweisenden Produkt und starken Investoren, die uns bei unserem Wachstum zur Seite stehen Du arbeitest in einem internationalen Team mit flachen Hierarchien und schnellen Entscheidungswegen Du kannst Dich jeden Tag weiterentwickeln und so täglich einen Einfluss auf WunderAgents Wachstum haben Werde Teil des WunderAgent Teams und schicke uns Deine vollständigen Bewerbungsunterlagen (Anschreiben, Lebenslauf, Zeugnisse und Zertifikate) sowie Angaben zu Deiner Verfügbarkeit. Wir freuen uns darauf dich kennenzulernen! Über WunderAgent Stresemannstraße 23, 10963 Berlin, Germany Tel.: 030 - 555 784 88 jobs@wunderagent.de www.wunderagent.de', 'Praktikant (m/w) Data Scientist - Business Intelligence', '2019-06-03', 'WunderAgent GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4742, 'Minimum qualifications: PhD degree in Computer Science, a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience. Programming experience in one or more of the following: C, C++ and/or Python. Experience in contributing to research communities and/or efforts, including publishing papers at conferences and in Machine Learning venues (e.g. JMLR, ICLR, NIPS, ICML, ACL, EMNLP, GECCO, SIGGRAPH, CVPR, etc). Preferred qualifications: Relevant work experience, including industry experience or experience as a researcher in a lab. Experience publishing blog articles related to machine learning. Background in contributing to open source projects that are related to machine learning research. Demonstrated publication record. Ability to design and execute on research agenda. About the job We do research differently here at Google. Our team of Research Scientists are embedded throughout the engineering organization allowing them to setup large-scale tests and deploy promising ideas quickly and broadly. Ideas may come from internal projects as well as from collaborations with research programs at partner universities and technical institutes all over the world. From creating experiments and prototyping implementations to designing new architectures, Research Scientists work on problems including artificial intelligence, data mining, natural language processing, hardware and software performance analysis, improving compilers for mobile platforms, as well as core search and much more. Research Scientists work closely with Software Engineers to discover, invent and build at the largest scale. Ideas may come from internal projects as well as from collaborations with researchers at partner universities and technical institutes all over the world. As a Google Research Scientist, you''ll continue to be an active contributor to the wider research community by collaborating with academic researchers and by publishing papers, open source projects and web articles to communicate research findings. Researchers on the Google AI team have the freedom to set their research agenda and to engage as much or as little as they wish with existing products, choosing between doing more basic, methodological research or more applied research as necessary to produce the most compelling results. Because many of the advances we develop today may take years to become useful, the team as a whole maintains a portfolio of projects across this spectrum. It is our philosophy that making substantive progress on hard applications can help to drive and sharpen the research questions we study, and in turn scientific breakthroughs can spawn entirely new applications. The Google AI team’s research focuses on methods that can learn multiple layers of rich, non-linear feature extractors and can scale to large amounts of data. Much of our work is best understood as part of the ''deep learning'' subfield of machine learning, but we are interested in any methods — such as evolutionary computing, novelty search or reinforcement learning — that advance the capabilities of machine intelligence. We have resources and access to projects impossible to find elsewhere. There is always more information out there, and the Research and Machine Intelligence team has a never-ending quest to find it and make it accessible. We''re constantly refining our signature search engine to provide better results, and developing offerings like Google Instant, Google Voice Search and Google Image Search to make it faster and more engaging. We''re providing users around the world with great search results every day, but at Google, great just isn''t good enough. We''re just getting started. Responsibilities Participate in cutting-edge research in machine intelligence and machine learning applications. Develop solutions for real world, large-scale problems. At Google, we don’t just accept difference—we celebrate it, we support it, and we thrive on it for the benefit of our employees, our products and our community. Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google''s EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing this form.', 'Research Scientist, Google AI', '2019-06-03', 'Google', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4743, 'Basic qualifications Doctorade degree in computer science, statistics, information systems, economics, mathematics or similar 5+ years of experience working with large-scale, complex datasets to create/optimize machine learning, predictive, forecasting, and/or optimization models Strong proficiency in SQL and R/Python/Scala is required Very strong self-learning skills. Ability to pick up and adapt modeling methods from other disciplines or leverage methods from colleagues in other departments. Practical understanding and hands-on experience with the following: * Supervised learning methods (linear and logistic regression, generalized linear models, decision trees, random forests, support vector machines, graphical models, neural networks / deep learning, etc.). * Unsupervised learning methods (K-means, hierarchical clustering, association rules, principal components, etc.). * Mathematical optimization (mixed integer programming, linear programming, stochastic programming/optimization discrete optimization convex optimization, reinforcement learning, etc.). At Amazon, we get our energy from inventing on behalf of customers. Success is measured against the possible, not the probable. We are inventors that are working to build the best solutions to unique problems through breakthrough technology – for example, Kindle has revolutionized the way customers consume digital content. Working on the EU Amazon Content team will be unlike any job you have had. The Kindle EU Content team is looking for an experienced Sr. Applied or Research Scientist based in the Luxembourg and/or Berlin Office. This role requires an individual with excellent analytical abilities, deep knowledge of predictive analytics (supervised, unsupervised learning) and Optimization techniques. The successful candidate should be able to learn by doing and apply methods quickly, iterating as necessary to drive business value. We are looking for someone with big love for big data. You will help us solve complex business problems and challenges we are facing by using top-of-the-line machine learning techniques and practices. This is a hands-on, high-impact technical position. You will spend most of your time writing code and wrangling data. The successful candidate will also be a self-starter, be comfortable with ambiguity, have strong attention to detail, and will be comfortable accessing and working with data from multiple sources. Amazon is an equal opportunities employer. We believe passionately that employing a diverse workforce is central to our success. We make recruiting decisions based on your experience and skills. We value your passion to discover, invent, simplify and build. We offer a competitive salary and stock units, we offer a whole host of other benefits, including an employee discount and pension scheme. We are committed to keeping compensation fair and equitable. Preferred qualifications PhD in a quantitative field such as Economics, Mathematics, Information Systems, Statistics, Operations Research or Computer Science Experience in NLP/Deep Learning/Reinforcement Learning Verbal/written communication & data presentation skills, including an ability to effectively communicate with both business and technical teams. Understanding of our technology environment, and the performance and scalability issue associated with certain applications. Superb attention to details and organizational skills', 'Sr. Research or Applied Scientist (Berlin or Luxembourg City)', '2019-06-03', 'Amazon EU SARL(Germany Branch)', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4744, 'We are proud to present a fantastic opportunity for a Data Scientist to become a key player in a large dynamic multicultural company. This is an exciting opportunity to be part of a really interesting and faced paced client that is experiencing extreme growth. If you’re an enthusiastic, creative problem solver, looking for a new adventure, an exciting job and an international workplace is waiting for you in the heart of the recently crowned capital of cool! Berlin. The Role Analyse and describe structured and semi-structured data from all areas of the business. Identify and specify data /quality requirements to support modelling. Research, design and implement descriptive, predictive and inferential models using artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques. Collaborate with data scientists, data engineers, product specialists, and user experience teams to understand business processes, identify data and solution requirements. Guide data engineers to develop well-crafted engineering solutions and design processes to ensure their efficient operation at scale. Requirements Must have: Degree in Computer Science, Telecommunications, Electrical Engineering or related. 6+ years experience designing and developing machine learning applications at scale. Strong knowledge and hands on experience in applied statistics, data mining and machine learning. Advanced knowledge of SQL, and either Python or Java. Should have: Strong (4+ yrs) experience of machine learning tools (Scikit, Pandas, Numpy, etc). 3+ yrs experience with data visualization packages and techniques. 3+ yrs experience with cloud data analysis and reporting tools. 3+ yrs experience using agile methodologies issue tracking tools and version control systems. 3+ yrs experience in performing A/B & multivariate testing to measure impact of applied models. Benefits An International working atmosphere and cross-cultural teams Security in numbers working for a large, stable firm but remains to have a startup mentality. Help with relocation Flexible working hours. Stellar career progression opportunities People come in all shapes and sizes! We are and our clients are equal opportunity employers and value diversity at our companies. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.', 'Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'nimbl.ai', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4745, 'Neuraum – „we shape the future of building for a better life”. Our vision shows that we are here to truly make a difference in the building industry. Therefore we are on an ambitious path: After a fast start in 2015 and the takeover of several online platforms from a 70+ year old internet pioneer, our major website Fertighaus.de has become the leading German house and building portal. We help hundreds of thousands find their dream house. But that’s just the beginning: in the future we will provide all prospective buyers with even broader and more profound business activities – and to achieve that, we are looking for you! We are a team of experienced entrepreneurs and professionals, working with fun and passion to achieve our ambitious vision. We believe in an agile and self-dependent working style, in sustainability and a healthy balance of work and personal life. These will be your tasks Being a Data Scientist for our key portal Fertighaus.de means working on big challenges and having significant impact on the lives of many. We have the data of millions of people interested in building and you will help us build an industry-shaping technology, that understands home builders and matches them with their perfect house and construction company. You will analyze our data and prototype forecasting as well as customer behavior models. You will fully own our iterative A/B testing process to continuously improve the platform. You will try out new tools and methods to continuously optimize our matching algorithms as well as qualification and scoring models. You will play a key role in developing our platform towards highly personalized funnels and services based on live streaming data. You will come up with new ideas and push us towards becoming even more data driven. You will work with our latest tech stack (Python, Jupyter Notebooks, Bigquery, Apache Airflow, Elasticsearch, GCP) as well as adding your own tools of choice to the stack. You will work in close collaboration with your teammates in data engineering, product and software development and with all other functions and our founders. You''re offering these qualifications You have 1-3 years - or 3-6 years for the senior role - of relevant experience in Data Science, BI or related fields. You have excellent analytical skills and solve problems in a creative and structured way. You know how to package, visualize and communicate your results to support all stakeholders and achieve maximum impact. You have a strong interest in understanding and optimizing the business and user impact of your work. You are experienced with cloud based setups (AWS or GCP) and querying relational databases (Postgres, Bigquery or Redshift). You are experienced with programming languages and libraries (preferably Python, Pandas, Numpy and Jupyter Notebook). You have experience or at least interest in machine learning and the usage of live streaming data. You like to work independently, push for high quality work results, investigate beyond the obvious and challenge the status quo. You have a positive can-do attitude, love what you do and own it. You can easily acquaint yourself with new topics and enjoy new challenges every day. You are a strong team player with a kind personality and the ability to achieve goals collaboratively. You speak and write English fluently. We''re offering these benefits The chance to join Neuraum Ventures at a truly interesting point in time and the opportunity to shape the future of building for a better life A fun, friendly and ambitious team Flat hierarchies and direct communication, to operate and learn fast as a team Challenging tasks and broad insights from day one as well as the the chance to rapidly grow responsibility Great possibilities for personal development including a structured feedback process, mentorship from experienced colleagues and full support for internal and external training & development activities Regular team events, a cosy office in Berlin-Mitte with a gigantic rooftop, language class support and a too good to be true Urban Sports Club Membership You want to make a difference and value to work in a great team? We should talk! If you have any questions don''t hesitate to contact us by phone at 030-577040922. Your contact person is Meike Klingsporn.', '(Senior) Data Scientist (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Neuraum Ventures GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4746, 'What''s next in music happens on SoundCloud first. As the world''s largest open audio platform, SoundCloud is powered by a connected community of creators, listeners and curators who share, discover and influence what''s new, now and next in music and audio. We''re looking for someone to join our Anti-Abuse team as an embedded Data Scientist. You will be a member of a diverse and skilled group of Data Scientists that operate across the organisation in product teams, business intelligence and analytics. Our Data Scientists work on a wide range of products and problems, embedded with engineering teams having direct impact on our millions of daily active users. We want people that come equipped with an open mind, creativity and a get-it-done attitude. About the role As a Senior Data Scientist on Anti-Abuse, you will take the lead on identifying the sources of fraud, spam and abuse and working on solving these problems in a pragmatic way using your expertise in statistics and machine learning. You will see projects through from start to finish performing research, prototyping solutions, and production deployment at scale using engineering best practices. We love specialists with deep experience, and we expect to use that experience alongside a Data Scientist''s ability to be general and tackle a wide range of problem areas. Problems in this space are often ill-defined and open so strong problem solving skills and an ability to look beyond the immediate scope of a problem are important. You will know when and how to be pragmatic and, for example, use human-readable heuristics or take the leap to learn a model to predict the expected behaviour of a user. Some projects you might work on include: Bot detection Time series anomaly detection Fraud analysis and prevention About You You are a Senior Data Scientist with a curious analytical mindset, experience with software engineering, and a track record of shipping solutions at large scale. You have a broad toolkit that spans languages and runtimes, and you can get up-to-speed with new tech stacks quickly. You enjoy working cross-functional with Engineers, Product Managers and peer Data Scientists. You have: A Ph.D. or M.Sc. in a relevant field such as computer science or machine learning (preferred but not required) A minimum of 3 years of experience in a full-time industry position (not academic) A deep understanding of the lifecycle of a Data Science project, with experience in research, solution development, tuning and inspecting models, etc. Experience with Scala, Python or similar languages that are used to ship production models and systems Experience wrangling very large datasets by writing and maintaining data processing pipelines with Hadoop, Spark, BigQuery, Redshift, or similar An ability to tell a story about data, to explore and reveal patterns, and to communicate to stakeholders about your discoveries and hypothesis Worked in cross-functional teams and are able to work in multiple parts of a tech stack Diversity at SoundCloud SoundCloud is for everyone. Diversity and open expression are fundamental to our organization; they help us build a social platform and global community where anyone can create, discover, and share sounds. We acknowledge the challenges in our industry, and strive to develop an inclusive culture where everyone can contribute.', 'Senior Data Scientist Anti-Abuse (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'SoundCloud', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4747, 'What''s next in music is first on SoundCloud. As the world''s largest open audio platform, SoundCloud is powered by a connected community of creators, listeners and curators who share, discover and influence what''s new, now and next in music and audio. We''re looking for exceptional Data Scientists to join our Data Science team in either Berlin or New York. As a keen analytical intellect and sharp commercial mind, you will work closely with key leaders across a broad array of impactful topics and directly help shape SoundCloud''s Product and Business Strategy. About the role You will be part of the Strategy & Analytics team at SoundCloud which focusses on informing company strategy through in-depth understanding of user behaviour/product/content dynamics and generating strategic value from SC''s vast data asset. You will be responsible for conducting behavioral analyses, designing, running and interpreting experiments, creating analytical frameworks, designing dashboards and building predictive models in order to inform decision making in a series of complex product and business problems and ultimately elevate SoundCloud''s ability to compete. On a daily basis you will help guide decisions with quantitative insights into user behavior, content and product dynamics. Our stack includes a wide variety of technologies such as BigQuery, Python, Spark and Tableau. Some topics you might be working on: Explore user engagement and retention to underpin growth strategies; Analyse A/B tests for new feature development or business model evolution; Develop foundational analytical frameworks to optimize lifecycle management for our subscription businesses; Work hand in hand with engineering teams to define data driven tracking for our new features. About You You are an experienced Data Scientist with minimum 3 years experience who excels at analytical thinking, and brings strong commercial and product intuition along with sound technical knowledge and fantastic storytelling skills. You feel comfortable writing SQL queries and Python code and you are willing to embrace new technologies. You have a background in a quantitative field (mathematics, computer science with strong academic record preferred) and a track record of applying statistical inference and engineering in real world data science problems (ideally in a global b2c product in the digital space). You enjoy working closely with teams and you want to make a real impact on the company, in the world of music and creative expression. Diversity at SoundCloud: SoundCloud is for everyone. Diversity and open expression are fundamental to our organization; they help us build a social platform and global community where anyone can create, discover, and share sounds. We acknowledge the challenges in our industry, and strive to develop an inclusive culture where everyone can contribute. Read more about engineering at SoundCloud here ( https://developers.soundcloud.com/blog/ ).', 'Senior Data Scientist - Analytics (f/m/d)', '2019-06-03', 'SoundCloud', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4749, 'As a part of our fast growing team, we’re looking for an experienced Senior Data Scientist (f/m/d) who can contribute, take ownership, and help us scale our product and business. WHAT WE OFFER YOU A decisive role: You are part of our Data Science and Engineering team, developing our proprietary machine learning stack that sits at the core of our value generation for our clients. Every member of the team has a prominent voice and is encouraged to experiment, take risks and make suggestions that will have an impact on the business. What enables you to work at your best: Choose from free breakfast and drinks, a driven team to work, challenge, and celebrate with, transparency, and more. We also take a personal interest in your development and provide a budget for educational purposes as well as realistic options for career development within the company. A range of technologies: The Data Science team uses a range of tools depending on what is best suited for the problem: scikit-learn, Spark, Tensorflow, Databricks, XGBoost, etc. Our environment is built on AWS and we use various AWS services (ECS, S3, Redshift, Lambda, etc). We deploy applications using Docker images with CircleCi, and Jenkins pipelines run our machine learning algorithms. YOUR ROLE & RESPONSIBILITIES Devise ways using machine learning to improve our marketing and product performance to increase the quantity, relevance and quality of candidates that we bring to our clients, customize user experiences, and improve conversions Own a problem area, identifying ways to improve it and devising solutions Be comfortable sharing ideas and discussing different approaches in an environment where your opinion has a direct impact, being part of our international, experienced, and highly motivated team Be encouraged to work independently, using your conceptual and creative skills Be a scientific leader within Data Science, contributing to mentoring and developing of your colleagues. YOUR PROFILE 2+ years of experience using & developing machine-learning solutions to solve real-world business problems 3+ years of experience programming in Python and analysing data with it using packages like NumPy, SciPy, Pandas, and scikit-learn Proven ability to independently own data science projects end-to-end Previous exposure to algorithmic marketing is a plus Experience in statistically modelling processes or outcomes A creative problem-solver who is not afraid to try new things and challenge the status-quo Interested? We are on a strong growth path, so don’t miss the chance! If you are curious about the startup culture at HeyJobs, do take a look at our Kununuor Glassdoor ratings (average 4.85 – April 2019)!', 'Senior Data Scientist (m/w/d) // HeyJobs', '2019-06-03', 'HeyJobs', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4750, 'Due to our rapid growth, we are looking for an experienced and ambitious character to support our team as a Senior Data Scientist (f/m). Your Role Development of new analysis and prediction ideas and execution of existing analysis and predictions Specification of the analysis and prediction goals Procurement, integration and conditioning of the necessary data fundamentals Leading of project from the scoping phase to implementation and maintenance; End-to- end responsibility for data projects Working on data mining projects and developing of different data mining models Translate business problems into quantitative terms and present the results in clear and effective manner through visualization and prototyping Securing of consistent and uniform data analysis; Data preparation Developing statistical predictive models with structured and unstructured data by using Data-Mining and Machine Learning technologies Improve existing models by analysing results and re-train algorithms Supporting model-integration and -automation into daily business Investigate and incorporate new technologies and application areas during your daily work life to improve our product Implementation of complex analysis regarding subject-specific questions and specific customer requirements Specifications and implementation of software solutions in combination with modern tools and standardized processes Development of statistical and automatic learning models as well as implementation of prototypes Your Profile Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Mathematics or Economics required A minimum of 4-6 years of practical data science and data engineering experience, preferably in the entertainment or ad tech industries Expert-level coding experience with SQL Strong data visualization skills Experience with Tableau a plus Experience with R and/or Python programs Experience pulling together large data sets from a variety of environments including APIs (json/xml) Experience with Adobe Analytics (Omniture) and common email service provider solutions a plus Experience deriving meaningful features from raw data to accelerate projects Strong experience with managing, analyzing, and visualizing large datasets Programming experience with two or more of Python, R, Java, Scala, Mathematica, and C++ Experience with relational and non-relational databases Strong analytical thinking and ability to quickly pick up new methods, tools and programming languages Problem solving versatility: making the best decisions possible given the data quality and time available Record of success and top-tier achievement in prior work and education experiences Past success in extracurricular math/science activities or competitions is highly regarded Hands-on mentality and strong communication skills Comfortable working independently in a fast-paced environment with ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and to prioritize effectively Well-structured work-style with high standards of quality Team player and ‘can-do’ attitude Interest in working cross-functionally with other teams Fluent in writing and speaking German and English What We Offer You We value results not time, therefore we have no vacation policy Flat hierarchies: potential for own ideas A crucial role in a highly motivated and talented team Opportunity to work closely with the whole team including founders in shaping, developing and growing our company Office in Berlin Mitte Potential for promotion to Head of Legal Drinks and snacks for free An attractive remuneration Dynamic team working in an international environment -we work hard, but we don’t forget to have fun along the way! :-) What are you waiting for? Join us, grow with us and shape our company in the early stage. Send your application to jobs@cover42.com We look forward to receiving your online application!', 'Senior Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'Cover 42 Group', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4751, 'Begleiten Sie KPMG bei den zukünftigen Herausforderungen unserer Kunden. Begeistern auch Sie sich für die Vielfalt unserer Fragestellungen - und machen Sie gemeinsam mit uns den Unterschied. Das Audit Center of Competence bündelt unser Know-how für die Analyse von Unternehmensdaten und der Auswahl geeigneter IT Strategien zur Durchführung von Jahres- und Konzernabschlussprüfungen. Weitere Schwerpunkte bilden die Entwicklung von Datenanalysetools sowie die Ablaufplanung unserer Prüfungsaufträge. Verstärken Sie unsere Teams am Standort Berlin. Ihre Herausforderungen Datenextraktion und Datenaggregation sowie Aufbereitung interner und externer Unternehmensdaten Qualitative und quantitative Analyse von Daten zur Identifikation von versteckten Fehlern und Risiken Visualisierung von Analyseergebnissen Datenmodellierung, Design, Implementierung und Test von Extraktions-, Lade- und Transformationsprogrammen (ETL) auf Basis von Microsoft SQL Server Ihr Profil Studium der (Wirtschafts-)Informatik, (Wirtschafts-)Mathematik oder eines vergleichbaren Studiengangs Mehrjährige Berufserfahrung als Data Analyst oder Data Scientist von Vorteil Betriebswirtschaftliche Kenntnisse im Bereich Rechnungswesen & Controlling Kenntnisse über Datenbanksysteme vorzugsweise MS SQL Server, ETL Ansätze und Systeme, SQL Programmierung Erste Erfahrungen mit den SAP Modulen FI, SD, MM wünschenswert Sicherer Umgang mit MS Office Sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse Ihre Benefits Die Grundlage unseres Erfolgs ist die Vielfalt unserer Mitarbeiter, die wir individuell in ihren Stärken fördern und ihnen stetig neue Chancen eröffnen. Wir leben eine offene Feedbackkultur, dadurch geben wir unseren Mitarbeitern die Möglichkeit, sich durch jedes neue Projekt weiter zu entwickeln. Unsere Mitarbeiter stellen sich als Generalist oder Spezialist im Team tagtäglich vielfältigen fachlichen und bereichsübergreifenden Herausforderungen. Ab dem Level Manager besteht auch die Möglichkeit Personal- und Führungsverantwortung zu übernehmen. Wir unterstützen dies z.B. mit individuellem Coaching sowie unserem umfangreichen Weiterbildungsangebot. Zu den vielseitigen Entwicklungsangeboten gehört auch die Vereinbarkeit von Beruf und Privatleben. Durch flexible Arbeitszeitmodelle und ein umfangreiches Portfolio an individuellen Gestaltungsmöglichkeiten ermöglichen wir eine Balance zwischen Beruf und Privatleben. Bei KPMG arbeiten wir an einer bedeutsamen Schnittstelle von Wirtschaft, Öffentlichkeit und Gesellschaft. Vom mittelständischen Unternehmen bis hin zum internationalen Großkonzern – wir entwickeln gemeinsam Lösungen für die Themen der Zukunft und haben so einen direkten Impact auf die Businesswelt von Morgen. Lesen Sie mehr dazu auf unserem Blog. Deshalb suchen wir Menschen, die mit uns gemeinsam die Zukunft angehen. Dabei sind uns eine wertebasierte Unternehmenskultur, umfassende, persönliche Karriereentwicklung und -förderung genauso wichtig wie der Anspruch, gemeinsam mit dem Kunden neue und innovative Wege zu gehen. Wir freuen uns auf Ihre aussagekräftige Online-Bewerbung. Für Rückfragen steht Ihnen das Experienced & Senior Hire Recruiting Team unter de-experienced-hires@kpmg.com und 030 / 2068 -2332 gerne zur Verfügung. [jobstairs, kimeta, SS90]', 'Data Scientist / Analyst IT (m/w) Audit Center of Competence', '2019-06-03', 'KPMG', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4752, 'Market Logic helps the world’s best brands to make fast, winning decisions that accelerate growth. We do this with marketing insight platforms that automate innovation, marketing and research workflows, with the right insights at the right time based on cognitive computing. Market Logic supports the world’s leading brands in 190 countries across CPG/FMCG, retail, finance and media sectors, including Unilever, News Corp, P&G, Johnson & Johnson, Coca-Cola and Tesco. We employ 300+ software developers, data scientists, business consultants and marketing professionals at regional headquarters in Berlin Germany and Chicago Illinois and Singapore. For more information see www.marketlogicsoftware.com. Responsibilities: Contribute to the development of a set of new machine learning products using the cutting-edge technologies Work on the best data driven insights engine for market research data Extract information from unstructured and structured data sources using a wide range of techniques like text embedding models and knowledge graphs Take responsibility to manage, train and mentor junior team members Collaborate closely with product managers to create AI based solutions to customer problems Coordinate your work with other data scientists and machine learning engineers Requirements Master’s degree or PhD in Computer Science: with focus on data science, machine learning or an equivalent highly quantitative field 2+ years of experience in and knowledge of in at least 2 of the following: Natural Language Processing (e.g. NER, topic modeling, machine translation) Machine Learning (in particular unsupervised machine learning) Deep Learning (models and frameworks) Graph theory (e.g. in the area of social networks analysis) Enterprise software development and software stacks Knowledge of machine learning frameworks (e.g. Tensorflow, Keras, Caffe, Torch, PyTorch, DL4J) Extensive programming experience in Java or Python (and willingness to learn missing the missing) Plus: Experience with Graph Databases Plus: Experience working in an agile development environment Plus: Experience with Scrum processes Plus: Cluster Computing Frameworks such as Apache Spark Benefits Work in an entrepreneurial, fast growing and successful business environment Join an agile team in implementing complex features with modern technologies The opportunity to develop into taking over team or technical responsibilities in a rapidly growing company Performance-oriented remuneration An experienced, professional team with flat hierarchies A laptop computer of your choice', '(Senior) Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'Market Logic Software', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4753, 'Making an impact that matters. Unser Anspruch ist, jeden Tag das zu tun, was wirklich zählt. Mit unserem breiten Leistungsspektrum – von Audit & Assurance, Risk Advisory über Tax & Legal bis Financial Advisory und Consulting – unterstützen wir Kunden auf einzigartige Weise. Wir setzen neue Maßstäbe, liefern innovative Denkansätze und ermöglichen nachhaltiges Wachstum. Wir fördern unsere hochqualifizierten Mitarbeiter mit ihren verschiedensten Talenten, sodass sie mit uns mehr erreichen. In unserem Deloitte Analytics Institute arbeiten wir in einem cross-funktionalen Expertenteam mit Kooperationspartnern aus Forschung und Wissenschaft sowie führenden Vendoren an innovativen und maßgeschneiderten Analytics-Lösungen für unsere namhaften Kunden. Für unser Team am Standort Berlin oder München suchen wir engagierte Verstärkung. Spannende Aufgaben erwarten Sie Identifizieren und Prägen von Trends im Bereich Big Data und Advanced Analytics im DAX30-Umfeld mit Start-up Atmosphäre Entwicklung neuer Geschäftsmodelle und innovativer Ansätze zur Gestaltung maßgeschneiderte Analytics-Lösungen für wirtschaftliche Fragestellungen Gewinnung und Validierung von Erkenntnissen aus großen Mengen strukturierter und unstrukturierter Daten unter Anwendung von Data-Mining- und Machine-Learning-Techniken Unterstützung bei der Durchführung von Projekten von der Entwurfsphase (inkl. Prototyping) über die Entwicklung bis hin zu einer produktiven Nutzung Unterstützung von Workshops, Expertenrunden und Meetings Branchenübergreifende Ergebnispräsentation und Kommunikation mit unseren Kunden Darin sind Sie stark Erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Bachelor- bzw. Masterstudium in (Wirtschafts-) Informatik, Betriebswirtschaftslehre, Mathematik, Physik oder Statistik Erste praktische Erfahrung in den Bereichen Machine Learning, Data Mining, Computational Analytics oder Optimierung Kenntnisse im Bereich Statistik, Datenanalyse und -modellierung (z.B. R, Python / scikit-learn, MATLAB oder SPSS) sowie Datenvisualisierung (z.B. Tableau, QlikView, D3js) Kenntnisse in einer oder mehreren Programmier- und Skriptsprachen wie z. B. C#, C++, Java, JavaScript, PHP und in der Anwendung von best practices wie z.B. agile Entwicklung Reisebereitschaft sowie sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse Analytische und innovative Denkweise, Experimentierfreude sowie die Fähigkeit zum Multitasking Was Sie von uns erwarten können Neben einem sicheren Arbeitsplatz in einer angenehmen, kollegialen Atmosphäre bieten wir Ihnen ein chancenreiches, internationales Arbeitsumfeld. Hier warten vielfältige Projekte bei Kunden unterschiedlicher Branchen auf Sie. Bei uns gelten flache Hierarchien und ein Prinzip der offenen Tür. Ein weiterer Pluspunkt: Dank einer Vielzahl maßgeschneiderter Weiterbildungsprogramme bringen wir Sie in Ihrer beruflichen und persönlichen Entwicklung einen großen Schritt nach vorn. Ihr Berufsexamen rückt näher? Um Sie bestmöglich zu entlasten, unterstützen wir Sie dabei gerne zeitlich und finanziell. Sie sind interessiert? Wir freuen uns auf Sie', 'Business Analyst / Consultant (m/w/d) Consulting - Data Scientist Analytics', '2019-06-03', 'Deloitte', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4754, 'This Data Scientist vacancy is based in Berlin with my client who develops a software platform for data processing within the Autonomous driving industry. This Data Scientist position will see you working with 10 other data scientists in a fun and diverse company culture. What can you expect? Primary responsibilities will be R&D working on complex algorithms for processing and analysing data. following specific customer needs primarily in the autonomous driving field. Further to this the Data Scientist vacancy will see working on highly advanced algorithms and assisting in the development of new ones. Eligible Data Scientists will have a relevant PhD in a quantitative field such as mathematics, Computer Science or Physics and experience in most of the following; 1.Good programming skills in Python, Matlab and C/C++ 2.Excellent mathematics skills i.e Linear Algebra (BLIS, BLAS, Eigen) 3.Machine Learning platforms (TensorFlow, Caffe) 4.Machine Learning Experience 5. Minimum either 4 years of academic experience or 2+ years in industry If this sounds like you and you’re keen to find out more then please apply and contact Diogo Pereira Specialist Consultant at IC Resources. Even if you are unsure that you fulfil all of the criteria, please still apply as there may be similar roles we can recommend. The post Data Scientist appeared first on IC Resources .', 'Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'IC Resources', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4755, 'Who we are Klarna’s mission is to free people from all the meaningless time spent managing money and purchases, so they can do more of what they love. Every day at Klarna we help consumers, merchants, and partners to explore just how smoooth the modern purchase experience can be. Our position at the crossroads of payments, consumer financing, ecommerce and banking means we are uniquely positioned to do this. There is no label for what we do. Klarna was born in Stockholm in 2005 and today has 2500 employees working across Europe and the US. We currently serve 60 million consumers, work together with 130,000 merchants and process more than a million payment transactions a day. We are growing at 40% year on year and our investors include Visa, Atomico, Sequoia Capital, Permira and Bestseller group/ Anders Holsch Povlsen. We have strong partnerships with some of the world’s leading brands, such as ASOS, IKEA, Adidas, Zara, Lufthansa and Spotify. To find out more about what it''s like to work at Klarna: klarna.com/careers Data Science plays a vital role in Klarna’s operation. Historically, our focus areas have revolved around real-time risk decision-making for transactions. This can either pertain to credit assessment for individuals or identification of fraudulent transactions. Since then we have added many new data science areas such predicting customer lifetime value, predicting return behavior in e-commerce, etc. Data scientists in our Decision Services domain work on both the more mature projects, as well as the newer ones. As a (Senior) Data Scientist in Decision Services you will: Develop state of the art models to classify transactions and individuals Bring your ideas to production using AWS Be involved in the whole process of model development. This includes everything from root cause analysis, data collection and feature engineering to training, validating and implementing machine learning models, computing performance statistics and live model monitoring Work closely with several engineering teams and business analysts to find new and smart ways of consolidating data and making use of it in order to make better models and ultimately better predictions Be part of the Engineering organisation. Hence your workflow will be software-driven in terms of deploying models to production, using version control, and in general employing software engineering best practices Be innovative, cooperative, collaborative, open and have a flexible mindset with critical thinking In order to be successful in this role we believe that you will have: Strong programming skills in Python, SQL and experience with popular machine/deep learning packages (e.g. scikit-learn, keras, tensorflow, mxnet) Experience with & knowledge of: Cloud platforms such as AWS or Google Cloud; Big data using Hive, Spark, EMR The theoretical foundations of classical and recent machine learning models and algorithms, such as generalized linear models, random forests and ensemble methods, deep neural networks etc. A degree from a university in a highly technically numerate subject (e.g. Maths, Physics, Engineering or Economics). How to apply Send over a CV in English. We can offer you an international working environment filled with smart and ambitious colleagues. We know that diverse teams are strong teams, so we welcome those from different backgrounds and experiences. As part of one of Europe’s fastest growing companies, you''ll help play an important role in taking Klarna to the next level.', '(Senior) Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'Klarna', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4756, 'About Us StackFuel is Germany’s first provider of practical online training courses in the field of data analytics and data science. Within the context of the widespread digital transformations that are taking place, Stackfuel prepares large corporations, medium-sized companies and start-ups to make sure that they are able to work effectively in a data-driven working environment. For this, the StackFuel team relies on the cloud-based training environment Data Lab, the award-winning training environment that has been developed in-house by Stackfuel. Participants can perform interactive programming exercises through a practice-oriented training approach, they can develop algorithms for machine learning or artificial intelligence, and they can learn and work with real data from various industries. With this approach, StackFuel is taking on a pioneering role in the area of digitized and data-ori-ented further education. Job description In this position, you will work with a team of Educational Data Scientists to create learning content. You will develop content for our interactive programming tasks in the Data Lab and you will create text and video units for our online training courses Data Analytics, Data Science and Data Engineering. Through your commitment, you will take an active part in shaping the company and you will be laying the foundation for a career within an aspiring start-up. Your tasks Development and implementation of interactive learning units in Python and R. Creation of data science content for video scripts, educational texts and project tasks based on real data sets and real business scenarios. Design and selection of training curricula and data science content. Formulating text for videos, exercises and project units. Logical structure and modularization of content in order to achieve learning objectives. Development of storyboards for project units. Quality assurance and the ongoing development of existing training courses. Data-driven evaluation of learning units. Development of dashboards to support participants. Assistance with tutorials regarding training related data science problems. Presentation of content in video lessons and webinars (optional). Your profile You have a degree (Bachelor, Master or PhD) in Data Science, Econometrics, Computer Science, Business Informatics, Statistics or similar. You have 1 – 2 years professional experience in Data Science, Data Analytics, Business Intelligence or related fields. Ideally, you have experience as a tutor or a research assistant. You are experienced in Python, R and statistical techniques. Experience with algorithms of artificial intelligence, natural language processing and time series analysis is desirable. You are able to take the perspective of our course participants. You have an independent and structured way of working. You have good communication skills, enjoy project-related work in a team and have a hands-on mentality. You speak German at a high, preferably native, level (C2, C1+). Our offer Experience a passion-driven startup in EdTech. Work in a young, dynamic and motivated team. Take responsibility from day one and contribute your own ideas. Well-equipped startup office with ping pong table and foosball table. Complete our online training courses and educate yourself to become a data expert. Experience an interesting and dynamic working environment in the heart of Berlin. Central office between Alexanderplatz and Hackescher Markt. We take care of our employees with small treats such as fresh fruit, varied team events and joint activities. Working time: 40 hours/week. Does that sound like you? Then send us your detailed application by e-mail to [email protected] and let us know when would be your earliest possible start date! We’re looking forward to meeting you. StackFuel GmbH Contact person: Lisa Freiberger Alte Schönhauser Str. 38 10119 Berlin T: 030 / 6800 9505 [email protected] www.stackfuel.com', 'Data Scientist (m/f/d) for the creation of learning content // StackFuel', '2019-06-03', 'StackFuel', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4757, 'What you will do: Draw on your extensive industry experience to steer your team toward the most impactful scientific work Perform prescriptive data analysis that drives business decisions Design and analyse hypothesis-based A/B experiments Establish and connect financial, product and operative KPIs to monitor and steer developments as well as assess impact on the entire value chain Design and monitor pricing, merchant and inventory models and create strategies for inventory management Create compelling stories for data-based insights Work cross-functionally to drive actionable data insights and solutions from large and rich datasets You ask and tackle crucial analytical questions with a view on driving product impact Provide analytical perspective to discussions and lead priorities within your team Translate business needs to technical requirements and experimental design What you should bring: The curiosity and methodologies of a researcher with academic experience in a quantitative research field Deep experience with common analytical tools using R, or Python (we use mostly python) Hands-on experience with a broad range of statistical techniques such as time series analysis, bayesian statistics, and good old regressions, and the ability to identify the appropriate technique in different scenarios Critical thinking, problem solving, interpersonal and decision-making skills Experience in performance driven creative collaboration, setting technical workflows and training junior peers Communication and visualisation skills that enable you to present findings in a clear and unambiguous way Deeply understand the business challenges and how to transform them into solvable data problems Being a team player comes naturally to you and you communicate fluently in English What will you get? Colleagues striving for excellence while using the latest technologies Relocation support to Germany which includes assistance with visa, apartment search and refund of moving costs A beautiful and modern office in the heart of Berlin (Kreuzberg, Bergmannkiez) with free drinks & fruits Team and company events like Hackathons, International Nights, Annual Company Parties, Football, Team Nights and more Attractive discounts on different services like gym, public transport, car purchases and others Flexible working hours Annual salary reviews weaved into our feedback cycle German Language courses for free, in the office Sounds interesting? Upload your CV with a note of your salary expectations. Milos Beronja is looking forward to your application. Contact: Milos Beronja', 'Senior Data Scientist, Business Decisions (d/f/m)', '2019-06-03', 'AUTO1', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4758, 'Meine Aufgaben Aufbau von Modellen und Analyse komplexer Systeme Sichtung, Validierung und Konvertierung von (Kunden-) Daten Recherche, Evaluierung und Erschließung räumlicher und soziodemographischer Datensätze Einarbeitung in bestehende Code-Architektur Neu- und Weiterentwicklung von Prozessketten zur Datenaufbereitung, Verkehrsmodellaufbau und -betrieb Mitarbeit an der Erarbeitung neuer Produkte und Solutions für den Kunden Aufbereitung und Kommunikation von Solutions innerhalb des Unternehmens Meine Qualifikationen Sicherer Umgang mit Versionierungssystemen wie Git Bereitschaft, neue Technologien und Werkzeuge zu erlernen Selbstständige und selbstkritische Arbeitsweise eingebettet in ein kleines Team Entwickeln von Lösungen im Team Meine Vorteile Abwechslungsreiche Tätigkeit in einem renommierten Unternehmen Mein Einsatz Als modernes Unternehmen entwickelt sich unser Mandant ständig weiter und geht dabei immer wieder neue Wege. Über Hays IT-Spezialisten haben gute Karten – denn Hays sucht für Unternehmen aus der Wirtschaft und dem öffentlichen Sektor engagierte Experten, die gerne über den eigenen Tellerrand blicken und an ihren Herausforderungen wachsen. Wir stellen sicher, dass Sie von unserer langjährigen Erfahrung in der IT-Personalvermittlung profitieren und mit uns passende Aufgaben finden – und das völlig kostenfrei für Sie. Registrieren Sie sich und freuen Sie sich auf interessante und passende Projekte und Positionen. Mein Kontakt bei Hays Mein Ansprechpartner Tobias Fleßner Referenznummer 417975/1 Kontakt aufnehmen E-Mail: tobias.flessner@hays.de', 'Data Scientist / Data Analyst (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Hays', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4759, 'We are The Mobile Bank. Our vision is to build a bank the world loves to use. Technology and design empower everything we do. N26 is Europe''s first Mobile Bank with a full European banking license. We have 2.3 million customers across 24 markets. Our team of over 700 employees in 3 locations is concentrated on reinventing the banking experience for the digital generation. Valentin Stalf and Maximilian Tayenthal founded N26 in 2013 and launched the initial product in early 2015. Since January 2015, N26 has been available for Android, iOS, and desktop. N26 has raised more than $500 million from investors including Insight Venture Partners, GIC, Tencent, Allianz X, Peter Thiel''s Valar Ventures, Li Ka-Shing''s Horizons Ventures, Earlybird Venture Capital, Greyhound Capital, Battery Ventures, in addition to members of the Zalando management board, and Redalpine Ventures. ------------------ Once here you will ------------------ As a Senior Data Scientist, you will have a major impact on our data landscape and help us leverage the latest technologies to create an effective data-driven FinTech product Work closely with multifunctional product teams and other data scientists to design and maintain scalable data products and machine learning pipelines Define, create and deliver new machine learning driven products in collaboration Perform exploratory data analysis and modeling which deepens our understanding of the underlying human and financial processes reflected in our data ------------------------- What you will bring along ------------------------- Ability to distill business needs and identify key data science problems Proficiency in modeling financial and behavioural data both mathematically and statistically Proven experience in developing valid, value-driven machine learning solutions which are production-ready from the start Sound understanding of underlying algorithms used in analyses and ability to teach other data scientists and key stakeholders of all backgrounds Deep knowledge of Python with a solid general CS or engineering background Experience with common data science toolkits such as R, Tensorflow, ggplot, Stan, Julia desired Experience with Postgres databases, AWS, and cloud-based infrastructure preferred You are creative, organised, self-motivated and able to drive ambitious data science projects to success from conception through coding to deployment Language skills: English full professional proficiency ------------- What We Offer ------------- High degree of autonomy Working with international, highly engaged peers Flat hierarchy and open communication Getting things done attitude Keep up to date with ourInsideN26 Magazine ( https://medium.com/insiden26 ) A stack of the most modern technologies Exciting challenges Find a career path. Not just a job. Some of our benefits and rewards can be found on our careers website ( https://next.n26.com/en/careers ) Sound good? Send us your application online, and we''ll get back to you soon.', 'Senior Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'N26', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4760, 'This Video Data Scientist vacancy is based in Berlin with my client who develops a software platform for data processing within the Autonomous driving industry. This Video Data Scientist position will see you working with 10 other data scientists in a fun and diverse company culture. What can you expect? Primary responsibilities will be R&D work around video applications and working on complex algorithms for processing and analysing video streams. following specific customer needs primarily in the autonomous driving field. Further to this the Data Scientist vacancy will see working on highly advanced algorithms and assisting in the development of new ones. Eligible Data Scientists will have a relevant PhD in a quantitative field such as mathematics, Computer Science or Physics and experience in most of the following; 1.Good programming skills in Python, Matlab and C/C++ 2.Excellent mathematics skills i.e Linear Algebra (BLIS, BLAS, Eigen) 3.Machine Learning platforms (TensorFlow, Caffe) 4.Video-based Machine Learning Experience 5. Minimum either 4 years academic experience or 2+ years in industry 6. Experience in managing interactions with other teams would be highly advantageous. If this sounds like you and you’re keen to find out more then please apply and contact Diogo Pereira Specialist Consultant at IC Resources. Even if you are unsure that you fulfil all of the criteria, please still apply as there may be similar roles we can recommend. The post Video Data Scientist appeared first on IC Resources .', 'Video Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'IC Resources', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4761, 'Conrad Connect is the central platform for IoT-projects within B2C and B2B. Conrad Connect links smart devices from different brands and digital services. The resulting ecosystem offers a variety of new possibilities for visualization and automation of processes within our daily lifes. In cooperation with our partners, we develop new digital business models, based on the aggregation of different data sources. Are you ready to support us? As part of Conrad Electronic Group, we operate independently with the agility of a startup. Our speed of growing is enormous, therefore we are looking for you to support our team in Berlin as Senior Data Scientist (m/f/d) - IoT device data Location Berlin Job ID 4185 These tasks are waiting for you: Be the professional lead for our data team Obtain actionable business-oriented insights from processed IoT data Identify and explore opportunities to apply machine learning algorithms and guide their development from initial testing to their final user-facing application Communicate and collaborate with the digital marketing, business development and product development teams in a high pace environment Processing and aggregation of terabytes of raw near real time/real time IoT data Maintenance, expansion, and optimization of existing data pipelines (ETL/ELT) Who we are looking for: required: Degree in Computer Science, Physics, Mathematics, Statistics, or related qualification A track record of identifying business opportunities and translating them into products Experience in developing machine learning products preferably using Google cloud or comparable Excellent knowledge in Python and SQL Experience with NoSQL: MongoDB and CassandraDB in particular Experience with the Google cloud platform: BigQuery, data studio and data proc Experience with Spark or Kafka Excellent analytical skills, and the ability to work in an organized and efficient manner in a startup environment Ability to communicate complex information clearly and concisely a plus: Keen interest in IoT Experience in product management Experience with kubernetes clusters Working with Conrad Connect: As part of a dynamic and international team of internet affin professionals you can expect to take on responsibility from day one. Sharing and implementing your own ideas, you’ll work independently in an environment with flat hierarchies and contribute directly to our growth and success. You will be part of a startup environment, working in a modern office in the heart of Berlin. Besides offering a competitive salary and bonus as well as free drinks & fruits, you will be having fun at regular team events that are part of our culture. Want to be part of the next big thing?Send us your application today on jobs.conrad.com. We''d love to hear from you! Contact: Ines Eydner 0179 4110215', 'Senior Data Scientist (m/f/d) - IoT device data', '2019-06-03', 'Conrad Electronic', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4762, 'Unsere Vision ist der „Persönliche Coach“ für jeden Mitarbeiter, der ihn begleitet und messbar voran bringt. CoachHub verbindet moderne Technologie und New Work Konzepte, um etwas bisher Undenkbares zu ermöglichen – Personalisiertes Coaching für Mitarbeiter aller Karrierestufen! Gemeinsam bauen wir die größte Coaching Plattform Europas und darüber hinaus. Zu unseren Kunden zählen die renommiertesten Tech-Firmen und globale Milliardenkonzerne. Wir coachen weltweit auf 5 Kontinenten in über 20 Sprachen. DEINE AUFGABEN Recherche und Konzeption von innovativem und expertenbasiertem Content für Micro-Learnings für unsere Plattform, die unseren Kunden dabei hilft, sich zur inspirierenden Führungskraft zu entwickeln Recherche und Verfassen von wissenschaftlichen Artikeln und Whitepapern basierend auf relevanten wissenschaftlichen Quellen aus Psychologie, Computerwissenschaften & Data Science, Verhaltensökonomie, kognitive Neurowissenschaften Design von Coaching-Konzepten und psychologischen Modellen, für interne Präsentationen (Sales, Marketing) sowie Konferenzen und/oder akademische Veröffentlichungen Design und Durchführung von innovativen interdisziplinären wissenschaftlichen Studien zu Fragestellungen im digitalen Coaching und Wohlbefinden globaler Führungskräfte und Young Professionals DEIN PROFIL Master-Abschluss in Psychologie, Sozialwissenschaften oder vergleichbare Qualifikation Sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse, weitere Fremdsprachen von Vorteil Stark an HR, Business Coaching und Start-Ups interessiert Teamfähigkeit, Kommunikationsstärke und hohes Empathievermögen Ausgeprägte Fähigkeit zum konzeptionellen und analytischen Denken Selbständige Arbeitsweise und viel Ownership ”Getting-things-done” Mentalität und Lernhunger WARUM WIR? Die einmalige Chance, unser stark wachsendes Start-Up von Anfang an mitzugestalten Vielfältige Lern- und Fortbildungsmöglichkeiten, sowie eine steile Lernkurve Deinen persönlichen Business-Coach Direkte Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Gründern und Geschäftsführern Spaß im höchst motivierten und humorvollem Team Viel Freiheit, Eigenverantwortung & flexible Arbeitszeiten Zentraler Standort in Berlin (inklusive viel Kaffee, Softdrinks und frischem Obst) Regelmäßige Team Events', 'Learning Scientist / Content Developer (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Coachhub GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4763, 'Wir arbeiten stets an bestmöglichen Produkten und Services für unsere Kunden. Hierfür ist die Analyse und Interpretation von Daten ein wesentlicher Bestandteil für bedarfsgerechte Kundenlösungen. Als Data Scientist/Data Analyst bei Verti liegt Ihr Fokus auf der Datenextraktion und -analyse unserer Kundendaten. Ziel ist es, unsere Produkte noch zielgruppengerechter zu entwickeln und zu vertreiben. Nutzen Sie die Möglichkeit, Ihre Expertise gewinnbringend einzubringen. Werden Sie Teil von Verti in Teltow bei Berlin. Die Position ist in Voll- oder Teilzeit zu besetzen. Data Scientist mit Schwerpunkt CRM (m/w/d) Das erwartet Sie: Sie extrahieren Daten, führen komplexe Datenanalysen durch und erarbeiten Prognosemodelle zur Lösung datengetriebener Fragestellungen entlang der gesamten Customer Journey (z.B. Modelle für Affinitäten oder zur Kündigungsprävention) Sie visualisieren Ihre Ergebnisse über ein Erfolgstracking, leiten Handlungsempfehlungen ab und sind auch für deren Kommunikation verantwortlich Sie behalten die Entwicklungen im Auge und setzen kontinuierlich Optimierungspotenziale um Sie wirken an bereichsübergreifenden Projekten zur CRM-Optimierung mit Sie sind Schnittstelle zu anderen datenverarbeitenden Bereichen wie z.B. Data Warehouse und Pricing Das bringen Sie mit: Erfolgreich abgeschlossenes MINT-Studium, Studium der Betriebswirtschaft oder einen vergleichbaren Studiengang Sicherer Umgang mit SQL sowie fundierte Kenntnisse im Umgang mit Microsoft Excel Erste Berufserfahrung und/oder relevante Praktika/Werkstudententätigkeiten wünschenswert Ausgeprägtes analytisches Denkvermögen, sehr gute konzeptionelle Fähigkeiten und eine hohe Problemlösungskompetenz Fähigkeit, komplexe Fragestellungen klar und verständlich zu visualisieren und zu kommunizieren Hohes Engagement, eine ergebnisorientierte und eigenständige Arbeitsweise sowie Teamfähigkeit Eine ausgeprägte Hands-On-Mentalität und Interesse mitzugestalten Sehr gute Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift Ihre Vorteile bei uns: Einstieg: Bei Verti setzen wir auf Kommunikation auf Augenhöhe und ein persönliches Miteinander. Diesen kollegialen Zusammenhalt und unsere Willkommenskultur erleben Sie vom ersten Tag an. So sind Sie erst gar nicht Neuling, sondern gleich Teil von Verti. Perspektive: Bei Einstellung erhalten Sie einen unbefristeten Arbeitsvertrag. Glocal: Lokale Dynamik trifft auf strategischen Weitblick unseres internationalen Mutterkonzerns – wir vereinen das Beste aus allen Welten. Innovation und Expertise: Ein Umfeld, in dem innovative, digitale Ideen wie in einem Start-up vorangetrieben werden – mit den Ressourcen und dem Know-how einer seit über 20 Jahren im Markt erfolgreichen Versicherung. Gestaltungsspielraum²: Wir bieten Ihnen nicht nur einen großen theoretischen Gestaltungsspielraum, sondern auch die Möglichkeit Ihre innovativen Ideen wirklich umzusetzen. Flache Hierarchien: Durch kurze Entscheidungswege machen wir eine schnelle Übernahme von Verantwortung möglich. So arbeiten wir nicht nur ergebnisorientiert - es macht auch Spaß. Leben und Arbeit: Sie sollen sich wohlfühlen und erfolgreich sein können. Dafür bieten wir beste Rahmenbedingungen: einen Gesundheitscoach, einen modernen und ergonomisch gestalteten Arbeitsplatz, eine Kantine mit Wohlfühlatmosphäre und ein Kids-Büro (falls die kurzfristige Betreuung mal nicht funktioniert) sowie flexible Arbeitszeiten sind nur einige Beispiele, die wir unseren Mitarbeitern anbieten.', 'Data Scientist mit Schwerpunkt CRM (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Verti Versicherung AG', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4764, 'ResearchGate is the professional network for scientists and researchers. Not a scientist or researcher? Never heard of us? That’s okay. Accelerating science is what drives us – we''ve built a platform that gives the world''s scientists the tools and services they need to connect, collaborate, and advance their research. Over 15 million members from 193 countries use ResearchGate to share, discover, and discuss research. Our investors include Bill Gates, Benchmark Capital, Founders Fund, Tenaya Capital, Goldman Sachs, Wellcome Trust and Four Rivers Group. We are a global company, with clients, users and colleagues from all corners of the world. Our team of 175 people is located at the heart of Berlin, one of the most exciting cities in the world - a place where everyone feels welcome. We''re guided by our mission to connect the world of science and make research open to all. We are looking for a talented, dedicated and experienced Head of People to report to our CEO and drive our mission through the strategic management of Human Resources, Recruiting, Company Culture, Internal Communications and Workplace initiatives and projects. Our team consists of 15 dedicated individuals who work hard to deliver on our People and Culture and Workplace-related needs. Now, we are looking for a senior level HR professional to lead the team and take us to the next level! The successful candidate will possess at least 8 years experience, with demonstrated success across a range of HR specialist areas and at least 3 years in a Director/Head of level. You will have a strong bias for action, accompanied by excellent team management skills and a proven ability to interact with, and influence senior leadership. Some of your experience in managing and leading change will ideally have been gained in a rapidly scaling environment – with exposure to both success and failure. You will have a strategic view, an entrepreneurial approach, and ideally, exposure to a tech environment. Interpersonally, your transparent style will complement your ability to drive leadership accountability, culture and excellence throughout organisations. Your record of achievement will include change and transformation planning, execution and measurement, and your guidance and coaching of leadership teams will have established your reputation as a trusted senior advisor. You will possess strong communication and interpersonal skills, with an aptitude for managing sensitive situations and building trust. Your previous experience will have assisted you to develop strong analytical and problem-solving skills and an affinity for data-driven approaches. As a result, you will have the ability to assess multiple aspects and impacts of organisational issues and opportunities, anticipate long-term implications, and devise and execute coherent and comprehensive strategies and plans. Curiousity will drive you, and your empathetic style will be balanced by a high level of commercial acumen. Working with smart people, in environments where change is constant will have enhanced your resilient nature and your ability to cope with ambiguity. Like us, you will be driven by our mission of opening the world of science and seeking to contribute in a more globally impactful way. Our company values embody who we are, and why we do what we do. Embrace pragmatic optimism We believe that science can and must be changed. We leverage this optimism to find pragmatic solutions that bring us closer to our goal. Don’t settle To change science, we have to keep challenging the status quo. We keep an open mind, stay curious, and never stop finding new ways to improve the product, ourselves, and the company. Build trust To build a product that scientists trust we first have to trust the people we work with. We share knowledge, communicate openly, take ownership, and trust in each other’s’ skills. Impact over hype Science isn’t going to change overnight, so we’re in it for the long run. We are committed to tackling the big problems, so we can build a successful company with a lasting and positive effect on the world.', 'Head of People', '2019-06-03', 'ResearchGate GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4765, 'What''s next in music happens on SoundCloud first. As the world''s largest open audio platform, SoundCloud is powered by a connected community of creators, listeners and curators who share, discover and influence what''s new, now and next in music and audio. We''re looking for someone to join our search team as an embedded Data Scientist. You will be a member of a diverse and skilled group of Data Scientists that operate across the organisation in product teams, business intelligence and analytics. As a Senior Data Scientist on search, you will take the lead on refining the search experience using your expertise in information retrieval and machine learning. Our Data Scientists work on a wide range of products and problems, embedded with engineering teams having direct impact on our millions of daily active users. We want people that come equipped with an open mind, creativity and a get-it-done attitude. About the role In this role you will be responsible for leading the efforts to build data products and internal solutions for some of the hardest problems in search. You will see projects through from start to finish performing research, prototyping solutions, production deployment at scale and A/B testing to validate your solutions. We love specialists with deep experience, and we expect to use that experience alongside a Data Scientist''s ability to be general and tackle a wide range of problem areas. Some projects you might work on include: Build and evaluate ranking models to improve the search experience of our users; Analyse user journeys and derive success metrics to support product decisions; Applying natural language processing (NLP) techniques to search queries to better understand user-intent and misspellings; About You You are a Senior Data Scientist with a curious analytical mindset, experience with software engineering, and a track record of shipping search solutions at large scale. You have a broad toolkit that spans languages and runtimes, and you can get up-to-speed with new tech stacks quickly. You enjoy working cross-functional with Engineers, Product Managers and peer Data Scientists. You have: A Ph.D. or M.Sc. in a relevant field such as computer science or machine learning (preferred but not required) A minimum of 5 years of experience in a full-time industry position (not academic) A deep understanding of the lifecycle of a Data Science project, with experience in research, solution development, tuning and inspecting models, etc. Experience with Scala, Python or similar languages that are used to ship production models and systems Experience wrangling very large datasets by writing and maintaining data processing pipelines with Hadoop, Spark, BigQuery, Redshift, or similar An ability to tell a story about data, to explore and reveal patterns, and to communicate to stakeholders about your discoveries and hypothesis Worked in cross-functional teams and are able to work in multiple parts of a tech stack Diversity at SoundCloud SoundCloud is for everyone. Diversity and open expression are fundamental to our organization; they help us build a social platform and global community where anyone can create, discover, and share sounds. We acknowledge the challenges in our industry, and strive to develop an inclusive culture where everyone can contribute.', 'Senior Data Scientist Search (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'SoundCloud', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4766, 'PhD degree in Computer Science or related field, or equivalent experience Publications in machine learning or data management conferences or journals (e.g., NIPS, ICML, VLDB, SIGMOD) Experience in machine learning/artificial intelligence, data quality, data science, or information integration research Experience in general-purpose programming languages such as Scala, Python, Java, or C++ Hundreds of millions of customers. Billions of queries per year and dollars in revenue. The scale and impact of Amazon search is huge and we need passionate, talented, and inventive scientists to realize the future of product search worldwide. The Search Customer Experience team is responsible for worldwide customer facing search features on desktops, tablets, and mobile devices. Everything from the moment a customer clicks into the search box to when they view search results. We use machine learning to build smarter and more personalized experiences for our customers across a wide variety of categories, from instant video and Kindle books to apparel and electronics. You will work alongside internationally recognized experts to develop novel algorithms and modeling techniques to advance the state-of-the-art in machine learning and data management. Applied Scientists at Amazon work in teams with Software Development Engineers to bring novel ideas into production systems. At Amazon, you have the ability to publish research papers and to work on a diverse team. 2+ years Post-doc or industry experience Experience with machine learning frameworks, distributed storage systems, or data processing frameworks Strong publication record', 'Applied Scientist - Amazon Search', '2019-06-03', 'Amazon Development Center DEU', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4767, 'Our client, the MENA region’s leading driver booking service requires a Data Scientist to join their rapidly developing analytics team based in Berlin. The Data Scientist will: Will work closely with the product and engineering teams to define and confront a range of problems and embark on exploratory data analysis projects to achieve better understanding of phenomena as well as to discover untapped areas of growth and optimization. Help define and track the appropriate key metrics for specific projects. Design and run randomized controlled experiments, analyse the resulting data and communicate results with other teams. Collaborate with engineers to build prototype predictive models into production and re-iterate as needed. Focus on dynamic pricing optimization, optimal dispatching, fraud detection and prevention, ETA prediction and location search optimization. The Data Scientist will: Be innovative, detail-oriented, result-focused, have a solid quantitative background - Advanced degree in a quantitative discipline such as Physics, Statistics, Mathematics, Engineering or Computer Science. Have 2+ years’ experience in data mining, predictive modelling, time series analysis, machine learning, Big Data methodologies, transformation and cleaning of both structured and unstructured data. Be fluent in English along with excellent oral and written communication skills. Be proficient and have demonstrated experience in at least 2 of the following: SQL, R, Python, Spark, Hive, RapidMiner. Have demonstrated experience with database technologies (e.g. Hadoop, Amazon EMR, Hive, Oracle, SAP, DB2, Teradata, MS SQL Server, MySQL) is a plus. Have demonstrated experience with business intelligence and visualization tools (Tableau, MicroStrategy, ChartIO, Qlik) along with geospatial data processing skills is also a plus. Be business savvy, and take full ownership of their work from the inception of the idea to the implementation of the final product. Have knowledge of Agile methodologies To apply please send your CV or call 01706 825 199.', 'Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'Aspire Data Recruitment', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4768, 'Lead Data Scientist - Decision Systems Credit Risk Python, SQL, scikit-learn, keras, tensorflow, mxnet, pytorch, Hive, Spark, EMR, AWS, Google Cloud Salary Range: EUR 75.000 - 85.000 BERLIN, GERMANY THE COMPANY Leading consumer payment provider active in enabling a smooth and modern purchase experience for consumers and merchants is looking for a Lead Data Scientist with a focus on creating classification models for real time credit risk scoring of large volumes of consumer data. The company offers unprecedented learning opportunities along the whole spectrum of data science in a cloud environment and enables close interaction and collaboration with developers, technical and non-technical team members and enjoys substantial and sustained growth in its user base. The successful candidate will have experience in a cloud environment (AWS, Google, Azure) and have intricate machine learning experience in a production environment. An end-to-end approach to Data Science from data acquisition through modelling to deployment and performance measurement as well as a good understanding of a model''s real-world business impact are key skills for the role. Market specific insights towards consumer credit and experience with automated credit risk scoring are beneficial but no must haves. A creative mindset, open attitude and ambition to learn and develop further is what the company is looking for. THE ROLE This exciting opportunity of Lead Data Scientist - Credit Risk will have you design advanced models for transaction classification and bring them to production utilizing AWS. The role acts as a full stack, end-to-end data scientist to support model development from root cause analysis, data collection as well as feature engineering through to validation, model deployment and, ultimately, model performance monitoring. As an embedded resource within the engineering organisation you will collaborate closely with engineers and non-technical business stakeholders to work out how to best collect data and thereby improve model accuracy and prediction performance. You will have a software driven workflow to ensure efficient model deployment into production and adhere to SW engineering best practices. YOUR SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE Must haves: An open mind, critical thinking skills and collaborative approach Coding skills in Python and SQL as well as experience in machine and deep learning packages Experience with cloud applications (AWS, Google) and Hive, Spark, EMR Exposure to and understanding of traditional and state of the art machine learning models and algorithms (generalized linear models, random forests, ensemble methods, deep neural networks) Educational background in math, physics, engineering or economics Good communication skills and ability to present insights and discoveries about data and patterns to peers as well as non-technical management and cross-functional stakeholders Fluent communication skills in English Nice to haves: Prior experience with consumer credit risk modelling, specifically classification models for rapid transaction scoring and automated credit decisioning systems HOW TO APPLY Please register your interest by sending your CV to Peter Schroeter via the Apply link on this page.', 'Lead Data Scientist - Decision Systems Credit Risk', '2019-06-03', 'Harnham', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4769, 'Fyber is a global technology company, developing a next-generation monetization platform for mobile publishers. Fyber combines proprietary technologies and expertise in mediation, RTB, video and audience segmentation to create holistic solutions that shape the future of the mobile app economy. Our vision is to create a world in which people have affordable access to quality content, while enjoying a pleasant, relevant user experience. Fyber is the powerful combination of 4 leading ad tech companies with complimentary publisher-focused technologies and capabilities, enabling us to introduce a range of truly innovative solutions packaged into a single mobile publisher platform. Our mission is to empower mobile publishers to unlock the true value of their properties by building a holistic, efficient, frictionless monetization environment. We are currently looking for an experienced Business Fraud Analyst who will analyze cases as they come in and conceptualize and create monitoring systems that will allow our team to detect and react to known and unknown threats. Your Role: Define the necessary tools and KPIs needed for the monitoring of traffic risks on the global Fyber platform. Constantly develop new signals to improve our reaction time to known suspicious threats and find new paths through proactive analysis. Analyze claims coming in, confirm whether fraudulent activity/ad quality breach has taken place and suggest measures to be taken to stop it moving forward. Support the business teams understanding traffic patterns and leading negotiations. Escalate cases when needed and work towards providing transparency to our customers. Educate the organization around the topic of fraud & ad quality and how to protect against it. Identify potential product and system vulnerabilities. Your Qualifications: University degree (Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, Operations Research or similar field) Relevant experience as a data scientist, business intelligence analyst or similar role At least 1 year experience analyzing massive sources of data (online or transactional fraud) - this terms resulted applications from a lot of unrelevant applicants Experience with business intelligence tools like Tableau, Business Objects etc. Very deep understanding of SQL Strong technical understanding of how internet applications work, especially from a security point of view Programming skills (C/C++/Python/JAVA/PHP/HTML) are a plus Experience in AdTech or FinTech is a big plus Highly analytical and self-organized Initiative, proactive and excellent communication skills Enjoy all of the perks of: free food/drinks (daily breakfasts, bi-weekly Thursday''s lunches, Friday''s happy hours, free fresh fruit and high-energetic drinks), 5 extra recharge days to enjoy your longer weekends flexible working hours stock options, our employees are fundamental for us and share our success with them pension scheme subsidized by company amazing office space in the heart of Berlin, highly equipped office building discounts for gym memberships internal and external training sessions Global team building social events Learn and grow with some of the best experts in the mobile industry. Work with a high-growth, software company (with over 350 employees worldwide). Join a friendly, culturally diverse team (+35 nationalities) where people live values like dedication, team spirit, mutual respect and accountability. Fyber is an equal opportunity employer. You are welcome to our Fyber team no matter your gender, race, color, ethnicity, nationality, religion, sexual orientation, age, disability, family status or any other matter.', 'Business Fraud Analyst*', '2019-06-03', 'Fyber', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4770, 'ABOUT THE TEAM -------------- Department: Customer Care Reports to: Engineering Lead Team Size: 15 Recruiter Name: Alicja Notowska ( alicja.notowska@zalando.de ) As a Senior Data Scientist, you will work on a new Machine Learning product that predicts which customers are likely to contact Customer Care soon and what their question will be, so we can contact them about it first. WHERE YOUR EXPERTISE IS NEEDED ------------------------------ Creating predictive models of customer issues to allow us to identify the customers whom we can proactively help without them having to contact us Querying and analysing data, setting up monitoring and data quality assurance Collaborating with engineers to translate ML prototypes into production systems Collaborating with product managers and other stakeholders to identify new areas of potential impact WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR ---------------------------- Excellent educational background (minimum M.Sc) in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics or other similar quantitative field At least 3 years of industry experience with Python and ML-related libraries such as pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow, Keras, XGBoost and big data frameworks such as Spark, Dask Strong understanding of Machine Learning methods and techniques, especially for customer behavior analysis and prediction Experience in building and maintaining data pipelines and collecting data from multiple sources and formats, and working with data science based services that provide an API PERKS AT WORK ------------- Working with large data sets including customer data, order data, and customer care data Community of nearly 100 data scientists at Zalando whom you can collaborate with and learn from Working in an agile development team with strong dedicated ownership of projects Culture of trust, empowerment and constructive feedback,open source ( https://opensource.zalando.com/ ) commitment, meetups, game nights, 70+ internal technical and fun guilds, knowledge sharing through tech talks, internal tech academy andblogs ( https://jobs.zalando.com/tech/blog/ ), product demos, parties & events Competitive salary, employee share shop, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, centrally located offices, public transport discounts, municipality services, great IT equipment, flexible working times, additional holidays and volunteering time off, free beverages and fruits, diverse sports and health offerings Extensive onboarding, mentoring and personal development opportunities and an international team of experts Relocation assistance for internationals, PME family service and parent & child rooms* (*available in select locations) We celebrate diversity and are committed to building teams that represent a variety of backgrounds, perspectives and skills. All employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. ABOUT ZALANDO ------------- At Zalando we care deeply about our customers and are always looking for ways to deliver a delightful customer experience. You will join a multi-disciplinary Berlin based Customer Care Technology Team, composed of engineers, product managers, content managers and system admins of 10 different nationalities. We are responsible for the technology between the customer and the Customer Care centres, using a variety of different technologies and approaches to help the customer get their problem solved. You will work with Product Specialists and engineers to implement and improve a data product that can anticipate customer needs and help solve them proactively, before the customer contacts us. This is the next generation of Customer Care and an exciting opportunity to make a real difference in the experience of millions of Zalando customers across all our markets. Customer Care is connected to all Zalando departments, so you will get a good understanding of different processes across the business.', 'Senior Data Scientist - Customer Care Technology', '2019-06-03', 'Zalando', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4771, 'Du hast Talent. Wir sind ein internationales Netzwerk aus 250.930 Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeitern, die ihr Wissen, ihre Erfahrungen und ihre Ideen miteinander teilen. Du suchst einen herausfordernden, spannenden Job. Wir bieten dir als weltweit führende Wirtschaftsprüfungs- und Beratungsgesellschaft ein Maximum an Möglichkeiten für einen Karriereweg nach deinen Vorstellungen. Du möchtest Verantwortung für deine Ergebnisse übernehmen, Lösungen gemeinsam mit dem Kunden entwickeln und einen Arbeitgeber mit passenden Werten. Unser Denken und Handeln orientiert sich an Grundsätzen, die von Vertrauen, Respekt, Weitsicht und Wertschätzung geprägt sind. Deine Aufgaben Software project - Together with a senior data scientist you work on a project to automate processes in indirect tax from conceptualization to implementation. Tasks include scrapping and organizing data and applying machine learning algorithms for prediction and classification. Data analysis - You assist team members in data analyses and data visualization for client projects such as outlier detection in financial transaction or visualization of indirect taxes. Legal tech - You gain insight into the legal tech market by working with our tools and monitoring the latest developments in the tax technology market. Network - You work in a young heterogeneous team, eager to shape the indirect tax technology market. Dein Profil You are proficient scripting R or Python. You have some experience with web technologies (javascript, HTML, css) You have gained some experience with machine learning algorithms You are confident with SQL and relational databases You have a growth mindset and are eager to learn new skills Tax or financial accounting knowledge is a plus German language skills are not required but a plus', 'Internship Data science Indirect Taxes (w/m/d)', '2019-06-03', 'PwC', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4772, 'Du magst Pinguine, Prozesse und Daten? Als Big Data Analytics Software revolutioniert LANA Process Mining die Welt der Prozessanalyse. LANA steht für "Log Analytics Automated" und unser Logo, der Pinguin, für unsere Software, die es erlaubt in dem Meer der undurchsichtigen Daten gezielt die Prozesse mit unserer Process Mining Software zu analysieren. Für jede verkaufte Lizenz und jeden Mitarbeiterin unterstützen wir zudem eine Kolonie von seltenen Magellan Pinguinen in Südchile. Um noch mehr Unternehmen hohe Einsparpotentiale und Pinguinadoptionen zu ermöglichen, suchen wir hilfsbereite & smarte Köpfe für unsere Process Mining Analysen. LANA - improve the world, one process at a time! Deine Mission Mentoring und Weiterenwicklung des Data Scientist Team, Unterstützung beim ﻿Aufsetzen von ﻿Tools und Prozessen Vorbereitung und Leitung von Workshops und Präsentationen fürs Management und unsere Kundschaft Steuerung und ﻿Kontrolle von Kundenprojekten, von den Anforderungen bis zur Live-Schaltung Entwicklung, Einsatz und Erhaltung von ﻿skalierbaren Big ﻿Data Pipelines Enge Zusammenarbeit mit Development und Devons Teams zu neuen Features, z.B. ﻿Streaming Prototypisierung von neuen Machine Learning Modellen für fortgeschrittene Analyse und Vorhersagen Schnittstelle zwischen Development und Data Science Teams, mit deiner Erfahrung hilfst du allen ﻿Seiten voranzukommen Sicherstellen und Aufrechterhaltung / Management von Daten Integration und Datenqualität Dein Profil 3+ Jahre Erfahrung, idealerweise Erfahrung als Teamlead Erfahrung mit distributed processing frameworks, idealerweise Spark Experience building, deploying and maintaining Big Data pipelines Erfolgreiche Kundeninteraktionen und Projektmanagement, idealerweise im B2B Bereich oder als Consultant Nachweisbarer track record in der Lösungsfindung für Big ﻿Data Probleme Gute Kenntnisse in ein bis zwei modernen Programmier-Sprachen Erfahrung in der Arbeit mit APIs/Interfaces von enterprise systems (e.g. SAP, Salesforce) Erfahrung mit SQL Fließendes Deutsch und Englisch Erfahrung in Datenvisualisierung, idealerweise R/Shiny Erfahrungen im Bereich Machine Learning Bonus: JVM Erfahrung (idealerweise Scala) und ﻿/ oder einer funktionalen Sprach Erfahrung mit SAP, JDE, SalesForce, Service Now oder ähnlicher enterprise software Erfahrung in der Anwendung von Machine Learning auf Time series data / process data Erfahrung in Business Process Modelling, Process analysis, BI What we offer Herausforderung im spannendsten Start-Up für Process Mining Hochmotiviertes, internationales Team Weitere Benefits wie wöchentlicher Teamlunch, täglich Obst & Getränke, flexible Arbeitszeiten, Sustainability und soziales Engagement als Part unserer Firmenkultur Einen eigenen Adoptiv-Pinguin in Südchile Wir freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung! Unfortunately we cannot accept your application if you level of German is below C1.', 'Senior Data Scientist &amp; Consultant', '2019-06-03', 'Lana Labs GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4773, 'As a Senior Data Scientist you''ll join our growing Data Products team and have a chance to make a large impact. As an embedded member of our Product or Marketing teams, you will be a trusted partner in a cross-functional team tackling the toughest and most impactful problems. The vast and diverse set of structured and unstructured data GetYourGuide has collected is powering data products such as search, recommendations and supplier on-boarding. You will own your projects end-to-end and work on the approach, build algorithms, data pipelines and metrics to measure success. Responsibilities: Build data products ( https://hbr.org/2018/10/how-to-build-great-data-products ) that delight our customers and boost our business Develop your ideas from a hypothesis to code in production Build data pipelines to feed your algorithms Analyze vast amounts of data to identify new opportunities Contribute in developing our machine learning infrastructure and best practices Make your team greater via continuous improvements and help in recruiting Requirements: Machine Learning: You apply regressors, classifiers, and recommenders. You understand in detail the underpinning of ML techniques. Applied experience productionizing machine learning models is a plus. Software Engineering: You are fluent in a modern programming language (Scala/Python). Working knowledge on distributed machine learning and computing framework (Spark) is a plus. Analytics: You are able to transform data into wisdom. You know how to test hypotheses. You are proficient with an analytics tool (pandas, R) and with SQL. Business Experience: You applied the skills mentioned above in a business environment for 4+ years. A track record of result-driven work gives evidence of this. Academic Background: You have an advanced degree in a quantitative field and can easily learn new skills or techniques We Offer: Work on a product that helps create memorable travel experiences Smart, engaged co-workers Speak English in the office with people from over 68 nationalities Virtual stock options - be part of our success story Monthly Hackathons and weekly tech talks Annual external training budget - be constantly learning Well stocked kitchen and our famous pizza & beer Friday''s GetYourGuide vouchers and free German lessons Relocation Assistance Curious? It is our commitment that every qualified person will be evaluated according to skills regardless of age, gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability status, or religion. Please refrain from including your picture and age with the application. You can get in touch with us via jobs@getyourguide.com ( jobs@getyourguide.com ), and make sure you check out life at GetYourGuide on our blog ( http://inside.getyourguide.com/ ). You can also take a look at our Tech Radar ( https://techradar.getyourguide.com/ ) for an insight into our stack.', 'Senior Data Scientist - Data Product', '2019-06-03', 'GetYourGuide', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4774, 'DEIN JOB: Du bist verantwortlich für die End-to-End Entwicklung und Operationalisierung von Machine Learning-Modellen in einem Team hochmotivierter Data Scientists und Data Engineers Du steuerst die Durchführung von explorativen Analysen strukturierter und unstrukturierter Datensätze sowie Feature Engineering Die Entwicklung von prädiktiven Machine Learning-Modellen gehört ebenfalls zu Deinen Aufgaben Daneben übernimmst Du die Operationalisierung von Modellen als API Weiterhin bist Du an der Definition und Ausarbeitung neuer Data Science-Anwendungsfälle in enger Zusammenarbeit mit einzelnen Fachabteilungen beteiligt DEIN PROFIL: Deine Erfahrung hat ein sicheres Fundament: Du hast ein abgeschlossenes Studium der Mathematik, Statistik, Data Science, Physik, Informatik oder eines vergleichbaren Studiengangs Promotion im Bereich Machine-Learning ist von Vorteil Du besitzt fundierte Kenntnisse in Machine Learning und Statistik Sehr gute Kenntnisse in den Programmiersprachen Python, R oder Scala kannst Du ebenfalls vorweisen Deine Kompetenzen liegen im Einsatz von Open-Source Machine Learning-Bibliotheken Ein Souveräner Umgang mit der Kommandozeile, Shell Scripting und Versionskontrollsystemen gehören zu Deinen Stärken Wenn Du idealerweise Erfahrung mit Spark, Hadoop oder SQL sowie der Anwendung von modernen Softwareentwicklungsmethoden hast, dann bist Du bei uns genau richtig Daneben zeichnest Du dich durch Teamfähigkeit, Kommunikationsfähigkeit und Hands-on-Mentalität aus UNSER ANGEBOT: Wir bieten Dir die herausragende Chance, als Schnittstelle zwischen unserer Data Science Abteilung, der NEW YORKER IT und den Fachbereichen zu fungieren und dabei eigene Ideen einzubringen, die konzernweit umgesetzt werden. Dabei kannst Du an spannenden Data Science-Fragestellungen arbeiten und wirst von NEW YORKER durch z. B. Meet-ups, Kurse und Konferenzen in Deiner persönlichen Entwicklung gefördert. Neben attraktiven Mitarbeiterangeboten, Sozialleistungen und Weiterbildungsmöglichkeiten erwartet Dich ein offenes und dynamisches Team mit flachen Hierarchien. Hast Du Lust, die Optimierung unserer internen Prozesse voranzutreiben und an komplexen Themen wie der Warenverteilung und Kunden-Empfehlungssystemen zu arbeiten? Dann freuen wir uns auf Deine aussagekräftige Online-Bewerbung unter Angabe Deines frühestmöglichen Eintrittstermins und Deiner Gehaltsvorstellung. NEW YORKER Group-Services International GmbH & Co. KG Ansprechpartner: Svea Popovic www.newyorker.de/Jobs', '(Senior) Data Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'New Yorker', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4775, 'Wer wir sind Als Spezialist*innen für künstliche Intelligenz, maschinelles Lernen und mathematische Modellierung unterstützen wir unsere Kund*innen entlang der gesamten Wertschöpfungskette: von der strategischen Beratung, über die konzeptionelle Lösungsentwicklung bis hin zur Implementierung der Lösungen in Softwaresystemen. Was uns antreibt Uns fasziniert an unserer Arbeit, dass wir mit allen neuen Kund*innen die Möglichkeit haben, ein ganz neues Umfeld kennenzulernen. So erfahren wir tagtäglich mehr über die Welt, in der wir leben. Uns motiviert, dass die Lösungen, die wir entwickeln, bei unseren Kund*innen einen echten Impact haben. Neue Menschen kennenzulernen, uns auf sie einzustellen und für sie zu arbeiten, macht uns Freude. Selbstständigkeit und der Drang sich stetig weiter zu entwickeln sind für diese Art zu arbeiten die wichtigsten Voraussetzungen. Diese grundsätzliche Einstellung ist uns bei neuen Team-Mitgliedern sogar wichtiger als bereits erworbene Kenntnisse und Fähigkeiten. Niemand in unserem Team betrachtet die eigene Entwicklung als abgeschlossen. Wenn auch Sie das Gefühl haben, in Ihrem Gebiet noch tiefer graben und noch mehr verstehen zu müssen, dann können wir das bestens nachvollziehen und freuen uns sehr, Sie kennenzulernen! Wen wir suchen Sie denken unternehmerisch, sind grenzenlos neugierig, haben einen ausgeprägten Schaffensdrang und wollen einen positiven Impact generieren. Sie haben Freude daran, sich weiterzuentwickeln, an Herausforderungen zu arbeiten und nach Exzellenz zu streben. In allem was Sie tun, legen Sie außerdem großen Wert auf starke zwischenmenschliche Beziehungen. Ihre Qualifikationen Sie studieren ein quantitatives Fach im Master (z.B. Ökonometrie, Informatik, Mathematik, Physik oder Ingenieurwesen) und verfügen über erste Erfahrungen im Bereich Datenanalyse, Statistik oder Machine Learning und haben grundlegende Programmierkenntnisse in Python oder R. Idealerweise haben Sie in interessanten Praktika oder Werkstudententätigkeiten auch bereits Erfahrungen im Consulting gesammelt. Gern gesehen sind auch Erfahrungen mit Datenvisualisierung und Software Engineering. Zu Ihren Stärken zählen effektive, freundliche Kommunikation und lösungsorientiertes, analytisches Denken. Sie können im Schnitt zwei Tage pro Woche arbeiten, in den Semesterferien auch mehr. Lassen Sie sich nicht davon abhalten, dass Sie eventuell eine der Anforderungen noch nicht erfüllen. Sagen Sie uns, warum Sie gerne in unserem Team arbeiten wollen und überzeugen Sie uns von sich. Unser Angebot Wir suchen unsere Kolleg*innen von morgen – bei idalab sind Sie von Beginn an Teil eines starken Teams, in dem Sie als vollwertiges Mitglied wertgeschätzt werden. Als Junior Data Scientist entwickeln sie unter dem Mentoring Ihrer erfahrenen Kolleg*innen komplexe Modelle, die Sie auch selbst bei unseren Kund*innen vorstellen werden. Sie werden lernen neben Ihren analytischen Fähigkeiten auch ein Gespür für die konzeptionellen, strategischen und kommunikativen Seiten Ihres Projektes zu entwickeln und auftretende Probleme pragmatisch zu lösen. Wir bieten unseren Junior Data Scientists eine hochwertige Arbeitsausstattung und eine attraktive Vergütung von 15 Euro/Stunde (nach einem Jahr 17 Euro/Stunde) - zuzüglich Gewinnbeteiligung. Unser Bewerbungsverfahren Unser Bewerbungsverfahren für Junior Data Scientists folgt einem standardisierten Prozess. Ein Online-Test fragt grundsätzliche Mathematik- und Statistikkenntnisse ab. Im Telefoninterview möchten wir mehr über Ihre Motivation und ihre Fähigkeiten komplexe Modelle auf zugängliche Art und Weise zu erklären erfahren. Unsere Challenge bietet Ihnen die Möglichkeit, Ihre technischen Fähigkeiten unter Beweis zu stellen. Am Interviewtag schließlich werden Sie die Ergebnisse Ihrer Challenge dem Team präsentieren und in insgesamt drei Einzelinterviews, sowie beim gemeinsamen Frühstück mit dem Team die Möglichkeit haben, Ihre zukünftigen Kolleg*innen kennenzulernen. Bewerben Sie sich bitte mit Ihrem Anschreiben, CV und einem Nachweis über bisher erbrachte Prüfungsleistungen (inklusive Noten) über die Karriereseite unserer Homepage. Wir freuen uns von Ihnen zu hören und sind gespannt auf Ihre Bewerbung!', 'Working Student Data Science (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'idalab GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4776, 'Grover is offering a simple, monthly subscription model for the best in tech. We are the first financing company for the circular economy, breaking the link between ownership and use, and buying products, so people don’t have to. Private customers as well as businesses get access to a wide assortment of tech products at a fraction of the purchase price. We’re on a mission to reinvent consumption, go easier on the world’s resources, and make innovative tech products accessible to everyone. As our community is growing every day, we’re now looking for a Data Engineer. Over the past year, we raised one of Europe’s largest Series A funding rounds with a total of €37 million, providing the capital that fuels the rapid growth of the company. If you feel like being challenged, working hard and learning a lot, come and join us for a unique rewarding experience. About the Role Together with Data Scientist, Data engineers are the central node to the Data Strategy of Grover. As a Data Engineer, you will be interfacing with front-end and back-end engineer to collect insights about our customers. Every decision at Grover is data driven, you will be working on the systems and tools that define our analytical power. Your Role: Productionize machine learning algorithms, help data scientists improve Grover platform Build robust distributed systems to process large scale data streams into useful applications Engineer fast, real-time data pipelines to process data from multiple sources to make fast and accurate decisions Implement risk monitoring systems to improve tracking and mitigation of several risks including fraud Work closely with data scientists and collaborate with back-end, front-end engineers to build products for gathering timely insights about customer behaviour, etc Create monitoring systems to track of the quality of data and the health of our systems Your Profile: Motivated and fast learner Proficient in Python Knowledge of SQL Understanding of Distributed systems Experience with Async programming (asyncio, tornado, twisted, Trio) is a plus Experience working with REST APIs and/or SOAP is a plus Technologies we use: Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana (ELK) Kafka Redis Redshift + AWS Suite Zookeeper What we offer you: Entrepreneurial responsibility and flat-hierarchies Ownership of your work Fun at work Modern, spacious office located in central Berlin A fun workplace Fresh Fruit & Drinks Team Events About us Grover is the one of the European market leaders in technology rentals, bringing the access economy to the consumer electronics market. If you want to work with a dedicated team at a fast-growing company, and help us to change the world of consumption? Then you’re in the right place. At Grover, we value entrepreneurship, intelligence, and speed in everything we do. We’re a team of over 70 creative and motivated minds, from more than 25 countries – which means our aims, beliefs, and ways of working are influenced by many different perspectives. We care for individuality and for team spirit, and act courageously and communicate openly. In our HQ, in Berlin Mitte, there’s no room for hierarchy, and plenty of space for fun, collaboration, and rethinking the way the world does, uses and values things.', 'Data Engineer // Grover', '2019-06-03', 'Grover', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4777, 'The Berlin-based Max Delbrück Center for Molecular Medicine in the Helmholtz Association (MDC) is one of the world-leading research institutes for molecular biology and genetics. MDC offers a large variety of cutting-edge technologies in life sciences. MDC has also a special focus on translational approaches to develop treatments for neurological, cardiovascular, metabolic diseases and cancer. MDC represents a lively and competitive research environment. The Animal Phenotyping Platform (APP) at the Max-Delbrueck-Center invites applications for a full-time MRI scientist to lead our state-of-the-art preclinical laboratory for magnetic resonance imaging. The APP is a comprehensive phenotyping lab that includes MRI (Bruker 3T system), micro-CT, ultrasound, photoacoustic imaging, and a range of in vivo optical imaging technologies. The position will broadly focus on the application of MRI to provide structural, microstructural and physiological data for preclinical models of disease and quantify alterations associated with therapy. We seek a highly motivated scientist with extensive MRI experience to advance preclinical MRI research to support MDC research groups. The scientist will develop and apply advanced MR imaging and data analysis techniques to address research questions across multiple therapeutic areas that may also have clinical translation application. Requirements The successful candidate should have an MD, MD/PhD, PhD, or equivalent degree with at least 3 years experience in MRI. The ideal candidate should have an advanced degree related to MRI, be able to handle anesthetized rodent subjects, adjust imaging parameters, and troubleshoot for scanner problems. The candidate will be involved in the application of novel methods and must demonstrate a keen awareness of image acquisition, animal handling, lab skills, image analysis and data visualization to help advance the imaging methods. Clear and accurate communication skills are a requirement in order to communicate with the various research groups. The candidate is also expected to have excellent writing and presentation skills. Applicants should send a CV, a brief outline of their research experience and interests and two letters of reference by e-mail to heuser@mdc-berlin.de. The MDC is an equal opportunity employer and supports gender equality. Please, send your application including all documents indicating the registration number preferably by e-mail to jobs@mdc-berlin.de as pdf files (2 files of 5 MB at the maximum) as we do not return any papers.', 'Post-doctoral Position', '2019-06-03', 'Max-Delbrück-Centrum für Molekulare Medizin', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4778, 'ABOUT THE TEAM -------------- Department: Zalando Research ( https://research.zalando.com/ ) Reports to: Research Head Team Size: 10 Recruiter Name: Alicja Notowska ( alicja.notowska@zalando.de ) We''re Zalando''s incubator for bold scientific experimentation. Machine Learning & AI are our research fields; including today''s most exciting topics, such as Deep Learning, Computer Vision & NLP, Large Scale Bayesian Inference, Reinforcement Learning, Causality. WHERE YOUR EXPERTISE IS NEEDED ------------------------------ Your work will be use case inspired basic research, enabled by your expertise, by Zalando''s vast data pool, and by our excellent high performance computing infrastructure Your developments will power Zalando''s next gen data products. Your research results will enhance your publication track record in the most exciting international academic community WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR ---------------------------- PhD degree in Machine Learning, NLP, Computer Vision, Data Mining, or similar field 3-5 years of proven experience in academic research or comparable research environment Strong publication record in top-tier research conferences and journals Deep understanding of theory behind state of the art Machine Learning methods in your domain, broad overview of Machine Learning methods, as well as knowing best practices in their application Experience as a speaker at scientific conferences or public scientific meetups Proven experience in leading Machine Learning research projects in a postdoc position Software engineering skills for prototype development and implementation of experimental setups PERKS AT WORK ------------- Culture of trust, empowerment and constructive feedback, open source ( https://opensource.zalando.com/ ) commitment, meetups, game nights, 70+ internal technical and fun guilds, knowledge sharing through tech talks, internal tech academy and blogs ( https://jobs.zalando.com/tech/blog/ ), product demos, parties & events Competitive salary, employee share shop, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, centrally located offices, public transport discounts, municipality services, great IT equipment, flexible working times, additional holidays and volunteering time off, free beverages and fruits, diverse sports and health offerings Extensive onboarding, mentoring and personal development opportunities and an international team of experts Relocation assistance for internationals, PME family service and parent & child rooms* (*available in select locations) We celebrate diversity and are committed to building teams that represent a variety of backgrounds, perspectives and skills. All employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. ABOUT ZALANDO ------------- Zalando is Europe''s leading online platform for fashion, connecting customers, brands and partners across 17 markets. We drive digital solutions for fashion, logistics, advertising and research, bringing head-to-toe fashion to more than 23 million active customers through diverse skill-sets, interests and languages ( https://opensource.zalando.com/tech-radar/ ) our teams choose to use. Zalando Research is one of the most collaborative places you can imagine. Partnerships begin within our own teams, with all key engineering and product teams, and with the international scientific community beyond Zalando. We stretch the limits of theory and apply novel ideas in practice and we experiment. We strongly encourage our team members to stay on top of the academic progress, seek patents, and publish research results whenever possible. If you are interested in doing academic research in a fascinating corporate environment then come join us! Please note that all applications must be completed in English using the online form - we do not accept applications via e-mail.', 'Research Scientist - Machine Learning &amp; AI', '2019-06-03', 'Zalando', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4779, 'So gestalten Sie Innovationen mit: Fachliche Leitung von Kundenprojekten im Kontext künstliche Intelligenz und Machine Learning für Gesundheitsanwendungen Konzeption und Implementierung von Artificial Intelligence / Machine Learning / Deep Learning Lösungen Unterstützung der Akquise von Kundenprojekten als fachlicher Experte in interdisziplinären Teams (Konzepterstellung, Use Cases, fachliche Beratung) Das bringen Sie mit: Erfolgreich absolviertes Studium der Informatik, Mathematik oder ein vergleichbarer Abschluss Mehrjährige Berufserfahrung in Extraktion von aussagekräftigen Daten aus großen Datenmengen – idealerweise im Umfeld Medizintechnik / Pharma / Diagnostik Praktische Erfahrung in Konzeption und Implementierung von Machine Learning / Deep Learning Lösungen – von der Methodenwahl bis zur Validierung Sehr fundierte Kenntnisse in Machine Learning Algorithmen, neuronalen Netzen und Entscheidungssystemen Gute Kenntnisse in Python, Datenbankmodellen, Java/C++/C# Klare Kommunikation und die Fähigkeit, komplexe Zusammenhänge und relevante Forschungsergebnisse an Kunde und das Entwicklungsteam zu vermitteln', 'Senior Data Scientist Medical', '2019-06-03', 'ITK Engineering', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4780, 'ABOUT THE TEAM -------------- Department: Zalon Data Reports to: Product Owner Team Size: < 5 Recruiter Name: Taryn Bonugli ( taryn.bonugli@zalando.de ) You are the bridge between machine learning algorithms and expert-human judgement. You make our article recommendations to generate innovative styles. You develop models that will create an adaptive, personalized new experience for our customers. WHERE YOUR EXPERTISE IS NEEDED ------------------------------ Support the team with your experience and technical skills Design the architecture and the analytics pipelines while taking into account appropriate time frames, and costs Contribute to developing Zalon''s overall technical capabilities by working one-on-one with your Data Scientists and Engineers Influence and rally the organization around new opportunities in order to turn obscure business problems into opportunities for algorithmic approaches WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR ---------------------------- Master''s or PhD in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or another quantitative field together with 5 or more years of industry experience in Data Science Experience in creating and implementing machine learning algorithms and advanced statistics in Python (and optionally R), together with comprehension of engineering best practices, which enables you to write high-quality production code with the support of a Software Engineer Strong proficiency in SQL queries and demonstrable experience in the full pipeline of data and software engineering, analytics, machine learning algorithms and production ready product Ability to work, collaborate and communicate in an agile and cross-functional team with engineers, product owners and other data scientists PERKS AT WORK ------------- Culture of trust, empowerment and constructive feedback, open source ( https://opensource.zalando.com/ ) commitment, meetups, game nights, 70+ internal technical and fun guilds, knowledge sharing through tech talks, internal tech academy and blogs ( https://jobs.zalando.com/tech/blog/ ), product demos, parties & events Competitive salary, employee share shop, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, centrally located offices, public transport discounts, municipality services, great IT equipment, flexible working times, additional holidays and volunteering time off, free beverages and fruits, diverse sports and health offerings Extensive onboarding, mentoring and personal development opportunities and an international team of experts Relocation assistance for internationals, PME family service and parent & child rooms* (*available in select locations) We celebrate diversity and are committed to building teams that represent a variety of backgrounds, perspectives and skills. All employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. ABOUT ZALON ----------- ZALON ( https://www.zalon.de/work-at-zalon ) is Zalando''s curated shopping service. Currently available in Germany, Austria, Switzerland, the Netherlands and Belgium, we connect customers to personal stylists and constantly changing selections. Whether it''s an outfit for a specific occasion, a general makeover or the thrill of trying something fresh, we focus on building a deep understanding of an individual''s personal style and particular needs, translating it into outfits and looks they''ll love. You will be a part of a senior and autonomous team of Software Engineers, Data Engineers and Data scientists. Our mission is to build cutting-edge data science products that support our fashion experts and enhance the experience of our customers.', 'Senior Data Scientist - Zalon Data', '2019-06-03', 'Zalando', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4781, 'To enhance our European Network Planning team that is largely centralized in Berlin, we are looking for a motivated Network Planner who is keen to operate in an international environment. A large part of the job exists of gathering data and using this data within GIS-tools, Microsoft excel and Power BI to find the best locations to extend our charger network. Since we are one of the main players in this new and growing industry, you will be able to shape the future of transport. You will mainly work with our Sales and Data Modelling colleagues to deliver and assess potential locations, and of course with your network planning colleagues. You will report to the team lead of our European Network Development team. Find the best locations for new chargers based on demand, existing infrastructure and other spatial factors Translate the company strategy into the charging network of the future Continuously improve the network planning process and knowledge base You have strong analytical skills and are able to independently deploy new ways of working to continuously adapt to the rapidly changing environment we are working in. Experience in data analysis and a deep interest in spatial planning are essential, best combined with at least basic experience in programming or database handling. You enjoy working with numbers and are always looking for ways to use data to improve our results and forecasts. Strong communication skills are required since you will collaborate with multiple internal stakeholders. As we will expand our network to many European countries, you are not afraid of fellow-Europeans. 3-5 years of experience as analyst, data scientist or comparable data related job Strong analytical skills and a passion for working with numbers Excel knowledge is a must, GIS (QGIS), Python and/or SQL knowledge is a plus Fluency in English Excitement to work in the highly innovative and international sector of sustainable mobility', 'Network Planner (M-V)', '2019-06-03', 'Allego', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4783, 'As a part of our fast growing team, we’re looking for an experienced Senior Data Scientist (f/m/d) who can contribute, take ownership, and help us scale our product and business. WHAT WE OFFER YOU A decisive role: You are part of our Data Science and Engineering team, developing our proprietary machine learning stack that sits at the core of our value generation for our clients. Every member of the team has a prominent voice and is encouraged to experiment, take risks and make suggestions that will have an impact on the business. What enables you to work at your best: Choose from free breakfast and drinks, a driven team to work, challenge, and celebrate with, transparency, and more. We also take a personal interest in your development and provide a budget for educational purposes as well as realistic options for career development within the company. A range of technologies: The Data Science team uses a range of tools depending on what is best suited for the problem: scikit-learn, Spark, Tensorflow, Databricks, XGBoost, etc. Our environment is built on AWS and we use various AWS services (ECS, S3, Redshift, Lambda, etc). We deploy applications using Docker images with CircleCi, and Jenkins pipelines run our machine learning algorithms. YOUR ROLE & RESPONSIBILITIES Devise ways using machine learning to improve our marketing and product performance to increase the quantity, relevance and quality of candidates that we bring to our clients, customize user experiences, and improve conversions Own a problem area, identifying ways to improve it and devising solutions Be comfortable sharing ideas and discussing different approaches in an environment where your opinion has a direct impact, being part of our international, experienced, and highly motivated team Be encouraged to work independently, using your conceptual and creative skills Be a scientific leader within Data Science, contributing to mentoring and developing of your colleagues. YOUR PROFILE 2+ years of experience using & developing machine-learning solutions to solve real-world business problems 3+ years of experience programming in Python and analysing data with it using packages like NumPy, SciPy, Pandas, and scikit-learn Proven ability to independently own data science projects end-to-end Previous exposure to algorithmic marketing is a plus Experience in statistically modelling processes or outcomes A creative problem-solver who is not afraid to try new things and challenge the status-quo Interested? We are on a strong growth path, so don’t miss the chance! If you are curious about the startup culture at HeyJobs, do take a look at our Kununu or Glassdoor ratings (average 4.85 - April 2019)! Verwandte Schlagwörter: Softwareentwickler/-in, Software Developer, , Software Developer, Software Development, Engineer, IT, Entwicklung, Entwickler, Entwicklerin, Programmierer, Programmiererin, development, developer, phyton NumPy, SciPy, Pandas, scikit-learn, machine-learning, programming, data science', 'Senior Data Scientist (f/m/d) full-time', '2019-06-03', 'HeyJobs GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4784, 'YOUR ROLE We are looking for an ambitious and talented Data Engineer who wants to leave its mark in the mobile gaming industry. The right candidate has a pragmatic approach to games and the drive to build an end-to-end analytics program from the ground up – including data infrastructure, architecture and process, combined with an entrepreneurial, hands-on mentality. In order to set you up for success, we provide everything you need within our dynamic and employee-centric company structure. You will work closely with the Data Scientist, whilst showing full responsibility and ownership of your project – you are the game! YOUR CONTRIBUTION Lead the design and execution of the development of our end-to-end analytics program Enable big data analytics by creating a system capable of ingesting, modifying and connecting data from disparate sources Build the infrastructure for an optimal ETL process that facilitates our business strategies Develop and implement effective, scalable, maintainable data engineering solutions Closely collaborate with data scientists and analysts YOUR PROFILE Hands-on experience in building large-scale, distributed data platforms and solutions Ability to understand business requirements and translate them into technical solutions Programming experience in analyzing and manipulating data – preferably in Python or Scala Strong experience working on clouds such as; AWS, Google Cloud, Microsoft Azure Experience working with data storage systems such as; HDFS, MongoDB, S3 Familiar with Spark, Storm or Hadoop Basic programming skills (Python, R, C#) Entrepreneurial mindset and high level of self-motivation YOUR FUTURE TEAM Provides a driven, agile and ambitious environment that meanwhile encourages you to be your authentic self Emphasizes the need for commercial thinking and pragmatic, data-driven decision making Believes in accountability, direct feedback and self-reliance as the foundation of our work', 'Data Engineer (M/F/X) // Popcore', '2019-06-03', 'Popcore', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4785, 'ABOUT THE TEAM -------------- Department: Sizing Algorithms Reports to: Data Science Lead Team Size: 10 Recruiter Name: Alicja Notowska ( alicja.notowska@zalando.de ) As a Senior Data Scientist you will engage directly in shaping the future of Machine Learning / Deep Learning solutions that will guide Zalando fashion retail customers in buying products that best match their unique size and fit. WHERE YOUR EXPERTISE IS NEEDED ------------------------------ Bring in your experience in developing Machine Learning and Deep Learning algorithmic based solutions and prototypes to help customers make sense out of confusing sizing systems Conduct focused experiments using new technologies to tackle the challenges Provide recommendations and predictions on customer size and fit choices Propose, build and lead initiatives from development to deployment WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR ---------------------------- Ph.D or equivalent experience in Machine Learning, Deep Learning, or Data Science Hands on training of RNNs, LSTMs, CNNs for real world problems Programming languages: Python, and its libraries such as pandas, numpy, scipy Hands on experience with DL frameworks: TensorFlow/Keras/Slim, Caffe, Caffe2/Pytorch Knowledge of ML frameworks such as Stan, PyMC, scikit-learn PERKS AT WORK ------------- Culture of trust, empowerment and constructive feedback, open source ( https://opensource.zalando.com/ ) commitment, meetups, game nights, 70+ internal technical and fun guilds, knowledge sharing through tech talks, internal tech academy and blogs ( https://jobs.zalando.com/tech/blog/ ), product demos, parties & events Competitive salary, employee share shop, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, centrally located offices, public transport discounts, municipality services, great IT equipment, flexible working times, additional holidays and volunteering time off, free beverages and fruits, diverse sports and health offerings Extensive onboarding, mentoring and personal development opportunities and an international team of experts Relocation assistance for internationals, PME family service and parent & child rooms* (*available in select locations) We celebrate diversity and are committed to building teams that represent a variety of backgrounds, perspectives and skills. All employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. ABOUT ZALANDO ------------- Zalando is Europe''s leading online platform for fashion, connecting customers, brands and partners across 17 markets. We drive digital solutions for fashion, logistics, advertising and research, bringing head-to-toe fashion to more than 23 million active customers through diverse skill-sets, interests and languages ( https://opensource.zalando.com/tech-radar/ ) our teams choose to use. At Zalando we deeply understand that Size Matters, and are excited to use our rare and huge article and customer data-sets to tackle this challenge using novel ML techniques. How about you; would you like to bring in your skills to craft a great experience for your family and friends when buying clothes and shoes online? You will join our multi-disciplinary Berlin based Sizing Team, composed of Machine Learning / Deep Learning researchers, engineers, and full stack developers from 10 different nationalities. Working together with Product Specialists, Designers and Fashion Specialists, you''ll participate in defining customer facing problem statements and the mathematical models and algorithms required to deliver solutions. You will be working on exciting real world problems with measurable short term and long term impact. You will get the chance to learn and follow the latest developments in the deep learning domain. You will be provided the opportunity to work with Zalando Research Lab with highly qualified scientists and researchers. Please note that all applications must be completed in English using the online form - we do not accept applications via e-mail.', 'Senior Data Scientist - Machine Learning &amp; DL', '2019-06-03', 'Zalando', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4786, 'Sie sind bereit für eine *wirklich* spannende Aufgabe und denken gern "outside the box"? Sie sind ein neugieriger Mensch und lieben neue Methoden und Technologien? Dann werden Sie eines Teams, das neue Maßstäbe setzt, innovative Denkansätze liefert und nachhaltiges Wachstum ermöglicht! Das sind Ihre konkreten Aufgaben: Einsatz von Data Science Methoden & Artificial Intelligence und die Erarbeitung und Umsetzung neuer KI Anwendungsfälle Business Innovation: Konzeption und Umsetzung innovativer, datengetriebener Geschäftsmodelle, Identifikation, Konzeption und Bewertung von industrie- und kundenspezifischen Use Cases Einsatz von Datenmodellierung und -analyse in allen Aspekten von Sales, Marketing, Operations und Geschäftsmodellinnovation Big Data & Analytics: Verknüpfung unterschiedlicher Datenquellen zu anspruchsvollen analytischen Lösungen Digital Transformation: Konzeption und Umsetzung von Unternehmenstransformation hin zu „Data Driven Business“ unter Einsatz digitaler Technologien strategische und fachliche Beratung der Kunden (Analyse, Konzepte) Ihre Qualifikation Sie verfügen über einen ausgezeichneten Studienabschluss mit naturwissenschaftlicher, mathematischer, wirtschaftlicher oder informationstechnologischer Ausrichtung und bringen Fachkenntnisse und Erfahrung in der Anwendung von Analysemethoden (statistische Modellierung, Data Mining, Machine Learning, AI, Text Mining, Datenvisualisierung oder sonstige relevante Kenntnisse) mit. Darüber hinaus zeichnen Sie sich durch diese Qualifikationen und Kenntnisse aus: praktische Erfahrung in der Anwendung von Data Science Methoden und AI z. B. zur Segmentierung, Kundenwertmodellierung, Kündigerprävention, Marketingoptimierung, Kampagnensteuerung, Pricing, Bild- und Spracherkennung, Betrugserkennung, Robotics & Chatbots sowie Echtzeitauswertungen fundierte Kenntnisse von Business Intelligence Tools und relevanten Statistik-Tools wie R, Python, SAS o.ä. eingehendes Verständnis von Datenstrukturen und Datenmanagement und herausragende Fähigkeiten in der Aufbereitung von Datenquellen konzeptionelle und analytische Denkweise strukturierter Arbeitsstil mit Freude am Lösen komplexer Aufgaben Spaß an der Kombination von technologischem Verständnis, strategischer Analyse und Umsetzungsarbeit hohe Zuverlässigkeit, ausgeprägter Teamgeist und sicheres Auftreten ausgeprägte Präsentations- und Moderationsfähigkeiten Deutschkenntnisse auf muttersprachlichem Niveau und Englisch in Wort und Schrift Reisebreitschaft innerhalb Deutschlands mit gelegentlichen Übernachtungen', 'Data Scientist (m/w/d)', '2019-06-03', 'xinonet', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4787, 'This Lead Data Science vacancy is based in Berlin with my client who develops mobile apps and software for different industry with a focus on UI/UX. This Lead Data Scientist vacancy would give you a chance to join a growing team and building on softer skills as well as technical. What can you expect? Primary responsibilities will be in developing practical machine learning applications and be involved in the entirety of the project life cycle. Eligible Lead Data Scientists will have a relevant degree such as Data Science, Machine Learning, Mathematics, Physics or similar and experience in most of the following; 1. Programming in Python and libraries (Pandas, Scikit-learn, keras), Java, Scala, Spark, Hadoop 2. Experience with Cloud environments 3. Experience in the Business development side and the ability to communicate to non technical people 4. Experience with a variety of different Machine Learning Algorithms If this sounds like you and you’re keen to find out more then please apply and contact Diogo Pereira, a Specialist Consultant at IC Resources. Even if you are unsure that you fulfil all of the criteria, please still apply as there may be similar roles we can recommend. The post Lead Data Scientist appeared first on IC Resources .', 'Lead Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'IC Resources', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4788, 'Senior Consultant - Data Scientist Insurance (m/w/d) MIT SCHARFSINN UND TEAMGEIST Berlin, Dortmund, Frankfurt am Main, Hamburg, Köln, München, Stuttgart, Essen, Aachen IHRE ROLLE - DAS WARTET AUF SIE Sie möchten unsere Kunden auf dem Weg in die Digitalisierung maßgeblich führen und sind der Schlüsselspieler zwischen der Fachabteilung und der IT. Sie identifizieren Einsatzmöglichkeiten künstlicher Intelligenz mit dem Ziel, die Geschäftsprozesse unserer Kunden zu verbessern oder NEU zu denken. Ihr Aufgabengebiet im Einzelnen beinhaltet weiterhin: Unterstützen unseres Vertrieb in konkreten Vertriebssituationen und Weiterentwickeln von UseCases der künstlichen Intelligenz in der Organisation Identifizieren von Einsatzmöglichkeiten und Potenzialen KI-basierter Konzepte, Lösungen und Technologien und Verbessern der Kernprozesse unserer Kunden Entwickeln von Geschäftsmodellen und innovativen Lösungen angereichert um Methoden der KI aus einer fachlichen Perspektive Schaffen eines maßgeblichen Mehrwert für unsere Kunden Entwickeln von KI-basierten Lösungsvorschlägen auf der Grundlage fachlicher Anforderungen unter Berücksichtigung von Chancen und Risiken sowie Kosten-/Nutzenaspekten innerhalb der Rahmenbedingungen unserer Kunden Konzeptionieren und Gestalten von Architekturen und Anwendungsprototypen Prozessberatung in klassischen IT-Themen In unseren Teams denken und handeln adessi interdisziplinär, lösungsorientiert und gehen gemeinsam mit unseren Kunden voran. Wir wissen - diese Aufgaben lassen sich nur mit offenem Erfahrungsaustausch, gegenseitiger Unterstützung, kontinuierlicher Weiterbildung und gut ausgestattet erfüllen. Rund 500 Consultants bei adesso und über 120 Schulungen – bspw. zum Management von IT-Projekten nach PRINCE2 oder agile Coach – sowie Smartphone und Laptop ihrer Wahl warten ab Tag 1 auf Sie! IHRE SKILLS – DAS BRINGEN SIE MIT Überdurchschnittlich gut abgeschlossenes Studium der (Wirtschafts-)Informatik oder Mathematik oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation Fundiertes Übersichtswissen über aktuelle Trends, Konzepte und Technologien im Bereich künstliche Intelligenz (Wissensrepräsentation, Reasoning, Maschinelles Lernen, Natural Language Processing, Textmining, Informationsextraktion) und deren Anwendungen Erste Erfahrungen mit KI-Frameworks und deren Integration in komplexe IT-Landschaften sowie mit technischen Plattformen etablierter Player, wie IBM Watson, Google Cloud Machine Learning Engine, Microsoft Azure Machine Learning, Amazon Rekognition / Machine Learning Gute Kenntnisse in der Modellierung komplexer Sachverhalte Hervorragende analytische Fähigkeiten, strukturiertes Vorgehen, schnelle Auffassungsgabe, hohe Leistungsmotivation und Engagement – gepaart mit Witz, Kreativität und gesundem Menschenverstand Echter Teamplayer, der souverän kommuniziert, überzeugend auftritt und kundenorientiert agiert Vorteilhaft sind praktische Erfahrungen im Bereich der Konzepterstellung und Spezifikation im Versicherungssektor Projektbezogene Reisebereitschaft innerhalb Deutschlands CHANCENGEBER – WAS ADESSO AUSMACHT Wir gehören für Einsteiger und Professionals zu den Top-Adressen in der IT-Welt. In unseren interdisziplinären Teams bringen wir unsere Technologie und Beratungskompetenz mit der Branchenexpertise der Menschen zusammen. Kontinuierlicher Austausch, Teamgeist und ein respektvoller sowie anerkennender Umgang sorgen für ein Arbeitsklima, das verbindet. So belegen wir nach 2016 auch in 2018 erneut den 1. Platz beim Wettbewerb „Deutschlands Beste Arbeitgeber in der ITK“! Wir eröffnen Entwicklungs- und Führungsmöglichkeiten – unser Versprechen, ein Chancengeber zu sein, nehmen wir ernst. Egal ob Sie eher die Fach- oder Führungslaufbahn anstreben – unsere transparenten Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten bspw. zum Managing/ Principal Consultant oder agile Coach sorgen dafür, dass Ihre Entwicklung bei uns nicht still steht Sie sind offen für neue und anspruchsvolle Aufgaben? Dann senden Sie uns Ihre aussagekräftigen Bewerbungsunterlagen inklusive der Angabe Ihrer Gehaltsvorstellung sowie des frühestmöglichen Eintrittstermins vorzugsweise über unser Webformular. Kontakt: adesso AG Olivia Slotta Adessoplatz 1 44269 Dortmund T +49 231 7000-7100', 'Senior Consultant - Data Scientist Insurance (w/m/d)', '2019-06-03', 'adesso AG', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4789, 'My client are an A.I. driven financial services platform based in Berlin with huge investment potential and a pan European reach who are looking for a Data Scientist to assist both the Lead Data Scientist and Chief Risk officer in deriving risk insights from Data for implementation into their investment platforms. Responsibilities: Perform data interpretation and presentation of highly accurate data. Work collaboratively cross-functionally delivering various risk and performance measures. Take ownership of tasks and projects from POC stage to implementation. Work closely with data team to enhance quality and drive forward risk model techniques. Requirements: Masters degree or higher (Mathematics, Statistics, Business informatics, Finance or Economics) Strong analytical skills and ability to manage large amounts of data from various sources. Knowledge of extraction tools (SQL, R, Qlik or similar) Financial services background and risk experience would be beneficial. If you''re a Data analyst who is looking for that next step in their career working for one of the most forward thinking A.I. financial services get in touch at Daniel.Neaves@darwinrecruitment.com with your CV and a suitable time to speak.', 'Data Analyst', '2019-06-03', 'Darwin Recruitment', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4790, 'The Leibniz-Forschungsinstitut für Molekulare Pharmakologie (FMP) belongs to the „Forschungsverbund Berlin e. V. (FVB)“. The FVB is an institution of eight natural sciences research institutes in Berlin funded by the Federal Republic of Germany and the association of its federal states. The research institutes are members of the Leibniz association. The Leibniz-Forschungsinstitut für Molekulare Pharmakologie (FMP) is a non-university academic research organisation dedicated to basic biomedical research and is located at the Research Campus Berlin Buch in close vicinity to the Max Delbrück Center for Molecular Medicine and the Charité Experimental and Clinical Research Center. The research group of mass spectrometry and proteomics (led by Dr. Fan Liu) offers positions for PhD students and Post-doctoral researchers in biochemistry and informatics (m/f) (Ref. 36/2018) starting January 2019 or later. The positions are initially limited to 3 years for PhD students and 1 year for Postdocs with the potential of extension. Job description: Our group is interested in developing and applying tools to characterize the complexity of protein interactions within the cell. We use multi-disciplinary approaches that combines proteomics, cross-linking mass spectrometry, molecular biology, structural biology and bioinformatics to investigate the organizational aspects of protein assemblies and their biological consequences in various organelles. For this position, we are particularly looking for a informatician who is interested in large-scale data analysis in the direction of computational proteomics/interactomics. In addition, opportunities are also available in developing software packages with industrial corporations. For further information, please visit www.leibniz-fmp.de/liu. Requirements: We are looking for a highly motivated, responsible, reliable, and flexible scientist that works well independently as well as with others. Candidates with a strong interest in biochemistry, informatics and/or mass spectrometry techniques are especially encouraged to apply. A good command of the English language and a high personal motivation to excel in science are required. For PhD students, the candidate should have a master degree in chemistry, biochemistry or relevant fields.For Postdocs, the candidate should have a PhD degree in analytical chemistry, biochemistry or relevant fields. He/she should have strong expertise in programming, preferably also with basic knowledge in mass spectrometry. For more information please contact: Dr. Fan Liu; e-mail: fliu@fmp-berlin.de phone: +49 (0)30 94793 141 Homepage FMP: http://www.fmp-berlin.de/liu Salaries will be based on TVöD (Bund). In 2013 the institute has been awarded the certificate of the audit Beruf und Familie as family-friendly employer. We offer equal opportunities regardless of gender and welcome applications of disabled candidates. They will be preferred in case of equal qualification. Please upload complete application documents only as a single merged PDF-file including CV, copies of degree certificates and the names and contact informations of two referees before December 15th, 2018 via the FMP`s online job application facility (button “Apply online”). Failing to submit the materials as a single PDF results in immediate exclusion from the competition. We are looking forward to your application!', 'PhD students and Post-doctoral researchers in biochemistry and informatics (m/f)', '2019-06-03', 'Leibniz-Forschungsinstitut für Molekulare Pharmakologie', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4791, 'ABOUT THE TEAM Department: Supply & Demand Reports to: Engineering Lead Team Size: < 8 Pricing & Forecasting is at the core of our commercial operation. Our tools help to determine how much of each product to buy, to recommend the best prices for these products, and to ensure that we have the right level of logistics capacity to fulfill our customers demand. The Pricing and Forecasting team uses cutting edge technology, data science and machine learning to forecast demand and pricing with a focus on business and customer experience. Partnerships happen with the machine learning research team, all key engineering and product teams, business and customer experience teams. As a Senior Data Scientist working on Dynamic Pricing topics in the Pricing & Forecasting team, you will analyse our inventory and our customers'' recent orders in order to model future shopping behaviour and find out what our customers are willing to pay in real-time. You will help us set prices which reflect our current product offering, enabling us to protect our revenues by making smarter pricing decisions. Your work will be of great business influence, linearly linked to the bottom-line results of Zalando. WHERE YOUR EXPERTISE IS NEEDED Help us take control of Pricing to ensure a competitive market position and maximum growth for our company Build Machine Learning models that control the prices for more than 300,000 items we sell online across different markets Query, analyse and facilitate data, setting up monitoring and data quality assurance Collaborate with engineers to translate Machine Learning prototypes into production systems WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR Excellent educational background (minimum M.Sc) in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics or other similar quantitative field Solid industry experience with Python, Machine Learning related libraries such as pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow, Keras, and big data frameworks such as Spark Foundational understanding of statistics and machine learning from simple regressions to neural networks ( LSTM, Transformers), with an understanding of using right approaches. Practical/real world experiences within Dynamic Pricing, Perishable Inventory, Supply Chain/Logistics, Retail or the Airline/Aviation industry would be desirable. We celebrate diversity and are committed to building teams that represent a variety of backgrounds, perspectives and skills. All employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. ABOUT ZALANDO Zalando is Europe''s leading online platform for fashion and lifestyle, connecting customers, brands and partners across 17 markets. We drive digital solutions for fashion, logistics, advertising and research, bringing head-to-toe fashion to more than 23 million active customers through diverse skill-sets, interests andlanguages ( https://opensource.zalando.com/tech-radar/ ) our teams choose to use.', 'Senior Data Scientist - Dynamic Pricing', '2019-06-03', 'Zalando', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4792, 'ABOUT THE TEAM -------------- Department: Personalized Marketing Reports to: Head of Engineering & Data Science Team Size: 5-10 Recruiter Name: Alicja Notowska ( alicja.notowska@zalando.de ) You will join the team responsible for the data and AI driven future of Zalando''s marketing activities. We build Europe''s smartest Machine Learning platform for best-in-class marketing execution throughout all paid marketing platforms. WHERE YOUR EXPERTISE IS NEEDED ------------------------------ Take our marketing to the next level by matching the right customer with the right advertisement on a large scale fully driven by technology and AI Create a holistic system of integrated machine learning algorithms to predict campaign success and optimize ROI of our >100m€ annual ad budget Co-locate with our software developers and data engineers to create highly personalised marketing campaigns for example via Deep Learning Image Processing Leverage 1000+ Zalando data sources, APIs from 100+ other Zalando tech teams and ad platform APIs such as Google and Facebook WHAT WE''RE LOOKING FOR ---------------------------- M.Sc or PhD (or comparative experience) in Statistics, Computer Science, Mathematics or other similar quantitative field Deep understanding of Machine Learning methods and/or Statistical Modeling, applied in a commercial context. Eagerness to broaden your area of expertise Experience with bringing Machine Learning models into production and fluency in Python Hands-on experience with large real-world data sets in a big data environment PERKS AT WORK ------------- Culture of trust, empowerment and constructive feedback, open source ( https://opensource.zalando.com/ ) commitment, meetups, game nights, 70+ internal technical and fun guilds, knowledge sharing through tech talks, internal tech academy and blogs ( https://jobs.zalando.com/tech/blog/ ), product demos, parties & events Competitive salary, employee share shop, 40% Zalando shopping discount, discounts from external partners, centrally located offices, public transport discounts, municipality services, great IT equipment, flexible working times, additional holidays and volunteering time off, free beverages and fruits, diverse sports and health offerings Extensive onboarding, mentoring and personal development opportunities and an international team of experts Relocation assistance for internationals, PME family service and parent & child rooms* (*available in select locations) We celebrate diversity and are committed to building teams that represent a variety of backgrounds, perspectives and skills. All employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. ABOUT ZALANDO ------------- Zalando is Europe''s leading online platform for fashion, connecting customers, brands and partners across 17 markets. We drive digital solutions for fashion, logistics, advertising and research, bringing head-to-toe fashion to more than 23 million active customers through diverse skill-sets, interests and languages ( https://opensource.zalando.com/tech-radar/ ) our teams choose to use. Personalized Marketing is a passionate and agile team. With all roles and tech in one unit we act like a startup while scaling big. We have full ownership to allocate over 10M€ marketing budget per developer/scientist every year. In agile cross functional teams with engineers and marketing experts your models go live and scale fast. For this we run our own dedicated state-of-the-art AI tech stack (see "RulesofPlay(https://github.com/lmineiro/zalando-rules-of-play)") and at the same time enjoy access to thousands of Zalando internal APIs and data sets. Never walk alone. Boost your expertise through our Data Science guild, and collaboration with other Machine Learning teams across Zalando. Please note that all applications must be completed in English using the online form - we do not accept applications via e-mail.', '(Senior) Data Scientist - Personalized Marketing', '2019-06-03', 'Zalando', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4793, 'A PhD in Computer Vision, Robot Vision or a related discipline Broad knowledge of fundamentals and the state of the art in relevant areas of Computer Vision/Machine Learning/Robotics/Artificial Intelligence/Data Science/Deep Learning Three years of post-doctoral experience in either industry or academia A strong track record of publications at major Computer Vision and related conferences (e.g. CVPR, ICCV/ECCV, RSS, NeurIPS, ICRA, IROS, CoRL) or journals (IEEE T-PAMI, IJCV, CVIU, IJRR, IEEE TRO, JMLR) Outstanding coding skills in two or more programming languages such as Python and C/C++ Hands-on experience in Computer Vision and Machine Learning Excellent verbal and written communication skills Excellent problem solving ability Deep Learning implementation expertise (MxNet, TensorFlow, PyTorch etc) Do you want to develop Computer Vision and Machine Learning to create Robotic solutions with a worldwide impact? Amazon has the world''s most exciting treasure trove of robotic challenges. The Robotics AI team at Amazon is building high-performance, real-time robotic systems that can perceive, learn and act intelligently alongside humans, at Amazon scale. We are looking for an experienced Computer Vision Scientist capable of building and delivering robust perception systems for object understanding, to support robotic manipulation. You will join the European center for Robotics AI, which is based in Berlin, Germany. We work on computer vision, machine learning, deep learning, planning, control and simulation applied to robotics. You will be closely collaborating with scientists across all these disciplines. We are expanding to meet the huge application demand at Amazon. If you are excited to push the state of the art and to solve some of the most challenging real-world problems and if you would like to live in one of the world''s most exciting cities, then we have the perfect role for you. We are particularly excited to receive applications from candidates with specialisms in an area close to some of the following: object recognition (instance and categorical), 3D surface modeling and reconstruction, 3D pose estimation, multi-view stereo, structure from motion, object tracking, 2D/3D deformable modelling, segmentation (both semantic and instance based) or deep learning approaches to robot manipulation. We seek candidates who can: Research, design, implement and evaluate novel algorithms for robotic vision Collaborate closely with team members on developing systems from prototyping to production level Collaborate with teams spread all over the world, in particular Boston and Seattle Work closely with software engineering teams to drive Amazon scale, real-time implementations Be driven by business goals Amazon’s goal is to be the most customer-centric company in the world. To get there, we need exceptionally talented, bright, and goal-driven people. If you''re excited to be part of one of the world''s largest automation systems, this is your chance to make history. Experience in Robotics Experience with Cloud Computing and Services such as AWS 3+ years of experience in Python', 'Senior Applied Scientist, Computer Vision', '2019-06-03', 'Amazon Development Center DEU', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4794, 'At HelloFresh, our mission is to change the way people eat - forever. From our 2011 founding in Europe''s vibrant tech hub Berlin, we''ve become the global market leader in the meal kit sector and inspire millions of energised home cooks across the globe every week. We offer our meal kit boxes full of exciting recipes and thoughtfully sourced, fresh ingredients in more than 10 countries, operating from offices in Berlin, New York City, Sydney, Toronto, London and Amsterdam. Our more than 4,000 employees are the heart and soul of our highly international, fast-paced, and dynamic environment where innovation and smart, fast action is encouraged. Our Engineering, Data, Product and Security teams are located in Berlin and New York and are critical to what we do. From procurement tools, to conversion rate optimization, live pricing tools, payment services and add-on upselling features, we work on challenging problems and have a high output of building and releasing features and engines that make our business thrive and deliver real financial impact. You can get a taste of what we''ve been working on by checking out our tech blog ( https://engineering.hellofresh.com/ ). ------------- About the job ------------- Leading a goal-oriented team that delivers customer value early and often, diligently measuring results. Playing a key role in ensuring the ongoing alignment of our technology with the overall business strategy for the company. Hiring, inspiring, managing, and growing a cross-functional data science team, ensuring every Data Scientist and Machine Learning Engineer has adequate growth opportunities. Setting and ensuring the high standards for quality, scalability and customer focus. Working effectively with Product, Marketing, and Operations counterparts towards a common goal of delivering great experiences to our customers. Collaborating with cross-functional teams to discover innovative ways of leveraging vast repositories of user generated data. ---------------------- Who we are looking for ---------------------- Significant experience within technical and people management, leading both Data Scientists and Machine Learning Engineers. Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, ability to build effective communication structures in a fast growing engineering organization Exceptional technical background, demonstrated in past leadership roles with a clear impact towards achieving business goals. Demonstrable past experience with Agile methodologies, with a strong focus on data-driven experimentation, lean thinking and quick iterations Coached and mentored Data Scientists and Machine Learning Engineers in their careers. A self-organized individual, with excellent focus and prioritization of workload using business data and metrics. A strong understanding of the state of the art in machine learning methods and in depth techniques for practical application. Background working with Python and knowledge of data libraries as sklearn and pandas. ------------- What we offer ------------- Relocation assistance to move to Berlin and visa application support Competitive compensation Significant reduction on our meal kits Annual learning and development budget to attend conferences or purchase educational resources Sabbatical policy Work in our office located in the heart of Berlin A diverse and vibrant international environment A range of perks (Free in-house crash course in German, compensation for advanced German classes, in-house lecture series and knowledge sharing programme, discounts for our neighboring gym & Urban Sports Club, free weekly yoga classes, summer & winter parties, discount on our HelloFresh GO vending machines) The chance to have a significant impact on one of the fastest-growing technology companies in Europe in an exciting growth phase --------------------------- Are you up for a challenge? --------------------------- Please submit your complete application below including your salary expectations and earliest starting date.', 'Data Science Manager (m/f/x)', '2019-06-03', 'HelloFresh', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4795, 'Making an impact that matters. Unser Anspruch ist, jeden Tag das zu tun, was wirklich zählt. Mit unserem breiten Leistungsspektrum – von Audit über Tax & Legal bis Financial Advisory und Consulting – unterstützen wir Kunden auf einzigartige Weise. Wir setzen neue Maßstäbe, liefern innovative Denkansätze und ermöglichen nachhaltiges Wachstum. Wir fördern unsere hochqualifizierten Mitarbeiter mit ihren verschiedensten Talenten, sodass sie mit uns mehr erreichen. In unserem Deloitte Analytics Institute arbeiten wir in einem cross-funktionalen Expertenteam mit Kooperationspartnern aus Forschung, Wirtschaft und führenden Vendoren an innovativen und maßgeschneiderten Analytics-Lösungen für unsere namhaften Kunden. Für unser Team an den Standorten Berlin, Düsseldorf, Hamburg, Hannover, Frankfurt, Stuttgart und München suchen wir engagierte Verstärkung. Spannende Aufgaben erwarten Sie Identifikation und Entwicklung innovativer Ansätze im Bereich Big Data und Advanced Analytics im DAX30-Umfeld mit Start-up Atmosphäre Gewinnung und Validierung von Erkenntnissen aus großen Mengen strukturierter und unstrukturierter Daten unter Anwendung von Data-Mining- und Machine-Learning-Techniken Durchführung von Kundenpräsentationen, Workshops, Expertenrunden und Meetings Eigenständige Übernahme von (Teil-) Projekten von der Entwurfsphase (inkl. Prototyping) über die Entwicklung bis hin zu einer produktiven Nutzung Darin sind Sie Spezialist Erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Bachelor- bzw. Masterstudium in (Wirtschafts-) Informatik, Betriebswirtschaftslehre, Mathematik, Physik oder Statistik PhD und/oder mehrjährige Berufserfahrung in einem daten- und modellintensiven Bereich (z.B. Machine Learning, Data Mining, (Computational) Statistics, Optimierung, Computer Vision) Fundierte Kenntnisse im Bereich Statistik, Datenanalyse und –modellierung, der notwendigen Sprachen (z.B. R, Python, MATLAB, SAS, SPSS) und Frameworks (z.B. Stan, Pandas, Scikit-learn, H2O, Spark ML, Theano) Idealerweise Erfahrung in den folgenden Bereichen Datenvisualisierung / Dashboarding (z.B. Tableau, QlikView, D3) Probabilistic Programming Deep Learning Big-Data-Frameworks (Hadoop, Spark, Spark Streaming, Flink) Sichere Kenntnisse in einer oder mehreren Programmier- und Skriptsprachen wie z. B. Java, Scala, Python, C++, C#, JavaScript Reisebereitschaft sowie sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse Was Sie von uns erwarten können Neben einem sicheren Arbeitsplatz in einer angenehmen, kollegialen Atmosphäre bieten wir Ihnen ein chancenreiches, internationales Arbeitsumfeld. Hier warten vielfältige Projekte bei Kunden unterschiedlicher Branchen auf Sie. Bei uns gelten flache Hierarchien und ein Prinzip der offenen Tür. Ein weiterer Pluspunkt: Mit der Deloitte University verfolgen wir einen einzigartigen innovativen Ansatz für Ihre Weiterentwicklung. Durch ein für Sie maßgeschneidertes World Class Curriculum stellen wir sicher, dass Sie über das Know-how und die Qualifikation verfügen, um für unsere Kunden die besten Lösungen zu entwickeln. Sie sind interessiert? Wir freuen uns auf Sie', 'Senior Consultant (m/w) Consulting - Data Scientist Analytics', '2019-06-03', 'Deloitte', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4796, 'THE COMPANY Leading open audio platform active in enabling music and other audio content provision and community development is looking for a Senior Data Scientist with a focus on Anti -Fraud, -Spam and -Abuse to identify sources of abuse and use advanced statistics and machine learning to mitigate risks and provide end-to-end solutions with a creative mindset and open attitude. THE ROLE This exciting opportunity as a hands-on Senior Data Scientist will have you working on projects such as fraud analysis and prevention, time series anomaly detection as well as bot detection and defining sources of abuse. Generating pragmatic solutions based on ML and statistics, prototyping them and deploying them to production make this role an end-to-end solution provider in data-based fraud prevention. As an embedded resource within the engineering teams you will have a great and direct impact on the experience of millions of users daily. You also act as consultant and provide guidance to the business when it comes to providing growth-ready machine learning solutions for abuse prediction, detection and prevention. YOUR SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE Experience in a production environment as a data scientist, ideally in Anti-Abuse function, within a commercial environment Good understanding of Project Lifecycle Management in Data Science and experience in research & development of solutions and model tuning and inspection Knowledge of and exposure to programming languages such as Python and Scala Exposure to relevant tools to write/maintain large data processing pipelines with Hadoop, Spark, BigQuery, Redshift, among others Collaborative team player with experience to advise, guide and align various stakeholders and functional partners such as engineers, product managers and peers Good communication skills and ability to present insights and discoveries about data and patterns to peers as well as non-technical management and cross-functional stakeholders Fluent communication skills in English HOW TO APPLY Please register your interest by sending your CV to Peter Schroeter via the Apply link on this page.', 'Senior Data Scientist Anti-Fraud (m/f/d)', '2019-06-03', 'Harnham', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4797, 'My client, is a global data & analytics consultancy with a key focus on deriving solutions in the broad fields of Business Intelligence, Data Analytics, Artificial Intelligence and driving business performance. They''re data setup is diversified, scaling heavily across the Engineering, Analytics and Data Science space. As part of the next phase of their growth they''re looking to grow and scale the Data Science team to work in tandem with their Engineering/Data Analytics teams to offer a consolidated solutions to their clients across various industries (Finance, Automotive, Travel and more). Responsibilities: Develop and implement predictive models to help customers derive insights from their data. Integrate data from various analytical sources (Sensor Data, Google Analytics, CRM). Support data pipelines and provide support for Data architectures. Deliver project management activities - Creating project expense estimates, projects and resource planning. Manage and cleanse data making sure of the validity and quality for varying client requirements. Develop new Data science use cases whilst in collaboration with stakeholders and various business units. Provide collaboration with Data Scientists and Engineering teams enabling Machine Learning and advanced analytics projects. Requirements: Masters of PhD degree in informatics, Computer Science, or related fields. Passionate about building analytics solutions and working closely with customers. Deep knowledge and understanding of the development of algorithms and data structures. Background in implementing cloud platforms (Microsoft Azure, AWS). Deep technical knowledge in Microsoft SQL, Power BI, SQL, DWH, DataLake or similar technologies. Understanding and ability to work in a team, management skills and ability to liaise with stakeholders. Theoretical and practical experience in Machine Learning, Data mining, Data Science. German and English speaking. Willingness to travel regularly, usually 40% or less. If you''re working as a Data Scientist looking for that next step up, working on state of the art technologies across various industries and providing bespoke solutions to all types of companies do get in touch at Daniel.Neaves@darwinrecruitment.com along with your CV and a suitable time to speak.', 'Data Science Consultant', '2019-06-03', 'Darwin Recruitment', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4798, 'This Senior Data Scientist vacancy is based in Berlin, Germany with my client who develops software platforms for the business side of the advertising industry. This opportunity also allows you the ability to grown into a team lead positions if the right work ethic and motivations are shown in the first year with the company. What can you expect? You will be working alongside two other Data Scientists and your primary responsibilities will be in; 1. Using analytical, statistical and database skills to generate reports, analyses and insights from large, complex data sets, aiming to increase advertising efficiency 2. Develop algorithms for automated decision making around campaign & targeting setup, budget allocation, real-time bidding and performance optimisation Eligible Senior Data Scientists will have a relevant degree such as Mathematics, Computer Science or related discipline, and experience in most of the following; 1. 5+ years of commercial experience 2. Excellent programming in Python and Java or Scala is a plus 3. Knowledge of Big Data especially either Spark or Hadoop 4. Problem-solving ability to optimise algorithms 5. worked with Statistical methods before (classification/prediction models) If this sounds like you and you’re keen to find out more then please apply and contact Diogo Pereira, Specialist Consultant at IC Resources. Even if you are unsure that you fulfil all of the criteria, please still apply as there may be similar roles we can recommend. The post Senior Data Scientist appeared first on IC Resources .', 'Senior Data Scientist', '2019-06-03', 'IC Resources', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4799, 'Job Description As part of the Commercial / Marketing team based in our Berlin office, you will be working in a fast paced, multinational team where you will be speaking with scientists, both in research, biotechnology and the clinical arena, understanding their projects and plans, and exploring how Illumina’s market leading technology can really help in their lab. Identifying those customers who are genuinely interested, you will be using your communication skills as well as learning how our marketing projects can support the business across Europe If you want to move into the Commercial field we offer a genuine career development platform where you can expand your skills and experience and build a career with one of life sciences fastest growing companies.. Basic Function and Scope of the Position: Responsible for the qualification and development of marketing- and sales-generated leads. Focused on prospecting, response rate to marketing programs output, lead qualification and creation of high quality leads. Includes engaging with existing customers and qualified sales leads, guiding customers to the Illumina products that best meet their needs, and coordinating with internal resources to address customer questions/objections. Works closely with both inside and field sales representatives to meet and exceed sales quotas for a specific product line and/or sales territory. Tasks and Responsibilities: Ensures a high level of liaison with other departments & staff to ensure co-ordination of activities. Executes on and provides regular reports on results of lead generation projects and activities. Represents the company professionally, ethically and morally at all times. Makes outbound contact to existing and prospective customers to identify sales opportunities, promote relevant marketing/sales promotional programs and initiate the sales process. Responsible for entering and maintaining lead data into our customer relationship management database. All listed tasks and responsibilities are deemed as essential functions to this position; however, business conditions may require reasonable accommodations for additional task and responsibilities Preferred Educational Background: Bachelor’s degree or equivalent required. Business, science or technical degree strongly preferred. Chemistry or molecular biology degree a plus. Preferred Experiential Background: No prior sales experience required, but this would be advantageous. Fluency in Second European Language such as German would be useful. Genetic analysis sales experience and/or familiarity with the Illumina product line a plus. Demonstrated ability to quickly grasp and master highly technical concepts and articulate them well to others. Outstanding listening, verbal and written communication skills. Strong interpersonal skills with the ability to communicate effectively with a wide range of customer personality types. Ability to interact well with highly educated research scientist customers. Strong ability to identify customer needs, obstacles to the sales process and solutions using Illumina products & services. Proficient with Microsoft Office (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint). Experience working with SalesForce.com or a similar CRM database a plus. Team goal oriented with a focus on achieving team sales performance metrics. Efficient time management skills with the ability to stay focused on primary business objectives in a fast-paced, dynamic environment. INDHP Illumina believes that everyone has the ability to make an impact, and we are proud to be an equal opportunities employer committed to providing employment opportunity regardless of sex, race, creed, color, gender, religion, marital status, domestic partner status, age, national origin or ancestry, physical or mental disability, medical condition, sexual orientation, pregnancy, military or veteran status, citizenship status, and genetic information.', 'Commercial Lead Generation Specialist , DACH region', '2019-06-03', 'Illumina', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4800, 'My client are an advanced stealth mode ventures backed by one of the largest management consultancies who are in the process of developing AI based SaaS solution to support credit analysts and risk assessments. They''re looking for a Senior Data Scientist Risk expert to come onboard and drive the credit risk modelling projects to springboard the company from stealth mode to production. Responsibilities: Develop and implement Machine Learning and Data mining technologies within the domain of credit risk modelling. Validate and utilise Machine Learning and data mining technologies using real-time credit risk data. Drive forward state of the art tools and methods for quantitative data and translate into product and services. Organise and validate knowledge from large amounts of structured/unstructured data using random forest, gradient boosting, deep learning and non-linear regression. Work in coordination with product team and other business units. Requirements: Masters degree in statistics, Economics, Econometrics, Computer Science or related quantitative studies. 3 years professional experience working with quant data analysis or equivalent PhD. Deep knowledge of building and validating credit rating models in a Bank, rating agency or asset management practice. Detailed knowledge of Machine Learning methods, random forests, gradient boosting, deep learning, non-linear regression approaches. Strong skills in SQL, Data Analysis and model prototyping. R & Python knowledge. If you''re a Data Scientist who is looking for the challenge to be a technical lead and drive forward quantitative analytics projects in an innovative venture please get in touch at Daniel.Neaves@darwinrecruitment.com with your CV and a convenient time to speak.', 'Senior Data Scientist/Risk Analyst', '2019-06-03', 'Darwin Recruitment', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4801, 'Basic qualifications Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or related field Good analytical and problem solving skills Experience in data structures, algorithm design, complexity analysis, object-oriented design 5+ years of professional experience in software development Proficiency in at least one modern programming language such as Java, Scala, Python, C++, C# External job description AWS SageMaker is looking for you – a Senior Software Development Engineer interested in automating machine learning (ML) and empowering the world to do more with it. Our team is building a platform to enable Scientists and Software Developers to design, build, train and tune ML models quicker and easier. Our product consists of APIs, SDKs, AWS Console UI, a growing library of ML algorithms and a highly available platform capable of hosting and automatically tuning customer''s ML models. We develop and run secure, highly available, robust and reliable distributed systems using latest technologies. You will work in close collaboration with scientist, building tools for experimentation at scale and work with your team-mates to turn end-to-end platform features into reality following best engineering practices. Responsibilities In this highly visible position you will have possibility to directly influence technical decisions as well as our business strategy. You will be building tools for large scale ML experiments You will be driving engineering best practices and mentoring junior engineers. You will lead architecture and engineering design decisions. You will be part of a R&D team that delivers state-of-the-art solutions to democratize ML and DL If this sounds exciting, then come and join our team where you will be experimenting, designing, implementing and shipping new and exciting ML platform features. Master''s degree in Computer Science, Computer or Electrical Engineering Experience in professional software engineering practices & best practices for the full software development life cycle, including coding standards, code reviews, source control management, build processes, testing, and operations Proven ability to take a project from scoping requirements through actual launch of the project Experience with building complex software systems that have been successfully delivered to customers Experience with Machine Learning, data mining, and/or statistical analysis tools Experience in communicating with users, other technical teams and senior management to collect requirements, describe software product features and technical designs Experience in mentoring junior software engineers to improve their skills, and make them more effective, product software engineers', 'Software Development Engineer', '2019-06-03', 'Amazon Development Center DEU', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4802, 'Requisition ID: 210369 Work Area: Software-Research Location: Berlin Expected Travel: 0 - 20% Career Status: Professional Employment Type: Regular Full Time COMPANY DESCRIPTION SAP started in 1972 as a team of five colleagues with a desire to do something new. Together, they changed enterprise software and reinvented how business was done. Today, as a market leader in enterprise application software, we remain true to our roots. That’s why we engineer solutions to fuel innovation, foster equality and spread opportunity for our employees and customers across borders and cultures. SAP values the entrepreneurial spirit, fostering creativity and building lasting relationships with our employees. We know that a diverse and inclusive workforce keeps us competitive and provides opportunities for all. We believe that together we can transform industries, grow economics, lift up societies and sustain our environment. Because it’s the best-run businesses that make the world run better and improve people’s lives. PURPOSE AND OBJECTIVES Technology & Innovation (T&I) is responsible for SAP’s overall platform and technology development such as SAP Cloud Platform and SAP HANA. In addition, T&I drives the incubation and adoption of intelligent technologies like Analytics, SAP Leonardo Machine Learning and IoT across SAP’s product portfolio. The T&I board area is also in charge of SAP’s global innovation agenda and builds new business model- and market driven innovations to help customers realize the most business value. SAP Leonardo Machine Learning is part of SAP’s intelligent technologies portfolio and one of the key drivers of the Intelligent Enterprise. It is our mission to infuse all enterprise applications with machine learning and to empower our customers to make the most of their business data. Our team is located in Germany, France, Israel, Singapore, India, and the US and exemplifies a start-up like, innovative work environment. Our ML Research team is a small and physically co-located team of deep learning experts. Here, at SAP, we have a unique task to bridge the gap between SAP machine learning product teams and academic research. To that end we work with top-tier universities around the world and push the state of the art in machine learning research in areas which have the potential to influence the SAP machine learning products in the future. We are an extremely competitive, highly ethical team that strives for excellence in research. EXPECTATIONS AND TASKS Push the state of the art in Machine Learning/Deep Learning via publications at top conferences Align results of your research with machine learning related problems in SAP product world Communicate and showcase results of your research to SAP executives and clients Whatever else it takes: we are a lean startup inside a corporate environment EDUCATION AND QUALIFICATIONS / SKILLS AND COMPETENCIES Required PhD in Computer Science or related field, with a very strong focus on machine learning Publications at top-tier conferences such as NIPS, CVPR, ICLR, ACL Strong academic network and proven track record of mentoring of Master students Ability to write research grade code in Python and run large scale experiments on AWS Experience with Deep Learning software packages such as TensorFlow or (Py)Torch Collaborative mindset and excellent written and oral communication skills in English Preferred Strong experience in Natural Language Processing with publication background therein Excellent work ethics and self-organization in a dynamic and fast-paced environment Contributions to open-source research communities Optional GPU programming proficiency with languages such as CUDA, OpenCL (Very) Good German language skills WHAT YOU GET FROM US Success is what you make it. At SAP, we help you make it your own. A career at SAP can open many doors for you. If you’re searching for a company that’s dedicated to your ideas and individual growth, recognizes you for your unique contributions, fills you with a strong sense of purpose, and provides a fun, flexible and inclusive work environment – apply now. SAP''S DIVERSITY COMMITMENT To harness the power of innovation, SAP invests in the development of its diverse employees. We aspire to leverage the qualities and appreciate the unique competencies that each person brings to the company. SAP is committed to the principles of Equal Employment Opportunity and to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team (Americas: Careers.NorthAmerica@sap.com or Careers.LatinAmerica@sap.com, APJ: Careers.APJ@sap.com, EMEA: Careers@sap.com). Successful candidates might be required to undergo a background verification with an external vendor. Additional Locations:', '(Senior) Research Scientist / (Senior) Researcher for SAP Machine Learning Research', '2019-06-03', 'SAP', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4803, 'Ihre Aufgabe Wir beraten unsere Kunden rund um Machine Learning und Analytics und entwickeln mit diesen Technologien innovative Produkte. Sie bringen sich folgendermaßen in unser Team ein: Konzeption des mathematischen und statistischen Vorgehens für Machine Learning Lösungen in Zusammenarbeit mit Kunden Konzeption, technische Architektur und Umsetzung von Machine Learning Lösungen: End-to-End von der Ideenfindung über den Proof of Concept bis zur Produktion und kontinuierlichen Verbesserung Analyse und Extraktion von geschäftsentscheidenden Einsichten aus einer Vielzahl an Datenquellen Kundenkommunikation, Visualisierung, Dokumentation und Präsentation von aus Daten und durch Modellierung gewonnenen Einsichten Kommunikation und Präsentation auf Konferenzen, durch Vorträge und Publikationen Ihr Profil Sie sind ein erfahrener Consultant und Data Scientist, der andere anleiten und begeistern kann. Mit Tatendrang und Eigeninitiative gehen Sie im Team neue Herausforderungen an, treiben bestehende Projekte auf Grundlage eigener Erfahrung voran und entwickeln eine Gesamtvision. Sie überzeugen andere durch Ihr persönliches Auftreten und haben Spaß und Erfahrung im kundenorientierten Arbeiten. Ihre Basics, die Sie in mehreren Jahren praktischer Erfahrung erworben haben, sind: Mindestens drei Jahre Erfahrung in Machine Learning mit klassischen Methoden und Deep Learning, Statistik, Datenanalyse sowie verteiltem Rechnen Erfahrung in der Organisation und Struktur von datengetriebenen und Machine Learning Projekten Mehrere Jahre Erfahrung mit Python und seinem numerischen Ökosystem, insbesondere mit Pandas, Scikit-Learn, Numpy/Scipy, Matplotlib, Jupyter, Anaconda, Tensorflow / Pytorch Grundlegende Kenntnisse in R und SQL Praktisches Know how im Data Engineering und Feature Engineering Reisebereitschaft und Spaß daran, mit Kunden direkt vor Ort zusammen zu arbeiten Erfahrung in der Visualisierung, Kommunikation und Präsentation von Daten und analytischen Ergebnissen Fließende Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse Als weiteres Plus bringen Sie mit: Promotion in Mathematik, Informatik, Physik oder einer vergleichbaren quantitativen Fachrichtung, Erfahrung mit Konferenzbeiträgen und Publikationen in Fachjournalen Kenntnisse im Reinforcement Learning Erfahrung mit der Umsetzung von Clean Code Prinzipien, Test Driven Development und objektorientiertem Design in Machine Learning Projekten Kenntnisse in Julia, Scala und funktionaler Programmierung Erfahrung mit Spark und dem Hadoop Big Data Ökosystem Erfahrung mit agilen Projekten und ein DevOps Mindset der „Three Ways“ Über uns Multinationale Konzerne und öffentliche Institutionen sind unsere Kunden. Wir machen Wirtschaft und Gesellschaft startklar für die Gigabit-Gesellschaft. Überall auf der Welt. Mit einer globalen Infrastruktur aus Rechenzentren, Netzen und integrierten Lösungen. Sie haben Lust auf die vernetzte Zukunft? Dann zeigen Sie uns Ihre Innovationskraft.', 'Senior Consultant (m/w/d) Data Science', '2019-06-03', 'T-Systems International GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4804, 'SENIOR DATA SCIENTIST (m/f/d) BERLIN 70.000 - 95.000 + BENEFITS An exciting opportunity with one of the fastest growing companies in the financial sector just opened up. Are you passionate, driven and like to work in a truly international team? If this applies to you and you are ready to utilise your skills in an innovative, collaborative environment that will allow you to develop and advance your skills - this role is well suited for you. THE COMPANY You will be working with one of the leading companies in the fin tech sector in Europe. The company is going through strong growth as they are expanding and are in need for new talent to join their Berlin team. They offer the fantastic opportunity to work on challenging projects using machine learning. Supporting growth is key at this company hence, the candidate will benefit from regular feedback talks and support to develop yourself fin the company. They are located in very modern and open offices supporting a very welcoming work atmosphere. THE ROLE As a Senior Data Scientist in this fast-paced and international team, you will be working on large, diverse data sets alongside your colleagues to create innovative and forward-thinking data driven solutions for different solutions they are offering. The projects are solved in small teams consisting of highly motivated colleagues who like to push forward and learn from each other. The company puts great value that everyone can learn from each other hence, communication and willingness to learn is of great importance. In specific you can expect to be involved in the following: Machine learning is one of the core tasks from developing, testing and implementing machine learning algorithms using Python Develop and optimise supervised and unsupervised machine/deep learning models Work independently and try new approaches working with cloud solutions Work closely with the Data Engineering and Software Development team Have an entrepreneurial mindset, work independently and creatively on data driven solutions in order to ensure building and sustaining the best products YOUR SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Information Technology or Physics Relevant work experience in fast-paced environments and a strong background in Data Science/Analytics (random forests, deep neural networks) Excellent knowledge in Python, TensorFlow and Keras Strong knowledge of cloud solutions (AWS , Google Cloud) and Big Data Technologies (Hive, Spark) Being familiar with the whole process of model development ranging from data collection, validating and implementing Fluency in English, German is not required THE BENEFITS Salary ranging from 60.000 to 85.000 + Benefits A great team and company atmosphere with people from all over the world Work with cutting-edge technology Very modern and open offices Budget for your own development, conferences and workshops Great opportunity to grow within the company and being supported with your career development HOW TO APPLY Please register your interest by sending your CV to Sophia Fassbender at Harnham via the apply link on this page.', 'SENIOR DATA SCIENTIST', '2019-06-03', 'Harnham', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4805, 'Coordinator (m/f/d) for the International Max Planck Research School for Molecular Life Sciences, Munich Scientist Martinsried Developmental and Evolutionary Biology & Genetics Immunobiology and Infection Biology & Medicine Structural and Cell Biology Job Code: 303a Job Offer from May 02, 2019 The International Max Planck Research School for Molecular Life Sciences (IMPRS-LS) is a leading center for doctoral education providing interdisciplinary training to outstanding doctoral students in an environment of scientific excellence and collaboration. The school is a joint initiative of the Max Planck Institutes of Biochemistry and of Neurobiology as well as the Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München and the Technische Universität München. To strengthen our coordination office team, we seek an enthusiastic, self-motivated person with excellent organization- and communication skills as scientific coordinator (full time) at the earliest possible time point. Your profile You are expected to hold a PhD degree in the area of life sciences with a background covering some of the core competencies of the school’s research profile and have international experience in education, research or research administration. Moreover, you should enjoy working proactively, flexible and independently in a competitive international environment and be passionate about both, science and education. Previous experience with coordination of graduate training, data management and/or webpage design is considered highly advantageous. A very good command of spoken and written German and English is required. Your tasks will include planning, organization, coordination and continuous development of the IMPRS-LS training program;participation in coordination of the application procedures including marketing, selection of students and data management; managing administrative matters associated with IMPRS-LS; maintenance of the online application and data management system as well as of the homepage of IMPRS-LS; newsletter production, alumni work and maintenance of our social media platforms; providing practical and administrative support to foreign graduate students (e.g. Visa issues, accommodation, health insurance, child care and dealing with MPI, university and public administration); continuous quality management and conceptual further development of the program; We offer you An interesting and challenging position, initially limited for two years, in a leading international and interdisciplinary education program. A salary commensurate with your qualifications and responsibilities (starting with TVöD Bund level E13). Comprehensive employee benefits with a family-friendly culture at the institute and flexible working hours. Numerous opportunities for further training and development. The Max-Planck Society is committed to increasing the number of individuals with disabilities in its workforce and therefore encourages applications from such qualified individuals. The Max Planck Society strives for gender and diversity equality. We welcome applications from all backgrounds. Furthermore, the Max Planck Society seeks to increase the number of women in those areas where they are underrepresented and therefore explicitly encourages women to apply. Your application Qualified applicants are invited to apply online with representative documents as pdf files. Applications should be submitted no later than June 10, 2019. For further details regarding IMPRS-LS, please visit our homepage at www.imprs-ls.de.', 'Coordinator (m/f/d) for the International Max Planck Research School for Molecular Life Sciences, Munich', '2019-06-03', 'May 02', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4806, 'Making an impact that matters. Unser Anspruch ist, jeden Tag das zu tun, was wirklich zählt. Mit unserem breiten Leistungsspektrum – von Audit & Assurance, Risk Advisory über Tax & Legal bis Financial Advisory und Consulting – unterstützen wir Kunden auf einzigartige Weise. Wir setzen neue Maßstäbe, liefern innovative Denkansätze und ermöglichen nachhaltiges Wachstum. Wir fördern unsere hochqualifizierten Mitarbeiter mit ihren verschiedensten Talenten, sodass sie mit uns mehr erreichen. In unserem Deloitte Analytics Institute arbeiten wir in einem cross-funktionalen Expertenteam mit Kooperationspartnern aus Forschung und Wissenschaft sowie führenden Vendoren an innovativen und maßgeschneiderten Analytics-Lösungen für unsere namhaften Kunden. Für unsere Teams an den Standorten Berlin, Düsseldorf, Frankfurt und München suchen wir engagierte Verstärkung. Spannende Aufgaben erwarten Sie Identifizieren und Prägen von Trends im Bereich Big Data und Advanced Analytics im DAX30-Umfeld mit Start-up Atmosphäre Leitende Rolle im Data Science Bereich des Deloitte Analytics Institute und Subject Matter Expert bei Deloitte Begleitung von Projekten von der Entwurfsphase über die Entwicklung / Prototyping bis hin zu einer produktiven Umsetzung Nutzung von Data-Mining- und Machine-Learning-Techniken, um verschiedenste Modelle und geschäftsrelevante Erkenntnisse aus großen Mengen strukturierter und unstrukturierter Daten abzuleiten und systematisch zu validieren Zusammen mit führenden Wirtschafts- und Industrieexperten, Data Engineers und Informationsdesignern arbeiten Sie in marktrelevanten Projekten und präsentieren Ergebnisse gegenüber Kunden und Entwicklern Dabei haben Sie direkten Einfluss auf die Gestaltung von Analytics-Lösungen für eine Vielfalt von Stakeholdern, Industrien und Anwendungsgebieten Immer am Puls der Zeit identifizieren Sie Chancen für den Einsatz von neuen Technologien zum Lösen bestehender wie zukünftiger Anforderungen Darin sind Sie stark M.Sc. / PhD in Informatik, Physik, Mathematik, Statistik oder einem vergleichbaren quantitativen Feld und tiefgehendes theoretisches Verständnis zu Machine Learning und Data Mining Methoden Umfassende Kenntnisse im Projektmanagement größerer Data Analytics Projekte einschließlich Überzeugungskraft auf Top Management Level 5+ Jahre praktische Erfahrung im Bereich Data Science einschließlich der Umsetzung mit Systemen wie Python Pandas / scikit-learn, R, SAS oder SPSS Sehr gutes Verständnis des gesamten Prozesses der Datenanalyse von der Datengewinnung bis zur nutzerfokussierten Visualisierung im Frontend Nachweisbare Expertise in der Softwareentwicklung für den Aufbau und die produktive Umsetzung von Analytics Anwendungen (Methoden; Stack), idealerweise Erfahrung mit Big-Data-Lösungen und Konzepten (z.B. Hadoop, Spark) Reisebereitschaft sowie sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse Analytische und innovative Denkweise, Experimentierfreude sowie die Fähigkeit zum Multitasking Was Sie von uns erwarten können Neben einem sicheren Arbeitsplatz in einer angenehmen, kollegialen Atmosphäre bieten wir Ihnen ein chancenreiches, internationales Arbeitsumfeld. Hier warten vielfältige Projekte bei Kunden unterschiedlicher Branchen auf Sie. Bei uns gelten flache Hierarchien und ein Prinzip der offenen Tür. Ein weiterer Pluspunkt: Mit der Deloitte University verfolgen wir einen einzigartigen innovativen Ansatz für Ihre Weiterentwicklung. Durch ein für Sie maßgeschneidertes World Class Curriculum stellen wir sicher, dass Sie über das Know-how und die Qualifikation verfügen, um für unsere Kunden die besten Lösungen zu entwickeln. Sie sind interessiert? Wir freuen uns auf Sie', 'Senior- / Manager (m/w/d) Consulting - Data Scientist Analytics', '2019-06-03', 'Deloitte', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (4807, 'arivis, a world leader in 3D/4D image visualization, interaction, and analysis is searching for a talented individual to join our team as a business development manager. This position will provide direct sales interaction with arivis’s US potential customer base for arivis InViewR the first and only virtual reality system in the world to allow users to experience, interact with, and analyze their native imaging data in virtual reality without conversion. Candidate will have the opportunity to develop the market in their geographic region by providing information on the product and solutions to customers. Position provides ample opportunity for rapid advancement and increased earning potential. Position is ideal for candidates that enjoy travel but can also work easily out of their home office in their region. Will only consider exceptional candidates residing outside defined geographic region. Requirements for this position are: Imaging experience with Confocal, Multi-photon, Spinning Disk, Light Sheet, Widefield, live-cell 3D microscopes, and / or electron microscopy (EM), and / or 3D X-Ray or CT / MRI imaging Strong computer skills Experience with image data processing Outgoing personality with an affinity for self-motivation and responsibility Interest in scientific advances and innovations in image analysis and advanced optics. Excellent communication skills, oral, and written Ability to explain complex concepts in a concise manner Ability to vertically interface with multiple levels of diverse professional clients Degree or equivalent in a science or engineering discipline Highly desirable, but not required: Experience as a sales, application scientist, or technical supporter (in particular, in selling or supporting technical high-value software and/or microscopy hardware) Well-founded knowledge in the life sciences; biology, neuroscience or material sciences markets. Desirable, but not required: Technical knowledge of PC hardware, subsystems, peripheral and networking equipment Experience and knowledge of the Virtual Reality / Augmented Reality market and products Tasks and Duties: Sales Achieve and surpass all quarterly and annual sales target numbers. Research customers’ image analysis needs and provide solutions in a professional and effective manner. Perform customized customer demonstrations in a manner tailored for customer’s specific scientific needs. Provide answers to pre-sales technical and commercial questions from customers. Follow-up on all sales opportunities within a timely manner. Develop new business relationships within the defined territory with key science centers and scientists as well as strengthening existing customer relationships. Represent and promote the company in professional manner at courses, tradeshows and conferences. Channels Provide support for existing channel partners. Establish and maintain industry contacts that lead to sales. Maintain up-to-date understanding of industry trends and technical developments that impact target markets. Sales Management Manage designated sales leads, prospects and customer accounts in line with agreed business objectives. Manage and report sales bookings, potential sales, customer feedback and activity plan and other reports as required. Continually compile market information/intelligence on dedicated regions with a view to providing market feedback to assist in the shaping of future company strategy and product development. Regularly attend sales meetings and offer feedback and suggestions to improve product solutions. Compensation: Benefits include a base salary, performance based commission, 401K plan, healthcare, and vacation. Employee will work out of a home office. Travel and home office expenses are company paid. Please email CV and Cover Letter to: Michael C. Wussow Vice President Sales and Marketing – Imaging michael.wussowarivis.com +1 651-336-4600', 'Business Development Manager Southern US Based', '2019-06-03', 'Arivis', 'Data Scientist', 'Berlin', 'Indeed.com');
