INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5106, 'JOB PURPOSE/ROLE You will assume responsibility for the analysis of data sets utilised by the Global Investment Platform at Allianz Global Investors as part of the Investment Data Analysis team within the Global CIO Office. The Global CIO Office is a business management function supporting the Investment Platform at Allianz Global Investors. CIO - Chief Investment Officer KEY RESPONSIBILITIES Represent the Investment Platform on key AllianzGI data related strategic, operational and regulatory driven projects Data Analysis focused on optimising data utilisation across the Global Investment Platform (including but not limited to analysis of market data, firm reference data, firm-generated data, meta data) Meta Data Analysis and market data vendor cross-mapping - detailed analysis of data sets describing other data sets to automate data on-boarding and catalogue creation Data Automation for Investment Professionals - consultation and implementation of automation of data tasks for the Global Investment Platform Data Set Evaluation - consultation for the firm''s Investment Professionals when there is demand for data Data Governance - implementation of data governance best practice Data Quality analysis and rule set creation - ongoing analysis of data quality metrics, implementation of new data quality rules and working with data users to agree workflow for data quality problems Data Tooling specification, scoping and build - developing custom tooling as required to deal with data analysis, cataloguing or wrangling Primarily based in London or Frankfurt, but with opportunities to travel across all geographies when the need arises KEY REQUIREMENTS/SKILLS/EXPERIENCE Significant experience of working with data within an Investment Management environment Ability to problem-solve and think critically and independently Excellent analytical skillset with a core focus on data analysis and data wrangling Strong written communication (including presentations) skillset with high proficiency in English Strong verbal communication skillset with an ability to explain complex topics simply Strong programming skills with working experience of at least two of Python, SQL or R Expert-level proficiency with everyday workplace tools like MS Office, VBA, etc. Microsoft Azure suite experience advantageous Data science experience advantageous Investment data lifecycle and Investment lifecycle knowledge advantageous Market data analysis / management experience a plus Project Management skills / experience is beneficial Good fit to team dynamic Motivated to help others realise value from data Spoken German or French advantageous Reference Code AGI-5939228-5 Allianz is the home for those who dare – a supportive place where you can take the initiative to grow and to actively strengthen our global leadership position. By truly caring about people – both its 88 million private and corporate customers and more than 140,000 employees – Allianz fosters a culture where its employees are empowered to collaborate, perform, embrace trends and challenge the industry. Our main ambition is to be our customers’ trusted partner, instilling them with the confidence to grow. If you dare, join us at Allianz Group. Allianz is an equal opportunity employer. Everybody is welcome, regardless of other characteristics such as gender, age, origin, nationality, race or ethnicity, religion, disability, or sexual orientation. Allianz Global Investors is a leading active asset manager with over 770 investment professionals in 25 offices worldwide and managing EUR 535 billion in assets for individuals, families and institutions. Active is how we create and share value with clients. We believe in solving, not selling, adding value beyond pure economic gain. We invest long-term, drawing upon our broad and innovative investment expertise, and leveraging resources globally to ensure a superior client experience wherever they are based and whatever their investment needs. Active is: Allianz Global Investors You are committed to creating value for our clients so that they can meet their financial objectives throughout their lives. You embrace a collegial culture based on strong values, take individual responsibility, and are dedicated to mastering challenging tasks. You aspire to make an impact in a diverse, international, technology-enabled and increasingly agile environment. If you feel inspired to elevate the active asset management experience, this is the place for you since, Active is: Allianz Global Investors.', 'Data Analyst (f/m/d) for Investment', '2019-06-27', 'Allianz Global Investors', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5107, 'Field of activity StatistiX® is the Data Warehouse of Deutsche Börse Group. StatistiX® provides external and internal users worldwide with statistical information on financial markets. Aim of the position is not only to support the StatistiX DevOps Team of the classical Data Warehouse, but also to support the journey to a state of the art data lake. The job position requires a sound IT-operations know-how in order to be able to work in a rather self-contained environment and additionally a motivation to analyze problems and work out own solutions. Tasks/responsibilities Actively support the move from a classical Data Warehouse towards a Data Lake solution Participate in setting up the new infrastructure as well as building own POCs Creation and distribution of pre-defined standard reports to Business Units Understand DevOps as a culture Monitoring of production systems, interfaces and databases using events and alerts in Informatica, Control-M and the big data architecture (based on Spark and Hadoop) Investigation of impact of occurring errors within the entire job-schedule Incident management: First level support for users (acting as point of contact) Qualifications/required skills University degree in «Computer Science» and/or a comparable training At least 2 years of relevant professional experience Experience in one of these fields as well as a high interest in learning the other on the job is required: Classic Data Warehousing with Oracle, Control-M and Informatica PowerCenter or similar tools Data Lake Architecture with respective tools (Spark, Hadoop), major Cloud providers (Azure, AWS, GCP), programming languages (Go, Python), container / container cluster (Docker, Kubernetes) Experience with today’s data analytics tools (e.g. Trifacta, Zeppelin, Kylin) desirable An affinity for analyses and problem solving is highly desirable, incl. the associated skills Proficiency in written and spoken English is mandatory; French/German language skills will be an asset Proactive workstyle, experience in DevOps environments / SRE teams desirable What we offer: flexible working hours international working environment BVV pension plan Cantine with subsidised meals Jobticket and free parking spots and much more... There are numerous good reasons to work for us: responsibility at an early stage, attractive social benefits, an international work environment and a broad variety of career opportunities. Are you interested in working with a pleasant and very dedicated team? Convince us with an appealing application. Please use our online application portal. Deutsche Börse Group, Human Resources', 'Data Warehouse / Big Data / Data Lake Operations Specialist (f/m/d)', '2019-06-27', 'Deutsche Börse', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5108, 'Field of activity The Equity & Index Sales team goal is to increase distribution, develop deep relationships and act as the trusted advisor for clients on the buy and sell side across the globe. The team sits in over ten offices in the EU, US and Asia regions and covers over 1000 members, customers and prospects. The Sales Operations team is the backbone of the sales team. The team provide the tools, solutions and support to help the sales organization run effectively and efficiently to meet the overall Equity and Index strategic objectives. They are a key ingredient for our customers to depend on Eurex as a trusted advisor in the trading process. As an analyst at Eurex you will gain expertise in areas of product development and strategies, regulatory environment and norms, and market structure, you will have an excellent opportunity to experience the financial markets live and gain valuable practical experience in an innovative and fast-growing industry. As an analyst you will be responsible for the collection and interpretation of a wide range of data (volumes, revenues, market share, pricing etc.), using a variety of technics, ranging from simple data aggregation via statistical analysis to more complex data analysis and project development. In addition, you will be required to develop your product and customer knowledge, analyse the developing market trends, and to contribute to the elaboration of multiyear business plans. Tasks/responsibilities Product Sales Support Work with the sales team to create innovative data-driven sales materials Build and present business cases assessing the potential of Eurex products and functionalities Track product targets and disseminate to the global sales team to keep sales team accountable and motivated Customer support Handle incoming ad-hoc requests from customers for data analytics using a variety of techniques ranging from data aggregation to more complex multi-criteria analysis Produce research-based customer intelligence reports, supporting the sales team’s own intelligence Sales Management support Manage CRM, sales process and create innovative solutions to track sales targets, monitoring performance and to ensure the sales team is performing against their target Produce monthly activity reports, internal senior management reports using both qualitative and quantitative data collective from internal and external sources Support senior management to manage global sales budget Analyst Program Learn the various businesses, operations and processes in an exchange Establish yourself as a liaison between the businesses to share workload and best practices Develop leadership and subject matter expertise to expand responsibilities in the exchange Qualifications/required skills University degree in mathematics/computer science Outstanding academic record Excellent written and verbal communication skills Strong quantitative and analytical skills Exceptional self-motivation and a natural drive to achieve excellence, must have an impeccable attention to detail Team-based philosophy as well as ability to work independently Demonstrated capability and willingness to take ownership of tasks Excellent technical skills: VBA, SQL, Python, Microsoft office tools, Bloomberg Ability to create databases Dedication, team and communication skills, flexibility as well as competent handling of MS Office applications round out your profile. There are numerous good reasons to work for us: responsibility at an early stage, attractive social benefits, an international working environment and a broad variety of career opportunities. Applications from disabled persons are welcome. Are you interested in working with a pleasant and very dedicated team? Convince us with an appealing application. Please use our online application portal. Deutsche Börse Group, Human Resources', 'Business Data Analyst - Equity and Index Sales Operations (f/m/d)', '2019-06-27', 'Deutsche Börse', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5109, 'We help our customers to find the right solutions for their digital needs. We are committed to finding business by accompanying them in the areas of data analytics and artificial intelligence consulting. Tasks Conception of mathematical and statistical procedures for Machine Learning solutions in cooperation with customers. Conception, technical architecture and implementation of Machine Learning solutions: End-to-end from brainstorming and proof of concept to production and continuous improvement. Analysis and extraction of critical business insights from a variety of data sources. Customer communication, visualization, documentation and presentation of insights gained from data and modeling. Communication and presentation at conferences, through lectures and publications. Requirements At least three years of experience in Machine Learning with classical methods and deep learning, statistics, data analysis and distributed computing. Experience in the organization and structure of data-driven and Machine Learning projects. Several years experience with Python and its numerical ecosystem, especially with Pandas, Scikit-Learn, Numpy/Scipy, Matplotlib, Jupyter, Anaconda, Tensorflow/Pytorch. Good knowledge of R and SQL. Practical know-how in data engineering and feature engineering. Willingness to travel and enjoy working directly with customers on site. Experience in visualization, communication and presentation of data and analytical results. Fluent in German and English. Another plus you bring with you: Doctorate in mathematics, computer science, physics or a comparable quantitative discipline, experience with conference contributions and publications in specialist journals. Knowledge in Reinforcement Learning. Experience with the implementation of clean code principles, test driven development and object-oriented design in machine learning projects. Knowledge of Julia, Scala and functional programming. Experience with Spark and the Hadoop Big Data Ecosystem. Experience with agile projects and a DevOps mindset. Benefits Flexible working time model. Mobile work and home office. Employer-funded pension. Individual further education offers. Employee benefits and discounts. State of the Art Equipment.', 'Senior Consultant (M/W/D) Data Science', '2019-06-27', 'Taledo', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5110, 'Du hast Talent. Wir sind ein internationales Netzwerk aus 250.930 Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeitern, die ihr Wissen, ihre Erfahrungen und ihre Ideen miteinander teilen. Du suchst einen herausfordernden, spannenden Job. Wir bieten dir als weltweit führende Wirtschaftsprüfungs- und Beratungsgesellschaft ein Maximum an Möglichkeiten für einen Karriereweg nach deinen Vorstellungen. Du möchtest Verantwortung für deine Ergebnisse übernehmen, Lösungen gemeinsam mit dem Kunden entwickeln und einen Arbeitgeber mit passenden Werten. Unser Denken und Handeln orientiert sich an Grundsätzen, die von Vertrauen, Respekt, Weitsicht und Wertschätzung geprägt sind. Deine Aufgaben Individuelles Traineeprogramm – Du durchläufst einen maßgeschneiderten, sechsmonatigen Ausbildungsplan, der dich optimal auf das Berufsfeld des Data-Analytics-Beraters vorbereitet. Hierbei spielen fachliche und technische Trainings ebenso eine wichtige Rolle wie Schulungen in Arbeitsmethoden, Projektorganisation und Kundenkommunikation. In regelmäßigen Reviews erhältst du strukturiertes Feedback zu deiner Entwicklung. Schwerpunktwahl Data Analytics und Digital Operations – Du leitest aus den Herausforderungen der Digitalisierung in den Bereichen Beschaffung, Logistik und Produktion die Anforderungen an Data-Analytics-Lösungen ab und entwickelst darauf basierend ganzheitliche Anwendungen von der Strategie über die Architektur bis hin zur Umsetzung. Das Team – Unser ambitioniertes Team besteht aus technologieaffinen Menschen mit unterschiedlichen fachlichen Hintergründen wie Informatik, Ingenieurwesen und Wirtschaftswissenschaften. Unsere technischen Skills kombinieren wir mit fachlicher Expertise in den Themenfeldern Digital Procurement, Smart Manufacturing sowie Smart Warehousing & Logistics. Mehrwert für unsere Kunden – In unseren Lösungen bringen wir innovative Technologien und Methoden zur Anwendung. Durch den Einsatz moderner Verfahren aus den Bereichen Big Data, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence und Cloud Computing, wie bspw. R, Python, Graph Datenbanken oder Azure Databricks und Data Lake, ermöglichen wir es unseren Kunden ihre Effizienz zu steigern, ihre Produkte zu verbessern und neue digitale Geschäftsmodelle zu erschließen. Dabei legen wir unseren Schwerpunkt auf die Branchen Automobilindustrie, Fertigungsindustrie, Handel und Konsumgüter. Dein Profil Dein Studium der (Wirtschafts-) Informatik, der Wirtschaftswissenschaften,des Wirtschaftsingenieurwesens oder eines verwandten Fachbereichs hast du erfolgreich abgeschlossen oder stehst kurz davor. Du bringst Begeisterung dafür mit, dich mit der neuesten Technologie auseinanderzusetzen und mit Hilfe von modernen Werkzeugen Lösungen in den Bereichen Big Data, Internet-of-Things, Machine Learning und AI zu entwickeln. Idealerweise kannst du erste Erfahrungen in der Beratungsbranche und/oder dem Bereich Digital Operations und/oder Data Analytics vorweisen. Du verfügst über gute Kommunikationsfähigkeiten, eine hohe Kundenorientierung und hast Spaß an der persönlichen Weiterentwicklung. Zu deinen Stärken zählen ein kompetentes Auftreten sowie ausgeprägte analytische und konzeptionelle Fähigkeiten. Die im Beratungsumfeld notwendige Mobilität und Reisebereitschaft sind für dich selbstverständlich. Sehr gute Deutsch- und gute Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift runden dein Profil ab. Du kannst dich für die Standorte Duisburg, Düsseldorf, Frankfurt (M), Stuttgart und München bewerben. Das Programm selbst findet jedoch in Duisburg statt. Start ist der 01.10.2019 oder der 01.04.2020. In unserem Geschäftsbereich Advisory verknüpfen wir fundierte Beratungskompetenz mit spezifischem Branchen-Kenntnissen. Als Teil unseres Teams gestaltest du Prozesse, Organisationen oder IT-Systeme und berätst namhafte Unternehmen zu betriebs- und finanzwirtschaftlichen sowie regulatorischen Themen. Oder du begleitest den gesamten Transaktionsprozess und machst Unternehmen fit für die Zukunft. In allen Bereichen bieten wir unseren Kunden einzigartige Lösungen – von der Strategie bis zur Umsetzung.', 'Trainee Data Analytics &amp; AI - Digital Operations (w/m/d) an verschiedenen Standorten', '2019-06-27', 'PwC', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5111, 'Senior Data Scientist(w/m/d) EnBW Energie Baden-Württemberg AG Vertrag unbefristet Köln Vollzeit Sie möchten die Innovationskultur der EnBW mitgestalten und in einer kreativen Umgebung arbeiten? Der Wandel in der Energiewirtschaft bedeutet für Sie mehr Chancen als Risiko? Sie wollen Verantwortung übernehmen und die EnBW bei der Entwicklung von neuen Produkten und Geschäftsmodellen tatkräftig unterstützen und sind immer auf der Suche nach neuen Herausforderungen? Dann kommen Sie zu ins „EnBW Data Lab“. Ihre Aufgaben Eigenständige Entwicklung von Analyse- und Prognose-Modellen Überführung von Modellen in produktive Systeme Zusammenarbeit mit Kunden zur Identifizierung und Entwicklung von wirtschaftlichen Use-Cases Bewertung der Ergebnisse bzgl. unternehmerischem Nutzen Weiterentwicklung von analytischen Ansätzen Impulse aus dem Markt aufnehmen und in das Team tragen Ihr Profil Mit überdurchschnittlichem Erfolg abgeschlossenes Hochschulstudium der Fachrichtungen Statistik, Mathematik, (Wirtschafts-)Informatik oder vergleichbarer Schwerpunkt, Promotion wünschenswert Sehr gute Kenntnisse in Statistik, Datenanalyse und Machine Learning Erfahrung mit R, alternativ auch Python oder MatLab Erfahrung mit mathematischer Optimierung wünschenswert Praktische Programmierkenntnisse (z. B. Software-Entwicklung, R-Pakete, Error-Handling etc.) Mehrjährige Erfahrung in analytischen Projekten (z. B. Datenanalyse, Modellentwicklung) Datenbank-Kenntnisse, idealerweise praktische Erfahrung mit Datenbank-Technologien in der Cloud Das sind wir Gemeinsam bringen wir die wichtigen Dinge voran: Wir von der EnBW entwickeln intelligente Energieprodukte, machen unsere Städte nachhaltiger und treiben den Ausbau erneuerbarer Energien voran. Dafür benötigen wir tatkräftige Unterstützung – Machen Sie mit! Unser Angebot Spannende Aufgaben eröffnen vielfältige Perspektiven zur persönlichen Entwicklung Kollegiale Zusammenarbeit im Team und moderne Arbeitsplätze zeichnen uns aus Arbeiten mit neusten Technologien und Konzepten im Bereich Big Data Analytics Flexible Arbeitszeitmodelle ermöglichen die Vereinbarkeit von Beruf und Privatleben Attraktive Mitarbeiterangebote zählen zu unseren Stärken Die EnBW im Social Web', 'Senior Data Scientist (w/m/d) – Köln', '2019-06-27', 'EnBW Energie Baden-Württemberg AG', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5112, 'Job Summary This is an exciting opportunity to join one of the top UK pharmaceutical companies, dedicated to creating and delivering innovative pharmaceutical health care solutions that enable people to live longer and healthier. Roles & Responsibilities of the position The development of best-in-industry Data Science capabilities is critical to our ambition to be most innovative healthcare company. Combining various data streams and providing data near real-time data and visualizations are key component to obtaining our ambitions. We are looking for individuals who have aptitude and motivation learn the next generation data visualization strategy and help shape and grow with us in this journey. The position is primarily accountable for providing expertise, delivery and oversight of technical clinical data management activities from data stream integrations to submission-ready tabulation packages. Also responsible for contributing to our automation and innovation efforts. Principle Responsibilities Include; Development of data transfer agreements with ancillary data vendors ensuring use of standards, fit-for purpose data models and transfer intervals. Create and review specifications and mapping for data models to be used for quality review and for final data model (SDTM or other). Ensure quality review of datasets (e.g., Pinnacle 21 compliance checking); ensure datasets are available for stakeholder use (medical review, central monitoring, adaptive decision making, etc.) and compliant for database lock and submission-ready tabulation packages. Develop and maintain working knowledge and expertise in programming languages utilized in current data management (SAS, SQL, etc.) and apply continuous learning as part of next generation data strategy (R, Python, Scala, Java, etc.). Job Requirements Bachelor''s degree in Computer or Life Sciences or equivalent work experience 7 years of relevant experience in pharmaceutical industry is desired, experience in other industries in Data Engineering role will also be considered In-depth knowledge of protocol, current clinical drug development processes preferred General knowledge of eDC systems Expert programming skills SAS, SQL or other languages R, Python, etc. Expert knowledge of SDTM including Define.xml, CDASH, metadata preferred Ability to work with cross-functional team interpreting data requirements. Strong project management skills and knowledge of team management principles are required. Excellent written and verbal communication skills Aptitude and motivation learn new technologies and make appropriate recommendations for consideration is preferred. Vendor management oversight experience Remuneration & other details Competitive salary Home -Based Permanent Position', 'Technical Data Architect III (Principal SDTM Programmer)', '2019-06-27', 'Docs Global (Continental Europe)', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5113, 'DEINE AUFGABEN: Konzeption und Entwicklung von Forecasting Modellen (z.B. Order Forecast) und komplexeren Analytics Lösungen Nutzung von Data Mining-, statistischen Modellierungs- und Machine Learning-Ansätzen Identifizierung, Beschaffung und Aufbereitung relevanter Daten Aktive Suche nach möglichen weiteren Anwendungsfällen für Data Science Testen und bewerten von neuen Methoden, Technologien und Best Practices für die Verwendung im Unternehmen DEIN PROFIL: Du hast schon ein großen Teil deines Studiums der (Wirtschafts-) Informatik, Mathematik oder Physik abgeschlossen Du hast Erfahrungen im Bereich Data Science, Data Analytics bzw. Business Intelligence Du hast ein tieferes Verständnis für Datenbankstrukturen und Datenaufbereitung Du Erfahrung im Einsatz von R, Python oder KNIME Du kannst komplexe Zusammenhänge zwischen unseren Geschäftsprozessen und verschiedensten Daten herstellen und erkennen Du besitzt ausgeprägte analytische und konzeptionelle Fähigkeiten und kannst deine Auswertungen transparent Du arbeitest systematisch, bist selbstständig und bringst Eigeninitiative mit Gute Kommunikationsfähigkeit sowohl im Deutschen als auch Englischen in Wort und Schrift Hohes Engagement, Teamfähigkeit und Flexibilität. DEINE CHANCE: Spannende Aufgaben mit viel Gestaltungsspielraum innerhalb einer flachen Hierarchie und offenen Kommunikationskultur Ausgeprägtes Teamgefühl bei regelmäßigen Teamevents, gemeinsamen Mittagspausen etc. Erfolgreiche Zukunft und vielfältige Entwicklungs- und Karriereperspektiven in einem stark wachsenden und sehr abwechslungsreichen Unternehmen Haben wir Ihr Interesse geweckt? Dann übersenden Sie uns Ihre vollständigen Bewerbungsunterlagen an karriere@qubix.de', 'Praktikant Data Scientist (w/m) im Bereich e-Commerce', '2019-06-27', 'Qubix Consulting GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5114, 'Focus: Computer Vision and Deep Learning If your understanding of fun is reading up on the latest deep learning developments and when you’re eager to realize these new insights into reality - then you’ll be a great fit! We’re looking for experienced Data Scientists who are fearlessly curious truth seekers and who enjoy bringing the best out of themselves and our team. At zeroG we put people at the heart of our work, therefore we’re interested in the story behind the CV. Include in your cover letter an example of how you brought a great idea to leave and what your learned along the way. We combine aviation and data science know-how and work on the basis of distributed authority, collective intelligence, and a high degree of self-organization. By unlocking the intrinsic power of data, we generate new insights, develop data-driven business models, and innovative solutions that improve aviation. We cultivate diversity, mutual trust, and a positive family spirit – making zeroG unlike other organizations. To experience more about our growing company, check out our website and take a minute to watch our company video. zerog.aero/career Your role Provide clarity and generate new insights from big and complex data sets. Conduct complex, non-standard analysis. Apply advanced analytical models where appropriate. Get accustomed to the intricacies of aviation data and KPIs, lead and participate in the development of value creating use cases Iteratively build and prototype robust analytical pipelines to provide valuable insight and foresight Design and implement data pipelines in close collaboration with Data Engineers Appraisal of new tools and technologies regarding their use and benefit Interact cross-functionally within interdisciplinary environments from IT to Business Lead project teams and take responsibility for keeping our customers and team happy Engage with clients along the entire project life-cycle and actively manage a positive client relationship What we offer Join zeroG in an early stage and help us scale Start-up culture, with great benefits being a part of the Lufthansa Group Autonomy to realize great ideas and develop yourself personally An international, highly-skilled and diverse team that feels like a family Your profile Minimum Qualifications: A minimum of four years of professional experience and a Master’s degree in a quantitative discipline such as (but not exclusively) computer science, mathematics or physics Working experience with common analytical tools (e.g. R, Python, pandas, scikit-learn) and database languages (e.g. SQL) Knowledge and experience in statistics and machine learning Experience in advanced analytical concepts such as Deep Learning and/or Reinforcement Learning. Experience in classical computer vision (incl. tracking, optical flow and/ or stereo matching) Experience in applying advanced analytical techniques in real world projects A proven track record of leading analytical projects and successful client engagements Strong communicator and comfortable in designing and delivering presentations A strong desire to learn every day, self-starter mentality, and passion for analytics Up-to-date on state-of-the-art papers on advanced analytical concepts Enjoys sharing knowledge in the team and helping others shine Proficiency in English, a good sense of humor, and a love for aviation are also important to us. Preferred Qualifications: PhD in a Quantitative Academic Field Working experience using Big Data technologies such as the Hadoop Stack Working experience with data science software platforms such as SAS, Rapidminer, KNIME or SPSS Experience in project management (agile and waterfall), agile innovation methodologies (design thinking, design sprint), consulting projects and/or the aviation environment is a plus Your benefit Old-age provision / employee retirement Flight discounts Service phone Discounts / shopping Working at home Flexible working hours Development programs Vacation Days About zeroG GmbH At zeroG we combine airline and data science know-how and work on the basis of distributed authority, collective intelligence and a high degree of self-organization. By unlocking the intrinsic power of data, we generate new insights, develop data-driven business models and innovative solutions that elevate aviation. Our team cultivates diversity, mutual trust and a positive family spirit – making zeroG unlike other organizations. For further information: Abbi Wensyel: abbi.wensyel@zerog.aero', 'Lead Data Scientist', '2019-06-27', 'zeroG GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5115, 'Deine Persönlichkeit und Individualität machen den Unterschied. Im Team von Accenture steigern wir die unternehmerische Leistungsfähigkeit unserer Kunden und weisen ihnen den Weg ins digitale Zeitalter. So auch im Bereich Digital: Hier verbessern wir das Leben von Millionen von Menschen – als Impulsgeber noch nie dagewesener digitaler Produkte und Lösungen. Das ist genau dein Ding? Dann lebe deine Leidenschaft in einer Position, in der du innerhalb einer hochdynamischen Arbeitsatmosphäre immer neue und anspruchsvolle Projekte unserer weltweit aufgestellten Kunden begleitest. Die Anwendung neuester Technologien und vielfältige Wachstumsmöglichkeiten helfen dir außerdem dabei, gemeinsam mit uns persönlich, fachlich und beruflich zu wachsen. Hier machst du den Unterschied Du entwickelst innovative und umsetzbare datengesteuerte Lösungen für den Gesundheitsmarkt Zudem leitest du die entsprechenden Maßnahmen ein, um die Lösungsansätze umzusetzen In diesem Zusammenhang koordinierst du anspruchsvolle Projekte, inklusive der Entwicklung von Proof of Concepts Dabei stehst du stets in engem Kontakt zu Entscheidern auf Kundenseite Basierend auf deiner Erfahrung übernimmst du außerdem die Teamleitung und unterstützt bei der Angebotserstellung Hiermit kommst du bei uns an Abgeschlossenes Studium (Master oder PhD) in (Bio-)Informatik, (Bio-)Statistik, Biotechnologie oder einer vergleichbaren Richtung Know-how in Machine Learning, NP, Deep Learning, Spieltheorie und Forecasting Kenntnisse rund um SAS, R, Python, Hadoop, Spark, SQL, SPSS und MATLAB Sehr gutes Deutsch und Englisch Hohe Reisebereitschaft und Flexibilität Dein Kontakt Du hast Fragen? Dann wende dich an unser Recruiting Team per E-Mail an recruiting.germany@accenture.com oder telefonisch unter 00800 45045045. Wir freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung über unser Online-Formular.', 'Data Scientist/Consultant (all genders) Life Science', '2019-06-27', 'Accenture', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5116, 'Machen Sie mit uns den Unterschied. Bei Accenture Digital sind Sie maßgeblich daran beteiligt die Welt von morgen mitzugestalten – in Expertenteams, in denen Zusammenarbeit und Wissensaustausch großgeschrieben werden. Mit Ihrem Know-how verschaffen Sie unseren Kunden den entscheidenden Wettbewerbsvorsprung und führen Unternehmen erfolgreich in die Zukunft. Ihre Aufgaben Folgen Sie Ihrer Leidenschaft für Statistik, Mathematik und Data Science, um Ihren Kunden Erkentnisse zu liefern, die es ihnen ermöglichen, Spitzenleistungen zu erzielen. Was es braucht, um erfolgreich zu sein? Neben quantitativen Fähigkeiten, auch starke Beratungskompetenz. Wenn diese Fähigkeiten zu Ihren Stärken zählen, sind Sie die genau der richtige Kandidat für diese Position: Go for it! Verwenden Sie Ihre Geschäftssinn und analytischen Verstand, um innovative und umsetzbare datengesteuerte Lösungen für unsere Kunden zu entwickeln Als Teil eines internationalen Teams entwickeln Sie wertvolle Einblicke mit Hilfe von Advanced Analytics Modellen und verwalten große Mengen von strukturierten und unstrukturierten Daten auf der Grundlage Ihrer nachgewiesenen Data Science Kenntnisse Sie stehen in engem Kontakt mit den Entscheidern auf Kundenseite. Verstehen es Problemlösungen zu adressieren und entsprechend qualitativ zu lösen. Mit all Ihrer Erfahrung und kreativem Denken bringen Sie das Team vorran um Innovationen und die nächste Generation von Analytics-Angeboten zu schaffen. Abgeschlossenes Studium in Statistik, Betriebswirtschaft oder Ingenieurswissenschaften Nachgewiesene Kenntnisse in der Anwendung statistischer Methoden oder Machine Learning wie Monte Carlo/ Monty Hall Simulation, Design of Experiment, Segmentierung (Cluster Analyse), Exploraty Analytics (t-tests), Multivariate Regression (Logistic, OLS, GLM, etc.), Entscheidungsbäume, Non-Linear Modeling und Optimierung in relevantem Businesskontext Erfahrungen im Gebrauch digitaler und statistischer Modellierungssoftware wie R, SAS, SPSS, MATLAB oder Python Gute Kenntnisse traditioneller Datenbanken (Oracle, Teradata, Sybase, MS SQL) wie auch Big Data oder In-Memory Datenbanken (Hadoop, SAP HANA, Graph DB etc.) Erste Praxiseinblicke im Umgang mit BI and Visualization Tools (Cognos, Business Objects, Tableau, Spotfire) sind von Vorteil Hohe Reisebereitschaft und Flexibilität Sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse werden vorausgesetzt Accenture steht als Arbeitgeber für Chancengleichheit und begrüßt Bewerbungen aus allen Teilen der Gesellschaft. Wir diskriminieren niemanden aufgrund von Glaube, Herkunft, Behinderung, Alter, Nationalität, Familienstand, Partnerschaftsstatus, sexueller Orientierung, Geschlecht oder anderen gesetzlich geschützten Gründen.', 'Data Scientist/Consultant (all genders) Advanced Analytics', '2019-06-27', 'Accenture', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5117, 'Field of activity Deutsche Börse Group is one of the largest exchange organisations and market infrastructure providers worldwide – and information technology is our backbone. Our business is mainly transaction and data-driven, and is powered by an incredible amount of incoming real-world financial market data every day. Our software engineers engage in an array of fields, from latency-optimisation (nano-seconds) of our trading applications, to risk and margin calculator algorithms, expansion of data APIs on our digital business platform, and machine learning and natural language processing. If you strive to take ownership and develop creative solutions, are fascinated by technology, and like to work in a challenging and fast paced environment – then you are exactly the person we are looking for. Tasks/responsibilities Participation in the development of software for the financial industry Support senior programmer and analysts to build the libraries and frameworks of Microservices and APIs that support customer delivery excellence Join an agile team and develop new applications and functionalities Participate in all stages of the software lifecycle (design, implementation, test and production support) to ensure high quality and security standards Contribute to the transformation of our legacy applications into a modern cloud-based microservices architecture Qualifications/required skills Current studies in Computer Science or equivalent Experience with one or more general purpose programming languages including Go, Python, or Java Understanding of data structures and first experience with SQL Background knowledge on financial markets, systems and process would be an advantage Excellent written and spoken English skills alongside good communication and collaboration skills Practical experience with development of cloud-based applications (AWS, Azure or GCP) would be an advantage Practical experience with Business Intelligence, Data Warehouse and Data Lake technologies would be an advantage Experience with relational and non-relational database technologies (Oracle, Hive) would be an advantage Practical experience with an agile development methodology would be an advantage There are numerous good reasons to work for us: responsibility at an early stage, attractive social benefits, an international work environment and a broad variety of career opportunities. Are you interested in working with a pleasant and very dedicated team? Convince us with an appealing application. Please use our online application portal. Deutsche Börse Group, Human Resources', 'Student Assistant - Financial Industry / Data Warehouse / Data Platform (f/m/d)', '2019-06-27', 'Deutsche Börse', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5118, 'We, as Lufthansa AirPlus Servicekarten GmbH in Neu-Isenburg, are currently looking for support within our Division Marketing. The following tasks are part of your responsibility: We are looking for a Product Manager Data Strategy and Artificial Intelligence that likes to work with us in a fast paced and dynamic team to bring the AirPlus data products to the next level In your role, you will be responsible for creating data-based products to provide new and meaningful insights for our corporate customer to radically push forward their experience with AirPlus You will take over full ownership for the AirPlus product data strategy and artificial intelligence, you will be involved in projects and product development teams and push forward the realization of data-based products and business models in a holistic manner In this role, you will be an innovation driver, contributing to AirPlus staying ahead of the game by understanding and managing the value proposition, customer experience and technological developments You strive to research customer needs, future setups, have an ability and interest in trend scouting, understanding changing implications and their impact on the respective business model You will interface strongly with other product management, market intelligence and communications teams as well as sales, finance, legal and governance divisions to ensure efficient and compliant results of your profit delivering activities Your profile You are a creative problem solver and analytical thinker that likes to think outside the box without losing focus on priorities You have graduated from college or university in business studies or economics or in a comparable field and have at least three years of work experiences in product operations and/or management You have a deep understanding of what is possible today and what will soon be possible considering in data driven business models You have experience in creating value and monetizing data-based products such as customer reporting and analytics software. You are further experienced in designing and executing machine learning and artificial intelligence systems Experiences in agile product development methodologies such as design thinking, lean startup and scrum is a benefit You have comprehensive computer skills, including standard applications such as Microsoft Office You offer very good communication skills and are self-confident to work in an international environment and across different hierarchy levels To succeed in this role, you have to work independently in a very reliable manner The capability to cope with strong workload in line with an adequate accuracy, taking constructive feedback and conflicts is substantial International business trips can occur Very good written and spoken English skills are required Your benefit Old-age provision / employee retirement Financial consulting / social counseling Free parking Flight discounts Canteen (subsidized by employer) Jobticket Discounts / shopping Employee events (summer festivals, participation in sports competitions etc) Sabbatical / exemptions Part-time models Health days Working at home Family service (assistance with finding assistance) Flexible working hours Development programs Doctoral studies / Master‘s degree / Ph.D. Mentoring Fitness studio / sports facilities / company football etc. Massages, rest rooms, etc Lockers for cyclists / sportsmen Have a shower Free snacks / drinks About Lufthansa AirPlus Servicekarten GmbH AirPlus is a leading provider of corporate travel payment solutions for over 49,000 corporate customers worldwide. As the market leader in Germany with 25 years of experience, AirPlus is well known for innovations and expertise in the Business Travel Payment and Analysis area. With about 1,300 employees globally, AirPlus is a competent and reliable partner in matters relating to Business Travel Management. In order to maintain this high standard, the skills of our employees and the development of their potential, are especially important to us. www.airplus.com', 'Product Manager Data Strategy &amp; AI (m/f/diverse)', '2019-06-27', 'Lufthansa AirPlus Servicekarten GmbH', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
INSERT INTO test.Ausschreibungen (ausschreibungs_id, ausschreibungs_inhalt, ausschreibungs_titel, datum, firma, suchbegriff_job, suchbegriff_ort, webseite) VALUES (5119, 'As an Analyst, you will: Have expertise in R/SAS or similar tools and willing to specialize in analytics Deliver on analytics projects as part of a team Extract data and perform analysis as per plan Cleanse and process data utilizing data processing tools as well as a variety of other applications Conduct exploratory analysis to look for patterns Develop the analytic models using SAS/R or equivalent tools. Develop data analyses and visualization using a range of tools such as Tableau, Qlikview, equivalents. Perform data validation to ensure accuracy and quality of data What are we looking for: MBA, BE, BS, MS (Math, Finance, Stats, OR, Computer Engg.), or a CFA with relevant experience Strong problem-solving skills with good knowledge of SAS / R or equivalent tools. 3 – 5 years of programming experience in R / SAS or equivalent tools. Expertise in Big Data technologies such as HIVE, HDFS, Spark. Hands-on experience in SQL coding Knowledge of data visualization tools such as Tableau, Qlikview will be an added advantage. Knowledge of analytics using any big data platform is a plus Have analytics experience in one or more of the functional areas: oCustomer Analytics, CRM oSales & Marketing Analytics oWeb & Social Media Analytics oManufacturing, Supply Chain, Inventory & Operations Analytics oCPG Analytics, Pricing Analytics oFinancial & Risk Analytics Effective communication skills', 'Analyst - Data Science', '2019-06-27', 'ITL Germany', 'Data Scientist', 'Frankfurt am Main', 'Indeed.com');
